52llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCastToVoidPtr(llvm::Value *value) {
53 unsigned addressSpace =
54 cast<llvm::PointerType>(value->getType())->getAddressSpace();
55
56 llvm::PointerType *destType = Int8PtrTy;
57 if (addressSpace)
58 destType = llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(getLLVMContext(), addressSpace);
59
60 return EmitPointerCast(value, destType);
61}

63/// CreateTempAlloca - This creates a alloca and inserts it into the entry
64/// block.
65Address CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(llvm::Type *Ty,
66 CharUnits Align,
67 const Twine &Name,
68 llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
69 auto Alloca = CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Name, ArraySize);
70 Alloca->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
71 return Address(Alloca, Align);
72}
73
74/// CreateTempAlloca - This creates a alloca and inserts it into the entry
75/// block. The alloca is casted to default address space if necessary.
76Address CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty, CharUnits Align,
77 const Twine &Name,
78 llvm::Value *ArraySize,
79 Address *AllocaAddr) {
80 auto Alloca = CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(Ty, Align, Name, ArraySize);
81 if (AllocaAddr)
82 *AllocaAddr = Alloca;
83 llvm::Value *V = Alloca.getPointer();
84 // Alloca always returns a pointer in alloca address space, which may
85 // be different from the type defined by the language. For example,
86 // in C++ the auto variables are in the default address space. Therefore
87 // cast alloca to the default address space when necessary.
88 if (getASTAllocaAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default) {
89 auto DestAddrSpace = CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default);
90 llvm::IRBuilderBase::InsertPointGuard IPG(Builder);
91 // When ArraySize is nullptr, alloca is inserted at AllocaInsertPt,
92 // otherwise alloca is inserted at the current insertion point of the
93 // builder.
94 if (!ArraySize)
95 Builder.SetInsertPoint(AllocaInsertPt);
96 V = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
97 *this, V, getASTAllocaAddressSpace(), LangAS::Default,
98 Ty->getPointerTo(DestAddrSpace), /*non-null*/ true);
99 }
100
101 return Address(V, Align);
102}
103
104/// CreateTempAlloca - This creates an alloca and inserts it into the entry
105/// block if \p ArraySize is nullptr, otherwise inserts it at the current
106/// insertion point of the builder.
107llvm::AllocaInst *CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,
108 const Twine &Name,
109 llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
110 if (ArraySize)
111 return Builder.CreateAlloca(Ty, ArraySize, Name);
112 return new llvm::AllocaInst(Ty, CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace(),
113 ArraySize, Name, AllocaInsertPt);
114}
115
116/// CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca - This creates an alloca with the
117/// default alignment of the corresponding LLVM type, which is *not*
118/// guaranteed to be related in any way to the expected alignment of
119/// an AST type that might have been lowered to Ty.
120Address CodeGenFunction::CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,
121 const Twine &Name) {
122 CharUnits Align =
123 CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(Ty));
124 return CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Align, Name);
125}
126
127void CodeGenFunction::InitTempAlloca(Address Var, llvm::Value *Init) {
128 assert(isa<llvm::AllocaInst>(Var.getPointer()));
129 auto *Store = new llvm::StoreInst(Init, Var.getPointer());
130 Store->setAlignment(Var.getAlignment().getQuantity());
131 llvm::BasicBlock *Block = AllocaInsertPt->getParent();
132 Block->getInstList().insertAfter(AllocaInsertPt->getIterator(), Store);
133}

135Address CodeGenFunction::CreateIRTemp(QualType Ty, const Twine &Name) {
136 CharUnits Align = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
137 return CreateTempAlloca(ConvertType(Ty), Align, Name);
138}

140Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTemp(QualType Ty, const Twine &Name,
141 Address *Alloca) {
142 // FIXME: Should we prefer the preferred type alignment here?
143 return CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty), Name, Alloca);
144}

146Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTemp(QualType Ty, CharUnits Align,
147 const Twine &Name, Address *Alloca) {
148 return CreateTempAlloca(ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), Align, Name,
149 /*ArraySize=*/nullptr, Alloca);
150}

152Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTempWithoutCast(QualType Ty, CharUnits Align,
153 const Twine &Name) {
154 return CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), Align, Name);
155}
156
157Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTempWithoutCast(QualType Ty,
158 const Twine &Name) {
159 return CreateMemTempWithoutCast(Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty),
160 Name);

163/// EvaluateExprAsBool - Perform the usual unary conversions on the specified
164/// expression and compare the result against zero, returning an Int1Ty value.
165llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EvaluateExprAsBool(const Expr *E) {
166 PGO.setCurrentStmt(E);
167 if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = E->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
168 llvm::Value *MemPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E);
169 return CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(*this, MemPtr, MPT);
170 }
171
172 QualType BoolTy = getContext().BoolTy;
173 SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
174 if (!E->getType()->isAnyComplexType())
175 return EmitScalarConversion(EmitScalarExpr(E), E->getType(), BoolTy, Loc);
176
177 return EmitComplexToScalarConversion(EmitComplexExpr(E), E->getType(), BoolTy,
178 Loc);
179}

181/// EmitIgnoredExpr - Emit code to compute the specified expression,
182/// ignoring the result.
183void CodeGenFunction::EmitIgnoredExpr(const Expr *E) {
184 if (E->isRValue())
185 return (void) EmitAnyExpr(E, AggValueSlot::ignored(), true);
186
187 // Just emit it as an l-value and drop the result.
188 EmitLValue(E);
189}
190
191/// EmitAnyExpr - Emit code to compute the specified expression which
192/// can have any type. The result is returned as an RValue struct.
193/// If this is an aggregate expression, AggSlot indicates where the
194/// result should be returned.
195RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExpr(const Expr *E,
196 AggValueSlot aggSlot,
197 bool ignoreResult) {
198 switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
199 case TEK_Scalar:
200 return RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(E, ignoreResult));
201 case TEK_Complex:
202 return RValue::getComplex(EmitComplexExpr(E, ignoreResult, ignoreResult));
203 case TEK_Aggregate:
204 if (!ignoreResult && aggSlot.isIgnored())
205 aggSlot = CreateAggTemp(E->getType(), "agg-temp");
206 EmitAggExpr(E, aggSlot);
207 return aggSlot.asRValue();
208 }
209 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
210}
211
212/// EmitAnyExprToTemp - Similar to EmitAnyExpr(), however, the result will
213/// always be accessible even if no aggregate location is provided.
214RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExprToTemp(const Expr *E) {
215 AggValueSlot AggSlot = AggValueSlot::ignored();
216
217 if (hasAggregateEvaluationKind(E->getType()))
218 AggSlot = CreateAggTemp(E->getType(), "agg.tmp");
219 return EmitAnyExpr(E, AggSlot);
220}
221
222/// EmitAnyExprToMem - Evaluate an expression into a given memory
223/// location.
224void CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExprToMem(const Expr *E,
225 Address Location,
226 Qualifiers Quals,
227 bool IsInit) {
228 // FIXME: This function should take an LValue as an argument.
229 switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
230 case TEK_Complex:
231 EmitComplexExprIntoLValue(E, MakeAddrLValue(Location, E->getType()),
232 /*isInit*/ false);
233 return;
234
235 case TEK_Aggregate: {
236 EmitAggExpr(E, AggValueSlot::forAddr(Location, Quals,
237 AggValueSlot::IsDestructed_t(IsInit),
238 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
239 AggValueSlot::IsAliased_t(!IsInit),
240 AggValueSlot::MayOverlap));
241 return;
242 }
243
244 case TEK_Scalar: {
245 RValue RV = RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(E, /*Ignore*/ false));
246 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Location, E->getType());
247 EmitStoreThroughLValue(RV, LV);
248 return;
249 }
250 }
251 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
252}

254static void
255pushTemporaryCleanup(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M,
256 const Expr *E, Address ReferenceTemporary) {
257 // Objective-C++ ARC:
258 // If we are binding a reference to a temporary that has ownership, we
259 // need to perform retain/release operations on the temporary.
260 //
261 // FIXME: This should be looking at E, not M.
262 if (auto Lifetime = M->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
263 switch (Lifetime) {
264 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
265 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
266 // Carry on to normal cleanup handling.
267 break;
268
269 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
270 // Nothing to do; cleaned up by an autorelease pool.
271 return;
272
273 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
274 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
275 switch (StorageDuration Duration = M->getStorageDuration()) {
276 case SD_Static:
277 // Note: we intentionally do not register a cleanup to release
278 // the object on program termination.
279 return;
280
281 case SD_Thread:
282 // FIXME: We should probably register a cleanup in this case.
283 return;
284
285 case SD_Automatic:
286 case SD_FullExpression:
287 CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *Destroy;
288 CleanupKind CleanupKind;
289 if (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
290 const ValueDecl *VD = M->getExtendingDecl();
291 bool Precise =
292 VD && isa<VarDecl>(VD) && VD->hasAttr<ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr>();
293 CleanupKind = CGF.getARCCleanupKind();
294 Destroy = Precise ? &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongPrecise
295 : &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongImprecise;
296 } else {
297 // __weak objects always get EH cleanups; otherwise, exceptions
298 // could cause really nasty crashes instead of mere leaks.
299 CleanupKind = NormalAndEHCleanup;
300 Destroy = &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCWeak;
301 }
302 if (Duration == SD_FullExpression)
303 CGF.pushDestroy(CleanupKind, ReferenceTemporary,
304 M->getType(), *Destroy,
305 CleanupKind & EHCleanup);
306 else
307 CGF.pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(CleanupKind, ReferenceTemporary,
308 M->getType(),
309 *Destroy, CleanupKind & EHCleanup);
310 return;
311
312 case SD_Dynamic:
313 llvm_unreachable("temporary cannot have dynamic storage duration");
314 }
315 llvm_unreachable("unknown storage duration");
316 }
317 }
318
319 CXXDestructorDecl *ReferenceTemporaryDtor = nullptr;
320 if (const RecordType *RT =
321 E->getType()->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
322 // Get the destructor for the reference temporary.
323 auto *ClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
324 if (!ClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
325 ReferenceTemporaryDtor = ClassDecl->getDestructor();
326 }
327
328 if (!ReferenceTemporaryDtor)
329 return;
330
331 // Call the destructor for the temporary.
332 switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
333 case SD_Static:
334 case SD_Thread: {
335 llvm::FunctionCallee CleanupFn;
336 llvm::Constant *CleanupArg;
337 if (E->getType()->isArrayType()) {
338 CleanupFn = CodeGenFunction(CGF.CGM).generateDestroyHelper(
339 ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
340 CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject, CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions,
341 dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()));
342 CleanupArg = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int8PtrTy);
343 } else {
344 CleanupFn = CGF.CGM.getAddrAndTypeOfCXXStructor(
345 GlobalDecl(ReferenceTemporaryDtor, Dtor_Complete));
346 CleanupArg = cast<llvm::Constant>(ReferenceTemporary.getPointer());
347 }
348 CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().registerGlobalDtor(
349 CGF, *cast<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()), CleanupFn, CleanupArg);
350 break;
351 }
352
353 case SD_FullExpression:
354 CGF.pushDestroy(NormalAndEHCleanup, ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
355 CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject,
356 CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions);
357 break;
358
359 case SD_Automatic:
360 CGF.pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(NormalAndEHCleanup,
361 ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
362 CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject,
363 CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions);
364 break;
365
366 case SD_Dynamic:
367 llvm_unreachable("temporary cannot have dynamic storage duration");
368 }
369}
370
371static Address createReferenceTemporary(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
372 const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M,
373 const Expr *Inner,
374 Address *Alloca = nullptr) {
375 auto &TCG = CGF.getTargetHooks();
376 switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
377 case SD_FullExpression:
378 case SD_Automatic: {
379 // If we have a constant temporary array or record try to promote it into a
380 // constant global under the same rules a normal constant would've been
381 // promoted. This is easier on the optimizer and generally emits fewer
382 // instructions.
383 QualType Ty = Inner->getType();
384 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().MergeAllConstants &&
385 (Ty->isArrayType() || Ty->isRecordType()) &&
386 CGF.CGM.isTypeConstant(Ty, true))
387 if (auto Init = ConstantEmitter(CGF).tryEmitAbstract(Inner, Ty)) {
388 if (auto AddrSpace = CGF.getTarget().getConstantAddressSpace()) {
389 auto AS = AddrSpace.getValue();
390 auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
391 CGF.CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), /*isConstant=*/true,
392 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Init, ".ref.tmp", nullptr,
393 llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
394 CGF.CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(AS));
395 CharUnits alignment = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
396 GV->setAlignment(alignment.getQuantity());
397 llvm::Constant *C = GV;
398 if (AS != LangAS::Default)
399 C = TCG.performAddrSpaceCast(
400 CGF.CGM, GV, AS, LangAS::Default,
401 GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(
402 CGF.CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
403 // FIXME: Should we put the new global into a COMDAT?
404 return Address(C, alignment);
405 }
406 }
407 return CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty, "ref.tmp", Alloca);
408 }
409 case SD_Thread:
410 case SD_Static:
411 return CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalTemporary(M, Inner);
412
413 case SD_Dynamic:
414 llvm_unreachable("temporary can't have dynamic storage duration");
415 }
416 llvm_unreachable("unknown storage duration");
417}
418
419LValue CodeGenFunction::
420EmitMaterializeTemporaryExpr(const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M) {
421 const Expr *E = M->GetTemporaryExpr();
422
423 assert((!M->getExtendingDecl() || !isa<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()) ||
424 !cast<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl())->isARCPseudoStrong()) &&
425 "Reference should never be pseudo-strong!");
426
427 // FIXME: ideally this would use EmitAnyExprToMem, however, we cannot do so
428 // as that will cause the lifetime adjustment to be lost for ARC
429 auto ownership = M->getType().getObjCLifetime();
430 if (ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_None &&
431 ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
432 Address Object = createReferenceTemporary(*this, M, E);
433 if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Object.getPointer())) {
434 Object = Address(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Var,
435 ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType())
436 ->getPointerTo(Object.getAddressSpace())),
437 Object.getAlignment());
438
439 // createReferenceTemporary will promote the temporary to a global with a
440 // constant initializer if it can. It can only do this to a value of
441 // ARC-manageable type if the value is global and therefore "immune" to
442 // ref-counting operations. Therefore we have no need to emit either a
443 // dynamic initialization or a cleanup and we can just return the address
444 // of the temporary.
445 if (Var->hasInitializer())
446 return MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
447
448 Var->setInitializer(CGM.EmitNullConstant(E->getType()));
449 }
450 LValue RefTempDst = MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(),
451 AlignmentSource::Decl);
452
453 switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
454 default: llvm_unreachable("expected scalar or aggregate expression");
455 case TEK_Scalar:
456 EmitScalarInit(E, M->getExtendingDecl(), RefTempDst, false);
457 break;
458 case TEK_Aggregate: {
459 EmitAggExpr(E, AggValueSlot::forAddr(Object,
460 E->getType().getQualifiers(),
461 AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
462 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
463 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
464 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap));
465 break;
466 }
467 }
468
469 pushTemporaryCleanup(*this, M, E, Object);
470 return RefTempDst;
471 }
472
473 SmallVector<const Expr *, 2> CommaLHSs;
474 SmallVector<SubobjectAdjustment, 2> Adjustments;
475 E = E->skipRValueSubobjectAdjustments(CommaLHSs, Adjustments);
476
477 for (const auto &Ignored : CommaLHSs)
478 EmitIgnoredExpr(Ignored);
479
480 if (const auto *opaque = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E)) {
481 if (opaque->getType()->isRecordType()) {
482 assert(Adjustments.empty());
483 return EmitOpaqueValueLValue(opaque);
484 }
485 }
486
487 // Create and initialize the reference temporary.
488 Address Alloca = Address::invalid();
489 Address Object = createReferenceTemporary(*this, M, E, &Alloca);
490 if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
491 Object.getPointer()->stripPointerCasts())) {
492 unsigned AS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
493 Object = Address(llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
494 cast<llvm::Constant>(Object.getPointer()),
495 ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType())->getPointerTo(AS)),
496 Object.getAlignment());
497 // If the temporary is a global and has a constant initializer or is a
498 // constant temporary that we promoted to a global, we may have already
499 // initialized it.
500 if (!Var->hasInitializer()) {
501 Var->setInitializer(CGM.EmitNullConstant(E->getType()));
502 EmitAnyExprToMem(E, Object, Qualifiers(), /*IsInit*/true);
503 }
504 } else {
505 switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
506 case SD_Automatic:
507 if (auto *Size = EmitLifetimeStart(
508 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Alloca.getElementType()),
509 Alloca.getPointer())) {
510 pushCleanupAfterFullExpr<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker,
511 Alloca, Size);
512 }
513 break;
514
515 case SD_FullExpression: {
516 if (!ShouldEmitLifetimeMarkers)
517 break;
518
519 // Avoid creating a conditional cleanup just to hold an llvm.lifetime.end
520 // marker. Instead, start the lifetime of a conditional temporary earlier
521 // so that it's unconditional. Don't do this in ASan's use-after-scope
522 // mode so that it gets the more precise lifetime marks. If the type has
523 // a non-trivial destructor, we'll have a cleanup block for it anyway,
524 // so this typically doesn't help; skip it in that case.
525 ConditionalEvaluation *OldConditional = nullptr;
526 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint OldIP;
527 if (isInConditionalBranch() && !E->getType().isDestructedType() &&
528 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeAddressUseAfterScope) {
529 OldConditional = OutermostConditional;
530 OutermostConditional = nullptr;
531
532 OldIP = Builder.saveIP();
533 llvm::BasicBlock *Block = OldConditional->getStartingBlock();
534 Builder.restoreIP(CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint(
535 Block, llvm::BasicBlock::iterator(Block->back())));
536 }
537
538 if (auto *Size = EmitLifetimeStart(
539 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Alloca.getElementType()),
540 Alloca.getPointer())) {
541 pushFullExprCleanup<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker, Alloca,
542 Size);
543 }
544
545 if (OldConditional) {
546 OutermostConditional = OldConditional;
547 Builder.restoreIP(OldIP);
548 }
549 break;
550 }
551
552 default:
553 break;
554 }
555 EmitAnyExprToMem(E, Object, Qualifiers(), /*IsInit*/true);
556 }
557 pushTemporaryCleanup(*this, M, E, Object);
558
559 // Perform derived-to-base casts and/or field accesses, to get from the
560 // temporary object we created (and, potentially, for which we extended
561 // the lifetime) to the subobject we're binding the reference to.
562 for (unsigned I = Adjustments.size(); I != 0; --I) {
563 SubobjectAdjustment &Adjustment = Adjustments[I-1];
564 switch (Adjustment.Kind) {
565 case SubobjectAdjustment::DerivedToBaseAdjustment:
566 Object =
567 GetAddressOfBaseClass(Object, Adjustment.DerivedToBase.DerivedClass,
568 Adjustment.DerivedToBase.BasePath->path_begin(),
569 Adjustment.DerivedToBase.BasePath->path_end(),
570 /*NullCheckValue=*/ false, E->getExprLoc());
571 break;
572
573 case SubobjectAdjustment::FieldAdjustment: {
574 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Object, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
575 LV = EmitLValueForField(LV, Adjustment.Field);
576 assert(LV.isSimple() &&
577 "materialized temporary field is not a simple lvalue");
578 Object = LV.getAddress();
579 break;
580 }
581
582 case SubobjectAdjustment::MemberPointerAdjustment: {
583 llvm::Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(Adjustment.Ptr.RHS);
584 Object = EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(E, Object, Ptr,
585 Adjustment.Ptr.MPT);
586 break;
587 }
588 }
589 }
590
591 return MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
592}

630static StringRef boundsKindStr(SubObjectBoundsKind Kind) {
631 switch (Kind) {
632 case SubObjectBoundsKind::Reference:
633 return "reference";
634 case SubObjectBoundsKind::AddrOf:
635 return "address";
636 case SubObjectBoundsKind::ArraySubscript:
637 return "subscript";
638 case SubObjectBoundsKind::ArrayDecay:
639 return "decay";
640 }
641 llvm_unreachable("Invalid kind");
642}
643
644static llvm::cl::opt<unsigned> SubobjectBoundsSWPerm(
645 "cheri-subobject-bounds-clear-swperm", llvm::cl::ZeroOrMore,
646 llvm::cl::Hidden,
647 llvm::cl::desc("Clear the given software permission whenever "
648 "subobject-bounds narrowed the bounds"));
649
650// If we are setting bounds on the full container size, the csetbounds must
651// be done before the cincoffset!
652static llvm::Value *
653tightenCHERIBounds(CodeGenFunction &CGF, SubObjectBoundsKind Kind,
654 llvm::Value *Value, const Expr *LocExpr, QualType Ty,
655 const CodeGenFunction::TightenBoundsResult &TBR) {
656 llvm::Value *ValueToBound = Value;
657 llvm::GetElementPtrInst *GEP = nullptr;
658 StringRef KindStr = boundsKindStr(Kind);
659 if (TBR.IsContainerSize) {
660 if ((GEP = dyn_cast<llvm::GetElementPtrInst>(Value))) {
661 ValueToBound = GEP->getPointerOperand();
662 } else if (auto CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Value)) {
663 // If the source Value is not a GEP instruction but a GEP constantexp
664 // (e.g. bounds on a global &array[index]) we need to convert it to an
665 // instruction so that it can work with the result of a CSetBounds Inst
666 if (CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::GetElementPtr) {
667 GEP = cast<llvm::GetElementPtrInst>(CE->getAsInstruction());
668 CGF.Builder.Insert(GEP);
669 ValueToBound = GEP->getPointerOperand();
670 } else {
671 assert(CE->isCast() && "expected GEP or cast");
672 }
673 } else if (auto I = dyn_cast<llvm::Instruction>(Value)) {
674 // Other case where we use container size is unions -> must be a cast
675 assert(I->isCast() && "expected GEP or cast");
676 } else {
677 llvm_unreachable("Container type is not GEP or cast");
678 }
679 }
680 llvm::Type *BoundedTy = ValueToBound->getType();
681
682 SourceLocation Loc = LocExpr->getExprLoc();
683 SourceRange Range = LocExpr->getSourceRange();
684 StringRef StatsPrefix;
685 if (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::AddrOf) {
686 StatsPrefix = "addrof operator on ";
687 } else if (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::Reference) {
688 StatsPrefix = "C++ reference to ";
689 } else if (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::ArraySubscript) {
690 StatsPrefix = "array subscript for ";
691 } else if (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::ArrayDecay) {
692 StatsPrefix = "array decay for ";
693 } else {
694 llvm_unreachable("Invalid kind");
695 }
696 llvm::Value *SetBoundsSize = nullptr;
697 llvm::Value *SrcLength = nullptr;
698 std::string SizeStr;
699 if (TBR.UseRemainingSize) {
700 SizeStr = TBR.Size ? ("min(" + Twine(*TBR.Size) + ", remaining)").str()
701 : "remaining";
702 auto SrcAsI8 = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(ValueToBound, CGF.Int8CheriCapTy);
703 auto Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
704 llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_get, CGF.PtrDiffTy, SrcAsI8, nullptr,
705 "cur_offset");
706 SrcLength =
707 CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_length_get,
708 CGF.PtrDiffTy, SrcAsI8, nullptr, "cur_len");
709 SetBoundsSize = CGF.Builder.CreateSub(SrcLength, Offset, "remaining_bytes");
710 if (TBR.Size) {
711 auto MaxConst = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.PtrDiffTy, *TBR.Size);
712 auto LessThanMax = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpULT(SetBoundsSize, MaxConst,
713 "less_than_max_size");
714 SetBoundsSize = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(
715 LessThanMax, SetBoundsSize, MaxConst, "bounded_remaining_size");
716 }
717 } else {
718 SizeStr = llvm::utostr(*TBR.Size);
719 SetBoundsSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.PtrDiffTy, *TBR.Size);
720 }
721 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "setting bounds for '" << Ty.getAsString() << "' "
722 << KindStr << " to " << SizeStr << "\n");
723 if (TBR.TargetField) {
724 assert(TBR.IsSubObject);
725 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(Loc,
726 diag::remark_setting_cheri_subobject_bounds_field)
727 << TBR.TargetField << (int)Kind << Ty << SizeStr << TBR.DiagMessage
728 << Range;
729 } else {
730 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(Loc, diag::remark_setting_cheri_subobject_bounds)
731 << TBR.IsSubObject << (int)Kind << Ty << SizeStr << TBR.DiagMessage
732 << Range;
733 }
734 llvm::Value *Result = CGF.setPointerBounds(
735 ValueToBound, SetBoundsSize, Loc, KindStr + ".with.bounds",
736 "Add subobject bounds", TBR.IsSubObject, StatsPrefix + Ty.getAsString());
737
738 if (SubobjectBoundsSWPerm.getNumOccurrences() > 0) {
739 // Clear the given software permission bit to differentiate subobject-bounds
740 // violations from normal CHERI traps
741 if (!SrcLength) {
742 auto SrcAsI8 =
743 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(ValueToBound, CGF.Int8CheriCapTy);
744 SrcLength = CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
745 llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_length_get, CGF.PtrDiffTy, SrcAsI8,
746 nullptr, "cur_len");
747 }
748 auto ResultAsI8 =
749 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Result, CGF.Int8CheriCapTy);
750 auto ResultLength = CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
751 llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_length_get, CGF.PtrDiffTy, ResultAsI8,
752 nullptr, "new_len");
753 auto NewPermsMask = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
754 CGF.PtrDiffTy, ~((UINT64_C(1) << SubobjectBoundsSWPerm)
755 << llvm::cheri::MIPS_UPERMS_SHIFT));
756 auto WithClearedPerms = CGF.Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
757 llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_perms_and, CGF.PtrDiffTy,
758 {ResultAsI8, NewPermsMask}, nullptr, "new_len");
759 auto BoundsSmaller =
760 CGF.Builder.CreateICmpULT(ResultLength, SrcLength, "new_bounds_less");
761 Result = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(BoundsSmaller, WithClearedPerms,
762 ResultAsI8, "result");
763 }
764
765 Result = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Result, BoundedTy);
766 if (GEP) {
767 // Replace the GEP source with the new bounded source
768 GEP->setOperand(0, Result);
769 GEP->moveAfter(cast<llvm::Instruction>(Result));
770 Result = GEP;
771 }
772 return Result;
773}
774
775llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::setCHERIBoundsOnReference(llvm::Value *Value,
776 QualType Ty,
777 const Expr *E) {
778 if (getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() < LangOptions::CBM_References)
779 return Value; // Not enabled
780
781 // CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Trying to set CHERI bounds on reference ";
782 // E->dump(llvm::dbgs()));
783
784 NumReferencesCheckedForBoundsTightening++;
785 constexpr auto Kind = SubObjectBoundsKind::Reference;
786 if (auto TBR = canTightenCheriBounds(Value, Ty, E, Kind)) {
787 if (TBR->IsContainerSize) {
788 NumContainerBoundsSetOnReferences++;
789 } else if (TBR->UseRemainingSize) {
790 NumRemainingSizeBoundsSetOnReferences++;
791 } else {
792 NumTightBoundsSetOnReferences++;
793 }
794 return tightenCHERIBounds(*this, Kind, Value, E, Ty, *TBR);
795 }
796 return Value;
797}
798
799llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::setCHERIBoundsOnAddrOf(llvm::Value *Value,
800 clang::QualType Ty,
801 const Expr *E,
802 const Expr *LocExpr) {
803 assert(getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() >= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe);
804 // CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Trying to set CHERI bounds on addrof operator ";
805 // E->dump(llvm::dbgs()));
806
807 NumAddrOfCheckedForBoundsTightening++;
808 constexpr auto Kind = SubObjectBoundsKind::AddrOf;
809 if (auto TBR = canTightenCheriBounds(Value, Ty, E, Kind)) {
810 if (TBR->IsContainerSize) {
811 NumContainerBoundsSetOnAddrOf++;
812 } else if (TBR->UseRemainingSize) {
813 NumRemainingSizeBoundsSetOnAddrOf++;
814 } else {
815 NumTightBoundsSetOnAddrOf++;
816 }
817 return tightenCHERIBounds(*this, Kind, Value, LocExpr, Ty, *TBR);
818 }
819 return Value;
820}
821
822llvm::Value *
823CodeGenFunction::setCHERIBoundsOnArraySubscript(llvm::Value *Value,
824 const ArraySubscriptExpr *ASE) {
825 assert(getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() >= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe);
826 // CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Trying to set CHERI bounds on [] operator ";
827 // E->dump(llvm::dbgs()));
828 // We want to set the bounds on the subscript base type (NOT the result of
829 // the ASE which will be char for a char[10] subscript!)
830 const Expr *Base = ASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
831 QualType Ty = Base->getType();
832 NumArraySubscriptCheckedForBoundsTightening++;
833 constexpr auto Kind = SubObjectBoundsKind::ArraySubscript;
834 if (auto TBR = canTightenCheriBounds(Value, Ty, Base, Kind)) {
835 assert(!TBR->IsContainerSize && "Container size should not be use for array subscript bounds");
836 if (TBR->UseRemainingSize) {
837 NumRemainingSizeBoundsSetOnArraySubscript++;
838 } else {
839 NumTightBoundsSetOnArraySubscript++;
840 }
841 return tightenCHERIBounds(*this, Kind, Value, Base, Ty, *TBR);
842 }
843 return Value;
844}

846llvm::Value *
847CodeGenFunction::setCHERIBoundsOnArrayDecay(llvm::Value *Value, const Expr *E) {
848 // TODO: only do this for MemberExprs? Stack variables and globals should
849 // already be bounded by the backend.
850
851 assert(getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() >= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe);
852 // CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Trying to set CHERI bounds on array decay ";
853 // E->dump(llvm::dbgs()));
854
855 const Expr *Base = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
856 QualType Ty = Base->getType();
857 assert(Ty->isArrayType());
858 NumArrayDecayCheckedForBoundsTightening++;
859 constexpr auto Kind = SubObjectBoundsKind::ArrayDecay;
860 if (auto TBR = canTightenCheriBounds(Value, Ty, Base, Kind)) {
861 assert(!TBR->IsContainerSize && "Container size should not be use for array decay bounds");
862 if (TBR->UseRemainingSize) {
863 NumRemainingSizeBoundsSetOnArrayDecay++;
864 } else {
865 NumTightBoundsSetOnArrayDecay++;
866 }
867 return tightenCHERIBounds(*this, Kind, Value, Base, Ty, *TBR);
868 }
869 return Value;
870}

872static Optional<CodeGenFunction::TightenBoundsResult>
873cannotSetBounds(const CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, QualType Type,
874 SubObjectBoundsKind Kind, const Twine &Reason) {
875 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
876 diag::remark_no_cheri_subobject_bounds)
877 << (int)Kind << Type << Reason.str() << E->getSourceRange();
878 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< Reason << " -> not setting bounds\n");
879 return None;
880}
881
882static bool hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(const CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E,
883 QualType Ty, SubObjectBoundsKind Kind,
884 const Twine &Msg) {
885 if (Ty.isNull())
886 return false; // unknown type
887 if (Ty->hasAttr(attr::CHERINoSubobjectBounds)) {
888 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "opt-out: ");
889 cannotSetBounds(CGF, E, Ty, Kind, Msg + " has opt-out attribute");
890 return true;
891 }
892 if (RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl()) {
893 if (RD->hasAttr<CHERINoSubobjectBoundsAttr>()) {
894 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "opt-out: ");
895 cannotSetBounds(CGF, E, QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0), Kind,
896 Msg + " declaration has opt-out attribute");
897 return true;
898 }
899 }
900 return false;
901}
902
903static bool hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(const CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E,
904 const Decl *D, SubObjectBoundsKind Kind,
905 const StringRef Msg) {
906 if (D->hasAttr<CHERINoSubobjectBoundsAttr>()) {
907 StringRef Name = "<anonymous>";
908 if (auto ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D))
909 Name = ND->getName();
910 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "opt-out: ");
911 std::string DiagStr = (Msg + " has opt-out attribute").str();
912 if (auto TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(D)) {
913 cannotSetBounds(CGF, E, QualType(TD->getTypeForDecl(), 0), Kind, DiagStr);
914 } else {
915 CGF.CGM.getDiags().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
916 diag::remark_no_cheri_subobject_bounds)
917 << (int)Kind << ("field '" + Name + "'").str() << DiagStr
918 << E->getSourceRange();
919 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< DiagStr << " -> not setting bounds\n");
920 }
921 return true;
922 }
923 if (auto VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D)) {
924 return hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(CGF, E, VD->getType(), Kind,
925 Msg + " type");
926 }
927 return false;
928}

933 QualType BaseTy, QualType Ty,

940
941enum class ArrayBoundsResult {
942 Never = 0,
943 Always,
944 UseFullArray,
945 DependsOnType,
946};
947
948static ArrayBoundsResult canSetBoundsOnArraySubscript(
949 const Expr *E, const ArraySubscriptExpr *ASE, SubObjectBoundsKind Kind,
950 LangOptions::CheriBoundsMode BoundsMode, const CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
951 // TODO: should we opt-out even for references?
952 // TODO: I guess cheri_no_bounds should have a argument that identifies
953 // which kinds of narrowing are fine
954 if (hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(CGF, E, ASE->getType(), Kind, "array type"))
955 return ArrayBoundsResult::Never;
956 const Expr *Base = ASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
957 const QualType BaseTy = Base->getType();
958 if (hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(CGF, E, BaseTy, Kind, "array base type"))
959 return ArrayBoundsResult::Never;
960
961 if (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::Reference &&
962 BoundsMode >= LangOptions::CBM_References) {
963 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "using C++ reference -> ");
964 return ArrayBoundsResult::Always;
965 }
966 const Expr *Index = ASE->getIdx();
967 Expr::EvalResult ConstLengthResult;
968 if (!Index->EvaluateAsInt(ConstLengthResult, CGF.getContext())) {
969 // If the index is not a constant we should be able to set bounds:
970 // This indicates the code is something like
971 // for (int i = 0; i < max; i++) { do_something(array[i]); }
972 // and therefore we should be able to tightly bound.
973 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(
974 << "Index is not a constant (probably in a per-element loop) -> ");
975 // Use the full array bounds in safe mode since there is lots of code that
976 // uses &foo[n] to get an unbounded member access instead of foo + n
977 if (BoundsMode <= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe) {
978 if (BaseTy->isConstantArrayType())
979 remarkUsingContainerSize(CGF, E, BaseTy, ASE->getType(), "&array[n]");
980 return ArrayBoundsResult::UseFullArray;
981 }
982 return ArrayBoundsResult::DependsOnType;
983 }
984 llvm::APSInt ConstLength = ConstLengthResult.Val.getInt();
985 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Index is a constant -> ");
986 if (BoundsMode >= LangOptions::CBM_VeryAggressive) {
987 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "bounds-mode is very-aggressive -> bounds on "
988 "array[CONST] are fine -> ");
989 return ArrayBoundsResult::DependsOnType;
990 }
991 // In aggressive mode we set bounds on everything except &array[0],
992 // &array[last_index] and &array[last_index+1]
993 // since those may be used to pass start and end indices to functions like
994 // `for_each_elem(&array[0], &array[last_index]);
995 if (ConstLength == 0) {
996 if (BaseTy->isConstantArrayType())
997 remarkUsingContainerSize(CGF, E, BaseTy, ASE->getType(), "&array[0]");
998 return ArrayBoundsResult::UseFullArray;
999 }
1000
1001 if (BoundsMode < LangOptions::CBM_Aggressive) {
1002 // don't set bounds on array[constant] for subobject-safe
1003 if (BaseTy->isConstantArrayType())
1004 remarkUsingContainerSize(CGF, E, BaseTy, ASE->getType(),
1005 "&array[<CONSTANT>]");
1006 return ArrayBoundsResult::UseFullArray;
1007 }
1008
1009 assert(BoundsMode == LangOptions::CBM_Aggressive);
1010 // can't use operator<= here since it asserts
1011 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(BaseTy)) {
1012 auto ArraySizeMinusOne = llvm::APSInt(CAT->getSize() - 1, false);
1013 if (llvm::APSInt::compareValues(ConstLength, ArraySizeMinusOne) >= 0) {
1014 remarkUsingContainerSize(CGF, E, BaseTy, ASE->getType(),
1015 "bounds on &array[<last index>]");
1016 return ArrayBoundsResult::UseFullArray;
1017 }
1018 }
1019 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(
1020 << "const array index is not end and bounds==aggressive -> ");
1021 return ArrayBoundsResult::DependsOnType;
1022}
1023
1024static FieldDecl* findPossibleVLA(const RecordDecl *RD) {
1025 const bool CheckingUnion = RD->isUnion();
1026 for (auto i = RD->field_begin(), end = RD->field_end(); i != end; ++i) {
1027 // We only check the last field (except for unions!)
1028 if (!CheckingUnion) {
1029 auto i2 = i;
1030 const bool IsLastField = (++i2 == end);
1031 if (!IsLastField)
1032 continue;
1033 }
1034
1035 auto FieldTy = i->getType();
1036 // If a nested struct has a flexible array member, this union/struct also
1037 // has one.
1038 if (FieldTy->isRecordType()) {
1039 FieldDecl* NestedVLA = findPossibleVLA(FieldTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1040 if (NestedVLA)
1041 return NestedVLA;
1042 }
1043 if (FieldTy->isVariableArrayType() || FieldTy->isIncompleteArrayType())
1044 return *i;
1045
1046 if (FieldTy->isConstantArrayType()) {
1047 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
1048 dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(FieldTy.getTypePtr())) {
1049 // Assume that size 0 and size 1 arrays are meant to be
1050 // variable length arrays since that was the only way of
1051 // doing it before C99
1052 if (CAT->getSize() == 0 || CAT->getSize() == 1) {
1053 return *i;
1054 }
1055 }
1056 }
1057 }
1058 return nullptr;
1059}
1060
1061static bool containsVariableLengthArray(LangOptions::CheriBoundsMode BoundsMode,
1062 QualType Ty) {
1063 auto RD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl();
1064 if (!RD)
1065 return false;
1066
1067 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember()) {
1068 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "found real VLA in " << Ty.getAsString() << " -> ");
1069 return true;
1070 }
1071 if (BoundsMode >= LangOptions::CBM_VeryAggressive) {
1072 // In very-aggressive mode only accept real VLAs and not size 0 / size 1
1073 return false;
1074 }
1075
1076 return findPossibleVLA(RD) != nullptr;
1077}
1078
1079Optional<CodeGenFunction::TightenBoundsResult>
1080CodeGenFunction::canTightenCheriBounds(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty,
1081 const Expr *E,
1082 SubObjectBoundsKind Kind) {
1083 const auto BoundsMode = getLangOpts().getCheriBounds();
1084 assert(BoundsMode > LangOptions::CBM_Conservative);
1085 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< boundsKindStr(Kind) << " '" << Ty.getAsString()
1086 << "' subobj bounds check: ");
1087 if (!CGM.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(Value->getType())) {
1088 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Cannot set bounds on non-capability IR type ";
1089 Value->getType()->print(llvm::dbgs(), true);
1090 llvm::dbgs() << "\n");
1091 return None;
1092 }
1093
1094 if (Ty->isIncompleteType() && !Ty->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
1095 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind, "incomplete type");
1096 }
1097
1098 if (Ty->isDependentType()) {
1099 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind, "dependent type");
1100 }
1101
1102 if (Ty->isFunctionType()) {
1103 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind,
1104 Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::Reference
1105 ? "reference to function"
1106 : "address of function");
1107 }
1108 assert(CGM.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(Value->getType()));
1109
1110 E = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts(); // ignore array-to-pointer decay, etc
1111 // And we also neede to ignore parenexprs since oterwise we get a ParenExpr
1112 // instead of ArraySubscriptExpr/MemberExpr!
1113
1114 // Any expression other than DeclRefExpr (e.g. in the case &x) will be a
1115 // sub-object expression (array index, member expression (&x.a)
1116 const bool IsSubObject = !isa<DeclRefExpr>(E);
1117 // Check if the type of the expression or the container of the member expr
1118 // is annotated with no subobject bounds. In this case we must never set
1119 // bounds (even in everywhere-unsafe mode!)
1120 int64_t TypeSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty).getQuantity();
1121
1122 const auto BoundsOnContainer = [this, IsSubObject, Kind](QualType Container) {
1123 CodeGenFunction::TightenBoundsResult Result;
1124 Result.IsSubObject = IsSubObject;
1125 Result.IsContainerSize = true;
1126 Result.Size = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Container).getQuantity();
1127 assert(Kind != SubObjectBoundsKind::ArraySubscript);
1128 return Result;
1129 };
1130 ValueDecl* TargetField = nullptr;
1131 const auto ExactBounds = [IsSubObject, &TargetField](int64_t Size) {
1132 CodeGenFunction::TightenBoundsResult Result;
1133 Result.IsSubObject = IsSubObject;
1134 Result.IsContainerSize = false;
1135 Result.TargetField = TargetField;
1136 Result.Size = Size;
1137 return Result;
1138 };
1139 const auto UseRemainingSize = [IsSubObject,
1140 &TargetField](Twine Msg, uint64_t MaxSize = 0,
1141 bool IsContainerSize = false) {
1142 CodeGenFunction::TightenBoundsResult Result;
1143 Result.IsSubObject = IsSubObject;
1144 Result.IsContainerSize = IsContainerSize;
1145 Result.UseRemainingSize = true;
1146 if (MaxSize != 0) {
1147 Result.Size = MaxSize;
1148 }
1149 Result.TargetField = TargetField;
1150 if (!Msg.isTriviallyEmpty())
1151 Result.DiagMessage = (" (" + Msg + ")").str();
1152 return Result;
1153 };
1154
1155 // Do not set bounds on &foo if foo is already a reference (we can just
1156 // trust the original reference size. If that size is wrong, it means that
1157 // the calling code was compiled without sub-object bounds and therefore
1158 // tightening the bounds might not be safe!
1159 //
1160 // Note: the same also applies for C++ references (there is no need to add
1161 // another csetbounds if we are just forwarding a reference to another call)
1162 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::AddrOf ||
1163 Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::Reference)) {
1164 // TODO: fix getRealReferenceType() to take ASTContext&
1165 bool IsReference = false;
1166 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<const CallExpr>(E)) {
1167 QualType CallTy = CE->getCallReturnType(getContext());
1168 IsReference = CallTy->isReferenceType();
1169 IsReference = CE->getCallReturnType(getContext())->isReferenceType();
1170 if (IsReference && Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::AddrOf) {
1171 // diagnose address-of std::string/vector operator[]/.at();
1172 // This would set bounds to one element but most uses seem to be &buf[0]
1173 // which clearly wants the full buffer as a pointer.
1174 if (auto FD = CE->getDirectCallee()) {
1175 if (auto CXXMD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
1176 bool KnownBad = CXXMD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Subscript;
1177 auto Name = CXXMD->getDeclName();
1178 if (!KnownBad && Name.isIdentifier()) {
1179 // Handle taking the address of .at(N)/.front()/.back()
1180 // NumParams == 1 for .at() due to implicit this not being counted
1181 auto ExpectedParams =
1182 llvm::StringSwitch<Optional<unsigned>>(CXXMD->getName())
1183 .Case("at", 1)
1184 .Cases("front", "back", 0)
1185 .Default(None);
1186 if (ExpectedParams && CXXMD->getNumParams() == *ExpectedParams)
1187 KnownBad = true;
1188 }
1189 if (KnownBad) {
1190 CGM.getDiags().Report(
1191 E->getExprLoc(),
1192 diag::warn_subobject_bounds_addressof_subscript)
1193 << FD << E->getSourceRange();
1194 CGM.getDiags().Report(
1195 E->getExprLoc(),
1196 diag::note_subobject_bounds_addressof_subscript_fixit)
1197 << CallTy << E->getSourceRange();
1198 }
1199 }
1200 }
1201 }
1202 } else {
1203 // We really only want a reference type for DeclRefExprs here.
1204 // getRealReferenceType() returns a reference type for all non-pointer
1205 // LValue expressions that have an underlying capability by default so
1206 // pass false for LValuesAsReferences.
1207 IsReference =
1208 E->getRealReferenceType(getContext(), /*LValuesAsReferences=*/false)
1209 ->isReferenceType();
1210 }
1211 if (IsReference)
1212 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind,
1213 "source is a C++ reference and therefore should "
1214 "already have sub-object bounds");
1215 }
1216
1217 if (auto DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
1218 // Don't set bounds on weak symbols since they might be NULL
1219 // See https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/llvm-project/issues/317
1220 // TODO: we could add a branch and only do the csetbounds if non-null.
1221 // However, these symbols will be global symbols so there is really no need
1222 // to set bounds (since the linker should initialize them correctly).
1223 // The only advantage of setting bounds here would be to detect mismatch
1224 // between the extern type declaration and the real declaration.
1225 // FIXME: should this be getDecl or getFoundDecl?
1226 auto Found = DRE->getFoundDecl();
1227 auto ValDecl = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(Found);
1228 if ((ValDecl && ValDecl->isWeak()) || Found->hasAttr<WeakAttr>()) {
1229 return cannotSetBounds(
1230 *this, E, Ty, Kind,
1231 "referenced value is a weak symbol and could therefore be NULL");
1232 }
1233 }
1234 if (auto ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
1235 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "got MemberExpr -> ");
1236 // TODO: should we do this recusively? E.g. for &foo.a.b.c.d if type a is
1237 // annotated with no bounds should that apply to d?
1238 auto BaseTy = ME->getBase()->getType();
1239 if (ME->isArrow() && !BaseTy->getPointeeType().isNull()) {
1240 if (hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(*this, E, BaseTy, Kind,
1241 "base pointer type"))
1242 return None;
1243 BaseTy = BaseTy->getPointeeType();
1244 }
1245 if (hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(*this, E, BaseTy, Kind, "base type"))
1246 return None;
1247 if (hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(*this, E, ME->getMemberDecl(), Kind, "field"))
1248 return None;
1249
1250 // Check whether the field or the field type has a "use-remaining-size" attr
1251 // TODO: also allow this attribute on typedefs?
1252 TargetField = ME->getMemberDecl();
1253 auto RSA = TargetField->getAttr<CHERISubobjectBoundsUseRemainingSizeAttr>();
1254 StringRef AttrSource;
1255 if (RSA) {
1256 AttrSource = "member";
1257 } else {
1258 AttrSource = "member type";
1259 if (auto TypeDecl = TargetField->getType()->getAsRecordDecl())
1260 RSA = TypeDecl->getAttr<CHERISubobjectBoundsUseRemainingSizeAttr>();
1261 }
1262 if (RSA) {
1263 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "got RemainingSize(" << RSA->getMaxSize()
1264 << ") attribute on " << AttrSource << " -> ");
1265 return UseRemainingSize(AttrSource + " has use-remaining-size attribute",
1266 RSA->getMaxSize());
1267 }
1268
1269 if (BoundsMode < LangOptions::CBM_VeryAggressive &&
1270 ME->getMemberDecl() == findPossibleVLA(BaseTy->getAsRecordDecl()))
1271 return UseRemainingSize("member is potential variable length array");
1272
1273 // For unions we have to be careful since some code uses pointers to members
1274 // interchangably with a pointer to the main union. Use the containing type
1275 // unless we are doing an array subcript operation or are in aggressive
1276 // mode.
1277 if (Kind != SubObjectBoundsKind::ArraySubscript && Kind != SubObjectBoundsKind::ArrayDecay && BaseTy->isUnionType() &&
1278 BoundsMode < LangOptions::CBM_VeryAggressive) {
1279 // FIXME: we should set bounds to the whole union rather than not setting bounds at all
1280 // FIXME: should we set bounds for references?
1281 if (BoundsMode < LangOptions::CBM_References)
1282 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind, "container is union");
1283
1284 if (containsVariableLengthArray(BoundsMode, BaseTy))
1285 return UseRemainingSize(
1286 "containing union includes a variable length array");
1287
1288 remarkUsingContainerSize(*this, E, BaseTy, Ty, "union member");
1289 return BoundsOnContainer(BaseTy);
1290 }
1291 }
1292
1293 // Array subscripts are the easiest case to handle:
1294 // We always set bounds if it is a constant size array, otherwise never set
1295 // them since we can't known the actual size. This is very similar to
1296 // -fsanitize=array-size and is equivalent to having a trap if index greater
1297 // constant size (but with a CHERI bounds violation instead)
1298 if (Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::ArraySubscript || Kind == SubObjectBoundsKind::ArrayDecay) {
1299 // E->dumpColor();
1300 // E->dumpPretty(getContext());
1301 // For array subscripts we can only set bounds for array types, and not
1302 // pointers since those have an unknown size
1303 // TODO: we could ignore all casts and check the underlying type
1304 // i.e. ((char*)buf)[10] if buf is an array of different type
1305 StringRef KindStr = boundsKindStr(Kind);
1306 if (!Ty->isArrayType()) {
1307 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind,
1308 "array " + KindStr + " on non-array type");
1309 } else if (Ty->isIncompleteArrayType() || !Ty->isConstantSizeType()) {
1310 return UseRemainingSize("array " + KindStr + " on variable size type");
1311 }
1312 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< KindStr << " on constant size array -> ");
1313 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1314 }
1315
1316 if (auto ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E)) {
1317 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Found array subscript -> ");
1318 switch (canSetBoundsOnArraySubscript(E, ASE, Kind, BoundsMode, *this)) {
1319 case ArrayBoundsResult::Never:
1320 return None;
1321 case ArrayBoundsResult::Always:
1322 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1323 case ArrayBoundsResult::UseFullArray: {
1324 const Expr *Base = ASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
1325 if (Base->getType()->isConstantArrayType()) {
1326 return BoundsOnContainer(Base->getType());
1327 } else if (Base->getType()->isArrayType()) {
1328 UseRemainingSize("bounds on full array but size not known", 0, true);
1329 }
1330 // Otherwise we have a non-constant array type -> don't set bounds to
1331 // avoid crashes at runtime
1332 return cannotSetBounds(
1333 *this, E, Ty, Kind,
1334 "should set bounds on full array but size is not known");
1335 }
1336 case ArrayBoundsResult::DependsOnType:
1337 break;
1338 }
1339 }
1340
1341 // General opt-out based on the type of the expression
1342 if (hasBoundsOptOutAnnotation(*this, E, Ty, Kind, "expression"))
1343 return None;
1344
1345 // if (Ty->isArrayType()) {
1346 if (const ArrayType *AT = getContext().getAsArrayType(Ty)) {
1347 if (isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT)) {
1348 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Found constant size array type -> ");
1349 // FIXME: what about size 0/size 1 VLA emulation for pre-C99 code
1350 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1351 } else if (isa<VariableArrayType>(AT)) {
1352 return UseRemainingSize("variable length array type");
1353 } else if (isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT)) {
1354 // int a[]
1355 return UseRemainingSize("incomplete array type");
1356 } else if (isa<DependentSizedArrayType>(AT)) {
1357 llvm_unreachable("Should not get dependent types in subobject codegen");
1358 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind, "dependent size array type");
1359 } else {
1360 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled array type");
1361 }
1362 }
1363
1364 assert(Ty->isConstantSizeType() && "unexpected variable size type.");
1365 // Zero-size structs are okay, but any other zero-size type should already
1366 // have benn handled:
1367 assert((Ty->isRecordType() || TypeSize != 0) && "Unknown size should already have been handled.");
1368
1369 if (BoundsMode >= LangOptions::CBM_EverywhereUnsafe) {
1370 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Bounds mode is everywhere-unsafe -> ");
1371 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1372 }
1373
1374 if (auto AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
1375 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "unwrapping _Atomic type -> ");
1376 Ty = AT->getValueType();
1377 }
1378
1379 // It should be possible to set the size for all scalar types
1380 if (Ty->isScalarType()) {
1381 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Found scalar type -> ");
1382 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1383 }
1384 // Same for vector types (they are fixed size)
1385 if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
1386 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Found vector type -> ");
1387 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1388 }
1389
1390 assert(!Ty->isArrayType());
1391 // It because a bit more tricky for class types since they might be
1392 // downcasted to something with a larger size.
1393 // TODO: can we try to set bounds on all classes without a vtable
1394 // I guess final classes would work
1395 if (Ty->isRecordType()) {
1396 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "Found record type '" << Ty.getAsString() << "' -> ");
1397 if (containsVariableLengthArray(BoundsMode, Ty)) {
1398 return UseRemainingSize("record has flexible array member");
1399 }
1400 // FIXME: some of this is too conservative and we could actually set bounds
1401 if (Ty->isStructureOrClassType() && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1402 // No inheritance or vtables in C -> we should be able to set bounds on
1403 // all structurs that don't have flexible array members and aren't
1404 // annotated as opt-out
1405 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "compiling C and no flexible array -> ");
1406 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1407 } else if (Ty->isCXXStructureOrClassType()) {
1408 CXXRecordDecl *CRD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1409 const bool IsFinalClass = CRD->hasAttr<FinalAttr>();
1410 // TODO: isCLike() -> safe to set bounds? hopefully not inherited from?
1411 if (!IsFinalClass && BoundsMode <= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe) {
1412 return cannotSetBounds(
1413 *this, E, Ty, Kind,
1414 "non-final class and using sub-object-safe mode");
1415 }
1416 // No bounds on classes with vtables
1417 if (CRD->isCLike()) {
1418 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "is C-like struct type and is marked as final -> ");
1419 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1420 }
1421 // Final class: check it doesn't have any virtual bases
1422 // TODO: check there are no flexible array members
1423 if (!CRD->isLiteral()) {
1424 return cannotSetBounds(
1425 *this, E, Ty, Kind,
1426 "final but not a literal type -> size might by dynamic");
1427 } else {
1428 assert(CRD->getNumVBases() == 0);
1429 CHERI_BOUNDS_DBG(<< "is literal type and is marked as final -> ");
1430 return ExactBounds(TypeSize);
1431 }
1432 }
1433 return cannotSetBounds(*this, E, Ty, Kind, "not a struct/class");
1434 }
1435 // Otherwise this type is unhandled, let's print a message:
1436 CGM.getDiags().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
1437 diag::warn_subobject_bounds_unknown_type)
1438 << Ty << E->getSourceRange();
1439#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
1440 llvm::errs() << "Don't know whether to set bounds:\n";
1441 E->dumpColor();
1442 llvm::errs() << "\tExpression type:\n";
1443 Ty.dump();
1444#endif
1445 // TODO: assert here to find all the cases?
1446 // llvm_unreachable("Don't know whether to set bounds on type");
1447 return None;
1448}
1449
1450RValue
1451CodeGenFunction::EmitReferenceBindingToExpr(const Expr *E) {
1452 // Emit the expression as an lvalue.
1453 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E);
1454 assert(LV.isSimple());
1455 llvm::Value *Value = LV.getPointer();
1456 QualType Ty = E->getType();
1457 if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck() && !Ty->isFunctionType()) {
1458 // C++11 [dcl.ref]p5 (as amended by core issue 453):
1459 // If a glvalue to which a reference is directly bound designates neither
1460 // an existing object or function of an appropriate type nor a region of
1461 // storage of suitable size and alignment to contain an object of the
1462 // reference's type, the behavior is undefined.
1463 QualType Ty = E->getType();
1464 EmitTypeCheck(TCK_ReferenceBinding, E->getExprLoc(), Value, Ty);
1465 }
1466 // For CHERI we want to insert bounds on references (at least for simple
1467 // types) unless they are references to functions
1468 // TODO: we should probably check if references are capabilities instead since
1469 // there could be a mode where references are capabilities but pointers aren't
1470 if (CGM.getTarget().areAllPointersCapabilities() && !Ty->isFunctionType())
1471 Value = setCHERIBoundsOnReference(Value, Ty, E);
1472 return RValue::get(Value, LV.getAlignment().getQuantity());
1473}

1476/// getAccessedFieldNo - Given an encoded value and a result number, return the
1477/// input field number being accessed.
1478unsigned CodeGenFunction::getAccessedFieldNo(unsigned Idx,
1479 const llvm::Constant *Elts) {
1480 return cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Elts->getAggregateElement(Idx))
1481 ->getZExtValue();
1482}
1483
1484/// Emit the hash_16_bytes function from include/llvm/ADT/Hashing.h.
1485static llvm::Value *emitHash16Bytes(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *Low,
1486 llvm::Value *High) {
1487 llvm::Value *KMul = Builder.getInt64(0x9ddfea08eb382d69ULL);
1488 llvm::Value *K47 = Builder.getInt64(47);
1489 llvm::Value *A0 = Builder.CreateMul(Builder.CreateXor(Low, High), KMul);
1490 llvm::Value *A1 = Builder.CreateXor(Builder.CreateLShr(A0, K47), A0);
1491 llvm::Value *B0 = Builder.CreateMul(Builder.CreateXor(High, A1), KMul);
1492 llvm::Value *B1 = Builder.CreateXor(Builder.CreateLShr(B0, K47), B0);
1493 return Builder.CreateMul(B1, KMul);
1494}
1495
1496bool CodeGenFunction::isNullPointerAllowed(TypeCheckKind TCK) {
1497 return TCK == TCK_DowncastPointer || TCK == TCK_Upcast ||
1498 TCK == TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase || TCK == TCK_DynamicOperation;
1499}
1500
1501bool CodeGenFunction::isVptrCheckRequired(TypeCheckKind TCK, QualType Ty) {
1502 CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1503 return (RD && RD->hasDefinition() && RD->isDynamicClass()) &&
1504 (TCK == TCK_MemberAccess || TCK == TCK_MemberCall ||
1505 TCK == TCK_DowncastPointer || TCK == TCK_DowncastReference ||
1506 TCK == TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase || TCK == TCK_DynamicOperation);
1507}
1508
1509bool CodeGenFunction::sanitizePerformTypeCheck() const {
1510 return SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Null) |
1511 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment) |
1512 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) |
1513 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr);
1514}
1515
1516void CodeGenFunction::EmitTypeCheck(TypeCheckKind TCK, SourceLocation Loc,
1517 llvm::Value *Ptr, QualType Ty,
1518 CharUnits Alignment,
1519 SanitizerSet SkippedChecks,
1520 llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
1521 // TODO: if this was called everywhere we might be able to add CHERI reduced
1522 // bounds in a central place instead of having toChecks
1523 if (!sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
1524 return;
1525
1526 // Don't check pointers outside the default address space. The null check
1527 // isn't correct, the object-size check isn't supported by LLVM, and we can't
1528 // communicate the addresses to the runtime handler for the vptr check.
1529 if (Ptr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())
1530 return;
1531
1532 // Don't check pointers to volatile data. The behavior here is implementation-
1533 // defined.
1534 if (Ty.isVolatileQualified())
1535 return;
1536
1537 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
1538
1539 SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 3> Checks;
1540 llvm::BasicBlock *Done = nullptr;
1541
1542 // Quickly determine whether we have a pointer to an alloca. It's possible
1543 // to skip null checks, and some alignment checks, for these pointers. This
1544 // can reduce compile-time significantly.
1545 auto PtrToAlloca =
1546 dyn_cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(Ptr->stripPointerCastsNoFollowAliases());
1547
1548 llvm::Value *True = llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(getLLVMContext());
1549 llvm::Value *IsNonNull = nullptr;
1550 bool IsGuaranteedNonNull =
1551 SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Null) || PtrToAlloca;
1552 bool AllowNullPointers = isNullPointerAllowed(TCK);
1553 if ((SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Null) || AllowNullPointers) &&
1554 !IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
1555 // The glvalue must not be an empty glvalue.
1556 IsNonNull = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
1557
1558 // The IR builder can constant-fold the null check if the pointer points to
1559 // a constant.
1560 IsGuaranteedNonNull = IsNonNull == True;
1561
1562 // Skip the null check if the pointer is known to be non-null.
1563 if (!IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
1564 if (AllowNullPointers) {
1565 // When performing pointer casts, it's OK if the value is null.
1566 // Skip the remaining checks in that case.
1567 Done = createBasicBlock("null");
1568 llvm::BasicBlock *Rest = createBasicBlock("not.null");
1569 Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNonNull, Rest, Done);
1570 EmitBlock(Rest);
1571 } else {
1572 Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(IsNonNull, SanitizerKind::Null));
1573 }
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) &&
1578 !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) &&
1579 !Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
1580 uint64_t TySize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty).getQuantity();
1581 llvm::Value *Size = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, TySize);
1582 if (ArraySize)
1583 Size = Builder.CreateMul(Size, ArraySize);
1584
1585 // Degenerate case: new X[0] does not need an objectsize check.
1586 llvm::Constant *ConstantSize = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(Size);
1587 if (!ConstantSize || !ConstantSize->isNullValue()) {
1588 // The glvalue must refer to a large enough storage region.
1589 // FIXME: If Address Sanitizer is enabled, insert dynamic instrumentation
1590 // to check this.
1591 // FIXME: Get object address space
1592 llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { IntPtrTy, Int8PtrTy };
1593 llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::objectsize, Tys);
1594 llvm::Value *Min = Builder.getFalse();
1595 llvm::Value *NullIsUnknown = Builder.getFalse();
1596 llvm::Value *Dynamic = Builder.getFalse();
1597 llvm::Value *CastAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, Int8PtrTy);
1598 llvm::Value *LargeEnough = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(
1599 Builder.CreateCall(F, {CastAddr, Min, NullIsUnknown, Dynamic}), Size);
1600 Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(LargeEnough, SanitizerKind::ObjectSize));
1601 }
1602 }
1603
1604 uint64_t AlignVal = 0;
1605 llvm::Value *PtrAsInt = nullptr;
1606
1607 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment) &&
1608 !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment)) {
1609 AlignVal = Alignment.getQuantity();
1610 if (!Ty->isIncompleteType() && !AlignVal)
1611 AlignVal = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty).getQuantity();
1612
1613 // The glvalue must be suitably aligned.
1614 if (AlignVal > 1 &&
1615 (!PtrToAlloca || PtrToAlloca->getAlignment() < AlignVal)) {
1616 PtrAsInt = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Ptr, IntPtrTy);
1617 llvm::Value *Align = Builder.CreateAnd(
1618 PtrAsInt, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, AlignVal - 1));
1619 llvm::Value *Aligned =
1620 Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Align, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, 0));
1621 if (Aligned != True)
1622 Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(Aligned, SanitizerKind::Alignment));
1623 }
1624 }
1625
1626 if (Checks.size() > 0) {
1627 // Make sure we're not losing information. Alignment needs to be a power of
1628 // 2
1629 assert(!AlignVal || (uint64_t)1 << llvm::Log2_64(AlignVal) == AlignVal);
1630 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
1631 EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty),
1632 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, AlignVal ? llvm::Log2_64(AlignVal) : 1),
1633 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK)};
1634 EmitCheck(Checks, SanitizerHandler::TypeMismatch, StaticData,
1635 PtrAsInt ? PtrAsInt : Ptr);
1636 }
1637
1638 // If possible, check that the vptr indicates that there is a subobject of
1639 // type Ty at offset zero within this object.
1640 //
1641 // C++11 [basic.life]p5,6:
1642 // [For storage which does not refer to an object within its lifetime]
1643 // The program has undefined behavior if:
1644 // -- the [pointer or glvalue] is used to access a non-static data member
1645 // or call a non-static member function
1646 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr) &&
1647 !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr) && isVptrCheckRequired(TCK, Ty)) {
1648 // Ensure that the pointer is non-null before loading it. If there is no
1649 // compile-time guarantee, reuse the run-time null check or emit a new one.
1650 if (!IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
1651 if (!IsNonNull)
1652 IsNonNull = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
1653 if (!Done)
1654 Done = createBasicBlock("vptr.null");
1655 llvm::BasicBlock *VptrNotNull = createBasicBlock("vptr.not.null");
1656 Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNonNull, VptrNotNull, Done);
1657 EmitBlock(VptrNotNull);
1658 }
1659
1660 // Compute a hash of the mangled name of the type.
1661 //
1662 // FIXME: This is not guaranteed to be deterministic! Move to a
1663 // fingerprinting mechanism once LLVM provides one. For the time
1664 // being the implementation happens to be deterministic.
1665 SmallString<64> MangledName;
1666 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
1667 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty.getUnqualifiedType(),
1668 Out);
1669
1670 // Blacklist based on the mangled type.
1671 if (!CGM.getContext().getSanitizerBlacklist().isBlacklistedType(
1672 SanitizerKind::Vptr, Out.str())) {
1673 llvm::hash_code TypeHash = hash_value(Out.str());
1674
1675 // Load the vptr, and compute hash_16_bytes(TypeHash, vptr).
1676 llvm::Value *Low = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, TypeHash);
1677 llvm::Type *VPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(IntPtrTy, 0);
1678 Address VPtrAddr(Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, VPtrTy), getPointerAlign());
1679 llvm::Value *VPtrVal = Builder.CreateLoad(VPtrAddr);
1680 llvm::Value *High = Builder.CreateZExt(VPtrVal, Int64Ty);
1681
1682 llvm::Value *Hash = emitHash16Bytes(Builder, Low, High);
1683 Hash = Builder.CreateTrunc(Hash, IntPtrTy);
1684
1685 // Look the hash up in our cache.
1686 const int CacheSize = 128;
1687 llvm::Type *HashTable = llvm::ArrayType::get(IntPtrTy, CacheSize);
1688 llvm::Value *Cache = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(HashTable,
1689 "__ubsan_vptr_type_cache");
1690 llvm::Value *Slot = Builder.CreateAnd(Hash,
1691 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy,
1692 CacheSize-1));
1693 llvm::Value *Indices[] = { Builder.getInt32(0), Slot };
1694 llvm::Value *CacheVal =
1695 Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Cache, Indices),
1696 getPointerAlign());
1697
1698 // If the hash isn't in the cache, call a runtime handler to perform the
1699 // hard work of checking whether the vptr is for an object of the right
1700 // type. This will either fill in the cache and return, or produce a
1701 // diagnostic.
1702 llvm::Value *EqualHash = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CacheVal, Hash);
1703 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
1704 EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
1705 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty),
1706 CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(Ty.getUnqualifiedType()),
1707 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK)
1708 };
1709 llvm::Value *DynamicData[] = { Ptr, Hash };
1710 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(EqualHash, SanitizerKind::Vptr),
1711 SanitizerHandler::DynamicTypeCacheMiss, StaticData,
1712 DynamicData);
1713 }
1714 }
1715
1716 if (Done) {
1717 Builder.CreateBr(Done);
1718 EmitBlock(Done);
1719 }
1720}
1721
1722/// Determine whether this expression refers to a flexible array member in a
1723/// struct. We disable array bounds checks for such members.
1724static bool isFlexibleArrayMemberExpr(const Expr *E) {
1725 // For compatibility with existing code, we treat arrays of length 0 or
1726 // 1 as flexible array members.
1727 const ArrayType *AT = E->getType()->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
1728 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)) {
1729 if (CAT->getSize().ugt(1))
1730 return false;
1731 } else if (!isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT))
1732 return false;
1733
1734 E = E->IgnoreParens();
1735
1736 // A flexible array member must be the last member in the class.
1737 if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
1738 // FIXME: If the base type of the member expr is not FD->getParent(),
1739 // this should not be treated as a flexible array member access.
1740 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
1741 RecordDecl::field_iterator FI(
1742 DeclContext::decl_iterator(const_cast<FieldDecl *>(FD)));
1743 return ++FI == FD->getParent()->field_end();
1744 }
1745 } else if (const auto *IRE = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E)) {
1746 return IRE->getDecl()->getNextIvar() == nullptr;
1747 }
1748
1749 return false;
1750}
1751
1752llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::LoadPassedObjectSize(const Expr *E,
1753 QualType EltTy) {
1754 ASTContext &C = getContext();
1755 uint64_t EltSize = C.getTypeSizeInChars(EltTy).getQuantity();
1756 if (!EltSize)
1757 return nullptr;
1758
1759 auto *ArrayDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
1760 if (!ArrayDeclRef)
1761 return nullptr;
1762
1763 auto *ParamDecl = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(ArrayDeclRef->getDecl());
1764 if (!ParamDecl)
1765 return nullptr;
1766
1767 auto *POSAttr = ParamDecl->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
1768 if (!POSAttr)
1769 return nullptr;
1770
1771 // Don't load the size if it's a lower bound.
1772 int POSType = POSAttr->getType();
1773 if (POSType != 0 && POSType != 1)
1774 return nullptr;
1775
1776 // Find the implicit size parameter.
1777 auto PassedSizeIt = SizeArguments.find(ParamDecl);
1778 if (PassedSizeIt == SizeArguments.end())
1779 return nullptr;
1780
1781 const ImplicitParamDecl *PassedSizeDecl = PassedSizeIt->second;
1782 assert(LocalDeclMap.count(PassedSizeDecl) && "Passed size not loadable");
1783 Address AddrOfSize = LocalDeclMap.find(PassedSizeDecl)->second;
1784 llvm::Value *SizeInBytes = EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrOfSize, /*Volatile=*/false,
1785 C.getSizeType(), E->getExprLoc());
1786 llvm::Value *SizeOfElement =
1787 llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeInBytes->getType(), EltSize);
1788 return Builder.CreateUDiv(SizeInBytes, SizeOfElement);
1789}
1790
1791/// If Base is known to point to the start of an array, return the length of
1792/// that array. Return 0 if the length cannot be determined.
1793static llvm::Value *getArrayIndexingBound(
1794 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *Base, QualType &IndexedType) {
1795 // For the vector indexing extension, the bound is the number of elements.
1796 if (const VectorType *VT = Base->getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
1797 IndexedType = Base->getType();
1798 return CGF.Builder.getInt32(VT->getNumElements());
1799 }
1800
1801 Base = Base->IgnoreParens();
1802
1803 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Base)) {
1804 if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_ArrayToPointerDecay &&
1805 !isFlexibleArrayMemberExpr(CE->getSubExpr())) {
1806 IndexedType = CE->getSubExpr()->getType();
1807 const ArrayType *AT = IndexedType->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
1808 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
1809 return CGF.Builder.getInt(CAT->getSize());
1810 else if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(AT))
1811 return CGF.getVLASize(VAT).NumElts;
1812 // Ignore pass_object_size here. It's not applicable on decayed pointers.
1813 }
1814 }
1815
1816 QualType EltTy{Base->getType()->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
1817 if (llvm::Value *POS = CGF.LoadPassedObjectSize(Base, EltTy)) {
1818 IndexedType = Base->getType();
1819 return POS;
1820 }
1821
1822 return nullptr;
1823}
1824
1825void CodeGenFunction::EmitBoundsCheck(const Expr *E, const Expr *Base,
1826 llvm::Value *Index, QualType IndexType,
1827 bool Accessed) {
1828 assert(SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds) &&
1829 "should not be called unless adding bounds checks");
1830 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
1831
1832 QualType IndexedType;
1833 llvm::Value *Bound = getArrayIndexingBound(*this, Base, IndexedType);
1834 if (!Bound)
1835 return;
1836
1837 bool IndexSigned = IndexType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1838 llvm::Value *IndexVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, SizeTy, IndexSigned);
1839 llvm::Value *BoundVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(Bound, SizeTy, false);
1840
1841 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
1842 EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getExprLoc()),
1843 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(IndexedType),
1844 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(IndexType)
1845 };
1846 llvm::Value *Check = Accessed ? Builder.CreateICmpULT(IndexVal, BoundVal)
1847 : Builder.CreateICmpULE(IndexVal, BoundVal);
1848 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds),
1849 SanitizerHandler::OutOfBounds, StaticData, Index);
1850}

1852
1853CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy CodeGenFunction::
1854EmitComplexPrePostIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E, LValue LV,
1855 bool isInc, bool isPre) {
1856 ComplexPairTy InVal = EmitLoadOfComplex(LV, E->getExprLoc());
1857
1858 llvm::Value *NextVal;
1859 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(InVal.first->getType())) {
1860 uint64_t AmountVal = isInc ? 1 : -1;
1861 NextVal = llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal.first->getType(), AmountVal, true);
1862
1863 // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
1864 NextVal = Builder.CreateAdd(InVal.first, NextVal, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
1865 } else {
1866 QualType ElemTy = E->getType()->getAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
1867 llvm::APFloat FVal(getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(ElemTy), 1);
1868 if (!isInc)
1869 FVal.changeSign();
1870 NextVal = llvm::ConstantFP::get(getLLVMContext(), FVal);
1871
1872 // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
1873 NextVal = Builder.CreateFAdd(InVal.first, NextVal, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
1874 }
1875
1876 ComplexPairTy IncVal(NextVal, InVal.second);
1877
1878 // Store the updated result through the lvalue.
1879 EmitStoreOfComplex(IncVal, LV, /*init*/ false);
1880
1881 // If this is a postinc, return the value read from memory, otherwise use the
1882 // updated value.
1883 return isPre ? IncVal : InVal;
1884}

1891
1892 if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())

1900/// EmitPointerWithAlignment - Given an expression of pointer type, try to
1901/// derive a more accurate bound on the alignment of the pointer.
1902Address CodeGenFunction::EmitPointerWithAlignment(const Expr *E,
1903 LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
1904 TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
1905 // We allow this with ObjC object pointers because of fragile ABIs.
1906 assert(E->getType()->isPointerType() ||
1907 E->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType());
1908 E = E->IgnoreParens();
1909
1910 // Casts:
1911 if (const CastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E)) {
1912 if (const auto *ECE = dyn_cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE))
1913 CGM.EmitExplicitCastExprType(ECE, this);
1914
1915 switch (CE->getCastKind()) {
1916 // Non-converting casts (but not C's implicit conversion from void*).
1917 case CK_BitCast:
1918 case CK_NoOp:
1919 case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
1920 if (auto PtrTy = CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1921 if (PtrTy->getPointeeType()->isVoidType())
1922 break;
1923
1924 LValueBaseInfo InnerBaseInfo;
1925 TBAAAccessInfo InnerTBAAInfo;
1926 Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE->getSubExpr(),
1927 &InnerBaseInfo,
1928 &InnerTBAAInfo);
1929 if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = InnerBaseInfo;
1930 if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = InnerTBAAInfo;
1931
1932 if (isa<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
1933 LValueBaseInfo TargetTypeBaseInfo;
1934 TBAAAccessInfo TargetTypeTBAAInfo;
1935 CharUnits Align = getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(E->getType(),
1936 &TargetTypeBaseInfo,
1937 &TargetTypeTBAAInfo);
1938 if (TBAAInfo)
1939 *TBAAInfo = CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForCast(*TBAAInfo,
1940 TargetTypeTBAAInfo);
1941 // If the source l-value is opaque, honor the alignment of the
1942 // casted-to type.
1943 if (InnerBaseInfo.getAlignmentSource() != AlignmentSource::Decl) {
1944 if (BaseInfo)
1945 BaseInfo->mergeForCast(TargetTypeBaseInfo);
1946 Addr = Address(Addr.getPointer(), Align);
1947 }
1948 }
1949
1950 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast) &&
1951 CE->getCastKind() == CK_BitCast) {
1952 if (auto PT = E->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
1953 EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(PT->getPointeeType(), Addr.getPointer(),
1954 /*MayBeNull=*/true,
1955 CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
1956 CE->getBeginLoc());
1957 }
1958 return CE->getCastKind() != CK_AddressSpaceConversion
1959 ? Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, ConvertType(E->getType()))
1960 : Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(Addr,
1961 ConvertType(E->getType()));
1962 }
1963 break;
1964
1965 // Array-to-pointer decay.
1966 case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
1967 return EmitArrayToPointerDecay(CE->getSubExpr(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1968
1969 // Derived-to-base conversions.
1970 case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
1971 case CK_DerivedToBase: {
1972 // TODO: Support accesses to members of base classes in TBAA. For now, we
1973 // conservatively pretend that the complete object is of the base class
1974 // type.
1975 if (TBAAInfo)
1976 *TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(E->getType());
1977 Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE->getSubExpr(), BaseInfo);
1978 auto Derived = CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
1979 return GetAddressOfBaseClass(Addr, Derived,
1980 CE->path_begin(), CE->path_end(),
1981 ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(CE),
1982 CE->getExprLoc());
1983 }
1984
1985 // TODO: Is there any reason to treat base-to-derived conversions
1986 // specially?
1987 default:
1988 break;
1989 }
1990 }
1991
1992 // Unary &.
1993 if (const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
1994 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf) {
1995 // FIXME: set bounds here!
1996 LValue LV = EmitLValue(UO->getSubExpr());
1997 if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
1998 if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = LV.getTBAAInfo();
1999 return LV.getAddress();
2000 }
2001 }
2002
2003 // TODO: conditional operators, comma.
2004
2005 // Otherwise, use the alignment of the type.
2006 CharUnits Align = getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(E->getType(), BaseInfo,
2007 TBAAInfo);
2008 return Address(EmitScalarExpr(E), Align);
2009}

2011RValue CodeGenFunction::GetUndefRValue(QualType Ty) {
2012 if (Ty->isVoidType())
2013 return RValue::get(nullptr);
2014
2015 switch (getEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
2016 case TEK_Complex: {
2017 llvm::Type *EltTy =
2018 ConvertType(Ty->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType());
2019 llvm::Value *U = llvm::UndefValue::get(EltTy);
2020 return RValue::getComplex(std::make_pair(U, U));
2021 }
2022
2023 // If this is a use of an undefined aggregate type, the aggregate must have an
2024 // identifiable address. Just because the contents of the value are undefined
2025 // doesn't mean that the address can't be taken and compared.
2026 case TEK_Aggregate: {
2027 Address DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(Ty, "undef.agg.tmp");
2028 return RValue::getAggregate(DestPtr);
2029 }
2030
2031 case TEK_Scalar:
2032 return RValue::get(llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertType(Ty)));
2033 }
2034 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
2035}

2051bool CodeGenFunction::IsWrappedCXXThis(const Expr *Obj) {
2052 const Expr *Base = Obj;
2053 while (!isa<CXXThisExpr>(Base)) {
2054 // The result of a dynamic_cast can be null.
2055 if (isa<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(Base))
2056 return false;
2057
2058 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Base)) {
2059 Base = CE->getSubExpr();
2060 } else if (const auto *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(Base)) {
2061 Base = PE->getSubExpr();
2062 } else if (const auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Base)) {
2063 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
2064 Base = UO->getSubExpr();
2065 else
2066 return false;
2067 } else {
2068 return false;
2069 }
2070 }
2071 return true;
2072}

2074LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedLValue(const Expr *E, TypeCheckKind TCK) {
2075 LValue LV;
2076 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds) && isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E))
2077 LV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E), /*Accessed*/true);
2078 else
2079 LV = EmitLValue(E);
2080 if (!isa<DeclRefExpr>(E) && !LV.isBitField() && LV.isSimple()) {
2081 SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
2082 if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
2083 bool IsBaseCXXThis = IsWrappedCXXThis(ME->getBase());
2084 if (IsBaseCXXThis)
2085 SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Alignment, true);
2086 if (IsBaseCXXThis || isa<DeclRefExpr>(ME->getBase()))
2087 SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
2088 }
2089 EmitTypeCheck(TCK, E->getExprLoc(), LV.getPointer(),
2090 E->getType(), LV.getAlignment(), SkippedChecks);
2091 }
2092 return LV;
2093}
