2095/// EmitLValue - Emit code to compute a designator that specifies the location
2096/// of the expression.
2097///
2098/// This can return one of two things: a simple address or a bitfield reference.
2099/// In either case, the LLVM Value* in the LValue structure is guaranteed to be
2100/// an LLVM pointer type.
2101///
2102/// If this returns a bitfield reference, nothing about the pointee type of the
2103/// LLVM value is known: For example, it may not be a pointer to an integer.
2104///
2105/// If this returns a normal address, and if the lvalue's C type is fixed size,
2106/// this method guarantees that the returned pointer type will point to an LLVM
2107/// type of the same size of the lvalue's type. If the lvalue has a variable
2108/// length type, this is not possible.
2109///
2110LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValue(const Expr *E) {
2111 ApplyDebugLocation DL(*this, E);
2112 switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
2113 default: return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "l-value expression");
2114
2115 case Expr::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
2116 llvm_unreachable("cannot emit a property reference directly");
2117
2118 case Expr::ObjCSelectorExprClass:
2119 return EmitObjCSelectorLValue(cast<ObjCSelectorExpr>(E));
2120 case Expr::ObjCIsaExprClass:
2121 return EmitObjCIsaExpr(cast<ObjCIsaExpr>(E));
2122 case Expr::BinaryOperatorClass:
2123 return EmitBinaryOperatorLValue(cast<BinaryOperator>(E));
2124 case Expr::CompoundAssignOperatorClass: {
2125 QualType Ty = E->getType();
2126 if (const AtomicType *AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>())
2127 Ty = AT->getValueType();
2128 if (!Ty->isAnyComplexType())
2129 return EmitCompoundAssignmentLValue(cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(E));
2130 return EmitComplexCompoundAssignmentLValue(cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(E));
2131 }
2132 case Expr::CallExprClass:
2133 case Expr::CXXMemberCallExprClass:
2134 case Expr::CXXOperatorCallExprClass:
2135 case Expr::UserDefinedLiteralClass:
2136 return EmitCallExprLValue(cast<CallExpr>(E));
2137 case Expr::VAArgExprClass:
2138 return EmitVAArgExprLValue(cast<VAArgExpr>(E));
2139 case Expr::DeclRefExprClass:
2140 return EmitDeclRefLValue(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E));
2141 case Expr::ConstantExprClass:
2142 return EmitLValue(cast<ConstantExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
2143 case Expr::ParenExprClass:
2144 return EmitLValue(cast<ParenExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
2145 case Expr::GenericSelectionExprClass:
2146 return EmitLValue(cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)->getResultExpr());
2147 case Expr::PredefinedExprClass:
2148 return EmitPredefinedLValue(cast<PredefinedExpr>(E));
2149 case Expr::StringLiteralClass:
2150 return EmitStringLiteralLValue(cast<StringLiteral>(E));
2151 case Expr::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
2152 return EmitObjCEncodeExprLValue(cast<ObjCEncodeExpr>(E));
2153 case Expr::PseudoObjectExprClass:
2154 return EmitPseudoObjectLValue(cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(E));
2155 case Expr::InitListExprClass:
2156 return EmitInitListLValue(cast<InitListExpr>(E));
2157 case Expr::CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass:
2158 case Expr::CXXConstructExprClass:
2159 return EmitCXXConstructLValue(cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E));
2160 case Expr::CXXBindTemporaryExprClass:
2161 return EmitCXXBindTemporaryLValue(cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E));
2162 case Expr::CXXUuidofExprClass:
2163 return EmitCXXUuidofLValue(cast<CXXUuidofExpr>(E));
2164 case Expr::LambdaExprClass:
2165 return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
2166
2167 case Expr::ExprWithCleanupsClass: {
2168 const auto *cleanups = cast<ExprWithCleanups>(E);
2169 enterFullExpression(cleanups);
2170 RunCleanupsScope Scope(*this);
2171 LValue LV = EmitLValue(cleanups->getSubExpr());
2172 if (LV.isSimple()) {
2173 // Defend against branches out of gnu statement expressions surrounded by
2174 // cleanups.
2175 llvm::Value *V = LV.getPointer();
2176 Scope.ForceCleanup({&V});
2177 return LValue::MakeAddr(Address(V, LV.getAlignment()), LV.getType(),
2178 getContext(), LV.getBaseInfo(), LV.getTBAAInfo());
2179 }
2180 // FIXME: Is it possible to create an ExprWithCleanups that produces a
2181 // bitfield lvalue or some other non-simple lvalue?
2182 return LV;
2183 }
2184
2185 case Expr::CXXDefaultArgExprClass: {
2186 auto *DAE = cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E);
2187 CXXDefaultArgExprScope Scope(*this, DAE);
2188 return EmitLValue(DAE->getExpr());
2189 }
2190 case Expr::CXXDefaultInitExprClass: {
2191 auto *DIE = cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(E);
2192 CXXDefaultInitExprScope Scope(*this, DIE);
2193 return EmitLValue(DIE->getExpr());
2194 }
2195 case Expr::CXXTypeidExprClass:
2196 return EmitCXXTypeidLValue(cast<CXXTypeidExpr>(E));
2197
2198 case Expr::ObjCMessageExprClass:
2199 return EmitObjCMessageExprLValue(cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E));
2200 case Expr::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
2201 return EmitObjCIvarRefLValue(cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E));
2202 case Expr::StmtExprClass:
2203 return EmitStmtExprLValue(cast<StmtExpr>(E));
2204 case Expr::UnaryOperatorClass:
2205 return EmitUnaryOpLValue(cast<UnaryOperator>(E));
2206 case Expr::ArraySubscriptExprClass:
2207 return EmitArraySubscriptExpr(cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E));
2208 case Expr::OMPArraySectionExprClass:
2209 return EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E));
2210 case Expr::ExtVectorElementExprClass:
2211 return EmitExtVectorElementExpr(cast<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E));
2212 case Expr::MemberExprClass:
2213 return EmitMemberExpr(cast<MemberExpr>(E));
2214 case Expr::CompoundLiteralExprClass:
2215 return EmitCompoundLiteralLValue(cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(E));
2216 case Expr::ConditionalOperatorClass:
2217 return EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(cast<ConditionalOperator>(E));
2218 case Expr::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass:
2219 return EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(cast<BinaryConditionalOperator>(E));
2220 case Expr::ChooseExprClass:
2221 return EmitLValue(cast<ChooseExpr>(E)->getChosenSubExpr());
2222 case Expr::OpaqueValueExprClass:
2223 return EmitOpaqueValueLValue(cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E));
2224 case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
2225 return EmitLValue(cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)->getReplacement());
2226 case Expr::ImplicitCastExprClass:
2227 case Expr::CStyleCastExprClass:
2228 case Expr::CXXFunctionalCastExprClass:
2229 case Expr::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
2230 case Expr::CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
2231 case Expr::CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
2232 case Expr::CXXConstCastExprClass:
2233 case Expr::ObjCBridgedCastExprClass:
2234 return EmitCastLValue(cast<CastExpr>(E));
2235
2236 case Expr::MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
2237 return EmitMaterializeTemporaryExpr(cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E));
2238
2239 case Expr::CoawaitExprClass:
2240 return EmitCoawaitLValue(cast<CoawaitExpr>(E));
2241 case Expr::CoyieldExprClass:
2242 return EmitCoyieldLValue(cast<CoyieldExpr>(E));
2243 }
2244}

2246/// Given an object of the given canonical type, can we safely copy a
2247/// value out of it based on its initializer?
2248static bool isConstantEmittableObjectType(QualType type) {
2249 assert(type.isCanonical());
2250 assert(!type->isReferenceType());
2251
2252 // Must be const-qualified but non-volatile.
2253 Qualifiers qs = type.getLocalQualifiers();
2254 if (!qs.hasConst() || qs.hasVolatile()) return false;
2255
2256 // Otherwise, all object types satisfy this except C++ classes with
2257 // mutable subobjects or non-trivial copy/destroy behavior.
2258 if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(type))
2259 if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
2260 if (RD->hasMutableFields() || !RD->isTrivial())
2261 return false;
2262
2263 return true;
2264}
2265
2266/// Can we constant-emit a load of a reference to a variable of the
2267/// given type? This is different from predicates like
2268/// Decl::mightBeUsableInConstantExpressions because we do want it to apply
2269/// in situations that don't necessarily satisfy the language's rules
2270/// for this (e.g. C++'s ODR-use rules). For example, we want to able
2271/// to do this with const float variables even if those variables
2272/// aren't marked 'constexpr'.
2273enum ConstantEmissionKind {
2274 CEK_None,
2275 CEK_AsReferenceOnly,
2276 CEK_AsValueOrReference,
2277 CEK_AsValueOnly
2278};
2279static ConstantEmissionKind checkVarTypeForConstantEmission(QualType type) {
2280 type = type.getCanonicalType();
2281 if (const auto *ref = dyn_cast<ReferenceType>(type)) {
2282 if (isConstantEmittableObjectType(ref->getPointeeType()))
2283 return CEK_AsValueOrReference;
2284 return CEK_AsReferenceOnly;
2285 }
2286 if (isConstantEmittableObjectType(type))
2287 return CEK_AsValueOnly;
2288 return CEK_None;
2289}
2290
2291/// Try to emit a reference to the given value without producing it as
2292/// an l-value. This is actually more than an optimization: we can't
2293/// produce an l-value for variables that we never actually captured
2294/// in a block or lambda, which means const int variables or constexpr
2295/// literals or similar.
2296CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission
2297CodeGenFunction::tryEmitAsConstant(DeclRefExpr *refExpr) {
2298 ValueDecl *value = refExpr->getDecl();
2299
2300 // The value needs to be an enum constant or a constant variable.
2301 ConstantEmissionKind CEK;
2302 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(value)) {
2303 CEK = CEK_None;
2304 } else if (auto *var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(value)) {
2305 CEK = checkVarTypeForConstantEmission(var->getType());
2306 } else if (isa<EnumConstantDecl>(value)) {
2307 CEK = CEK_AsValueOnly;
2308 } else {
2309 CEK = CEK_None;
2310 }
2311 if (CEK == CEK_None) return ConstantEmission();
2312
2313 Expr::EvalResult result;
2314 bool resultIsReference;
2315 QualType resultType;
2316
2317 // It's best to evaluate all the way as an r-value if that's permitted.
2318 if (CEK != CEK_AsReferenceOnly &&
2319 refExpr->EvaluateAsRValue(result, getContext())) {
2320 resultIsReference = false;
2321 resultType = refExpr->getType();
2322
2323 // Otherwise, try to evaluate as an l-value.
2324 } else if (CEK != CEK_AsValueOnly &&
2325 refExpr->EvaluateAsLValue(result, getContext())) {
2326 resultIsReference = true;
2327 resultType = value->getType();
2328
2329 // Failure.
2330 } else {
2331 return ConstantEmission();
2332 }
2333
2334 // In any case, if the initializer has side-effects, abandon ship.
2335 if (result.HasSideEffects)
2336 return ConstantEmission();
2337
2338 // Emit as a constant.
2339 auto C = ConstantEmitter(*this).emitAbstract(refExpr->getLocation(),
2340 result.Val, resultType);
2341
2342 // Make sure we emit a debug reference to the global variable.
2343 // This should probably fire even for
2344 if (isa<VarDecl>(value)) {
2345 if (!getContext().DeclMustBeEmitted(cast<VarDecl>(value)))
2346 EmitDeclRefExprDbgValue(refExpr, result.Val);
2347 } else {
2348 assert(isa<EnumConstantDecl>(value));
2349 EmitDeclRefExprDbgValue(refExpr, result.Val);
2350 }
2351
2352 // If we emitted a reference constant, we need to dereference that.
2353 if (resultIsReference)
2354 return ConstantEmission::forReference(C);
2355
2356 return ConstantEmission::forValue(C);
2357}
2358
2359static DeclRefExpr *tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2360 const MemberExpr *ME) {
2361 if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
2362 // Try to emit static variable member expressions as DREs.
2363 return DeclRefExpr::Create(
2364 CGF.getContext(), NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), SourceLocation(), VD,
2365 /*RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture=*/false, ME->getExprLoc(),
2366 ME->getType(), ME->getValueKind(), nullptr, nullptr, ME->isNonOdrUse());
2367 }
2368 return nullptr;
2369}
2370
2371CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission
2372CodeGenFunction::tryEmitAsConstant(const MemberExpr *ME) {
2373 if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(*this, ME))
2374 return tryEmitAsConstant(DRE);
2375 return ConstantEmission();
2376}

2378llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::emitScalarConstant(
2379 const CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission &Constant, Expr *E) {
2380 assert(Constant && "not a constant");
2381 if (Constant.isReference())
2382 return EmitLoadOfLValue(Constant.getReferenceLValue(*this, E),
2383 E->getExprLoc())
2384 .getScalarVal();
2385 // XXXAR: For CHERI convert inttoptr instructions to setPointerOffset on
2386 // null See https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/llvm/issues/268
2387 return Constant.getValue(*this);

2397static bool hasBooleanRepresentation(QualType Ty) {
2398 if (Ty->isBooleanType())
2399 return true;
2400
2401 if (const EnumType *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
2402 return ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType()->isBooleanType();
2403
2404 if (const AtomicType *AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>())
2405 return hasBooleanRepresentation(AT->getValueType());
2406
2407 return false;
2408}
2409
2410static bool getRangeForType(CodeGenFunction &CGF, QualType Ty,
2411 llvm::APInt &Min, llvm::APInt &End,
2412 bool StrictEnums, bool IsBool) {
2413 const EnumType *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
2414 bool IsRegularCPlusPlusEnum = CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && StrictEnums &&
2415 ET && !ET->getDecl()->isFixed();
2416 if (!IsBool && !IsRegularCPlusPlusEnum)
2417 return false;
2418
2419 if (IsBool) {
2420 Min = llvm::APInt(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 0);
2421 End = llvm::APInt(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 2);
2422 } else {
2423 const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl();
2424 llvm::Type *LTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ED->getIntegerType());
2425 unsigned Bitwidth = LTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
2426 unsigned NumNegativeBits = ED->getNumNegativeBits();
2427 unsigned NumPositiveBits = ED->getNumPositiveBits();
2428
2429 if (NumNegativeBits) {
2430 unsigned NumBits = std::max(NumNegativeBits, NumPositiveBits + 1);
2431 assert(NumBits <= Bitwidth);
2432 End = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 1) << (NumBits - 1);
2433 Min = -End;
2434 } else {
2435 assert(NumPositiveBits <= Bitwidth);
2436 End = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 1) << NumPositiveBits;
2437 Min = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 0);
2438 }
2439 }
2440 return true;
2441}
2442
2443llvm::MDNode *CodeGenFunction::getRangeForLoadFromType(QualType Ty) {
2444 llvm::APInt Min, End;
2445 if (!getRangeForType(*this, Ty, Min, End, CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictEnums,
2446 hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)))
2447 return nullptr;
2448
2449 llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
2450 return MDHelper.createRange(Min, End);
2451}
2452
2453bool CodeGenFunction::EmitScalarRangeCheck(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty,
2454 SourceLocation Loc) {
2455 bool HasBoolCheck = SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Bool);
2456 bool HasEnumCheck = SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Enum);
2457 if (!HasBoolCheck && !HasEnumCheck)
2458 return false;
2459
2460 bool IsBool = hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty) ||
2461 NSAPI(CGM.getContext()).isObjCBOOLType(Ty);
2462 bool NeedsBoolCheck = HasBoolCheck && IsBool;
2463 bool NeedsEnumCheck = HasEnumCheck && Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
2464 if (!NeedsBoolCheck && !NeedsEnumCheck)
2465 return false;
2466
2467 // Single-bit booleans don't need to be checked. Special-case this to avoid
2468 // a bit width mismatch when handling bitfield values. This is handled by
2469 // EmitFromMemory for the non-bitfield case.
2470 if (IsBool &&
2471 cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Value->getType())->getBitWidth() == 1)
2472 return false;
2473
2474 llvm::APInt Min, End;
2475 if (!getRangeForType(*this, Ty, Min, End, /*StrictEnums=*/true, IsBool))
2476 return true;
2477
2478 auto &Ctx = getLLVMContext();
2479 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
2480 llvm::Value *Check;
2481 --End;
2482 if (!Min) {
2483 Check = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, End));
2484 } else {
2485 llvm::Value *Upper =
2486 Builder.CreateICmpSLE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, End));
2487 llvm::Value *Lower =
2488 Builder.CreateICmpSGE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, Min));
2489 Check = Builder.CreateAnd(Upper, Lower);
2490 }
2491 llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
2492 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty)};
2493 SanitizerMask Kind =
2494 NeedsEnumCheck ? SanitizerKind::Enum : SanitizerKind::Bool;
2495 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, Kind), SanitizerHandler::LoadInvalidValue,
2496 StaticArgs, EmitCheckValue(Value));
2497 return true;
2498}
2499
2500llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfScalar(Address Addr, bool Volatile,
2501 QualType Ty,
2502 SourceLocation Loc,
2503 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo,
2504 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo,
2505 bool isNontemporal) {
2506 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type) {
2507 // For better performance, handle vector loads differently.
2508 if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
2509 const llvm::Type *EltTy = Addr.getElementType();
2510
2511 const auto *VTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(EltTy);
2512
2513 // Handle vectors of size 3 like size 4 for better performance.
2514 if (VTy->getNumElements() == 3) {
2515
2516 // Bitcast to vec4 type.
2517 llvm::VectorType *vec4Ty =
2518 llvm::VectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(), 4);
2519 Address Cast = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, vec4Ty, "castToVec4");
2520 // Now load value.
2521 llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateLoad(Cast, Volatile, "loadVec4");
2522
2523 // Shuffle vector to get vec3.
2524 V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, llvm::UndefValue::get(vec4Ty),
2525 {0, 1, 2}, "extractVec");
2526 return EmitFromMemory(V, Ty);
2527 }
2528 }
2529 }
2530
2531 // Atomic operations have to be done on integral types.
2532 LValue AtomicLValue =
2533 LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, Ty, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
2534 if (Ty->isAtomicType() || LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(AtomicLValue)) {
2535 return EmitAtomicLoad(AtomicLValue, Loc).getScalarVal();
2536 }
2537
2538 llvm::LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr, Volatile);
2539 if (isNontemporal) {
2540 llvm::MDNode *Node = llvm::MDNode::get(
2541 Load->getContext(), llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(1)));
2542 Load->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("nontemporal"), Node);
2543 }
2544
2545 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, TBAAInfo);
2546
2547 if (EmitScalarRangeCheck(Load, Ty, Loc)) {
2548 // In order to prevent the optimizer from throwing away the check, don't
2549 // attach range metadata to the load.
2550 } else if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0)
2551 if (llvm::MDNode *RangeInfo = getRangeForLoadFromType(Ty))
2552 Load->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_range, RangeInfo);
2553
2554 return EmitFromMemory(Load, Ty);
2555}
2556
2557llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitToMemory(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty) {
2558 // Bool has a different representation in memory than in registers.
2559 if (hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)) {
2560 // This should really always be an i1, but sometimes it's already
2561 // an i8, and it's awkward to track those cases down.
2562 if (Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(1))
2563 return Builder.CreateZExt(Value, ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), "frombool");
2564 assert(Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty)) &&
2565 "wrong value rep of bool");
2566 }
2567
2568 return Value;
2569}
2570
2571llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitFromMemory(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty) {
2572 // Bool has a different representation in memory than in registers.
2573 if (hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)) {
2574 assert(Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty)) &&
2575 "wrong value rep of bool");
2576 return Builder.CreateTrunc(Value, Builder.getInt1Ty(), "tobool");
2577 }
2578
2579 return Value;
2580}
2581
2582void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Value *Value, Address Addr,
2583 bool Volatile, QualType Ty,
2584 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo,
2585 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo,
2586 bool isInit, bool isNontemporal) {
2587 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type) {
2588 // Handle vectors differently to get better performance.
2589 if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
2590 llvm::Type *SrcTy = Value->getType();
2591 auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy);
2592 // Handle vec3 special.
2593 if (VecTy && VecTy->getNumElements() == 3) {
2594 // Our source is a vec3, do a shuffle vector to make it a vec4.
2595 llvm::Constant *Mask[] = {Builder.getInt32(0), Builder.getInt32(1),
2596 Builder.getInt32(2),
2597 llvm::UndefValue::get(Builder.getInt32Ty())};
2598 llvm::Value *MaskV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Mask);
2599 Value = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Value, llvm::UndefValue::get(VecTy),
2600 MaskV, "extractVec");
2601 SrcTy = llvm::VectorType::get(VecTy->getElementType(), 4);
2602 }
2603 if (Addr.getElementType() != SrcTy) {
2604 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, SrcTy, "storetmp");
2605 }
2606 }
2607 }
2608
2609 Value = EmitToMemory(Value, Ty);
2610
2611 LValue AtomicLValue =
2612 LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, Ty, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
2613 if (Ty->isAtomicType() ||
2614 (!isInit && LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(AtomicLValue))) {
2615 EmitAtomicStore(RValue::get(Value), AtomicLValue, isInit);
2616 return;
2617 }
2618
2619 llvm::StoreInst *Store = Builder.CreateStore(Value, Addr, Volatile);
2620 if (isNontemporal) {
2621 llvm::MDNode *Node =
2622 llvm::MDNode::get(Store->getContext(),
2623 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(1)));
2624 Store->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("nontemporal"), Node);
2625 }
2626
2627 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Store, TBAAInfo);
2628}
2629
2630void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Value *value, LValue lvalue,
2631 bool isInit) {
2632 EmitStoreOfScalar(value, lvalue.getAddress(), lvalue.isVolatile(),
2633 lvalue.getType(), lvalue.getBaseInfo(),
2634 lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), isInit, lvalue.isNontemporal());
2635}
2636
2637/// EmitLoadOfLValue - Given an expression that represents a value lvalue, this
2638/// method emits the address of the lvalue, then loads the result as an rvalue,
2639/// returning the rvalue.
2640RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfLValue(LValue LV, SourceLocation Loc) {
2641 if (LV.isObjCWeak()) {
2642 // load of a __weak object.
2643 Address AddrWeakObj = LV.getAddress();
2644 return RValue::get(CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCWeakRead(*this,
2645 AddrWeakObj));
2646 }
2647 if (LV.getQuals().getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
2648 // In MRC mode, we do a load+autorelease.
2649 if (!getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
2650 return RValue::get(EmitARCLoadWeak(LV.getAddress()));
2651 }
2652
2653 // In ARC mode, we load retained and then consume the value.
2654 llvm::Value *Object = EmitARCLoadWeakRetained(LV.getAddress());
2655 Object = EmitObjCConsumeObject(LV.getType(), Object);
2656 return RValue::get(Object);
2657 }
2658
2659 if (LV.isSimple()) {
2660 assert(!LV.getType()->isFunctionType());
2661
2662 // Everything needs a load.
2663 return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(LV, Loc));
2664 }
2665
2666 if (LV.isVectorElt()) {
2667 llvm::LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getVectorAddress(),
2668 LV.isVolatileQualified());
2669 return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Load, LV.getVectorIdx(),
2670 "vecext"));
2671 }
2672
2673 // If this is a reference to a subset of the elements of a vector, either
2674 // shuffle the input or extract/insert them as appropriate.
2675 if (LV.isExtVectorElt())
2676 return EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LV);
2677
2678 // Global Register variables always invoke intrinsics
2679 if (LV.isGlobalReg())
2680 return EmitLoadOfGlobalRegLValue(LV);
2681
2682 assert(LV.isBitField() && "Unknown LValue type!");
2683 return EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(LV, Loc);
2684}
2685
2686RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(LValue LV,
2687 SourceLocation Loc) {
2688 const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = LV.getBitFieldInfo();
2689
2690 // Get the output type.
2691 llvm::Type *ResLTy = ConvertType(LV.getType());
2692
2693 Address Ptr = LV.getBitFieldAddress();
2694 llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, LV.isVolatileQualified(), "bf.load");
2695
2696 if (Info.IsSigned) {
2697 assert(static_cast<unsigned>(Info.Offset + Info.Size) <= Info.StorageSize);
2698 unsigned HighBits = Info.StorageSize - Info.Offset - Info.Size;
2699 if (HighBits)
2700 Val = Builder.CreateShl(Val, HighBits, "bf.shl");
2701 if (Info.Offset + HighBits)
2702 Val = Builder.CreateAShr(Val, Info.Offset + HighBits, "bf.ashr");
2703 } else {
2704 if (Info.Offset)
2705 Val = Builder.CreateLShr(Val, Info.Offset, "bf.lshr");
2706 if (static_cast<unsigned>(Info.Offset) + Info.Size < Info.StorageSize)
2707 Val = Builder.CreateAnd(Val, llvm::APInt::getLowBitsSet(Info.StorageSize,
2708 Info.Size),
2709 "bf.clear");
2710 }
2711 Val = Builder.CreateIntCast(Val, ResLTy, Info.IsSigned, "bf.cast");
2712 EmitScalarRangeCheck(Val, LV.getType(), Loc);
2713 return RValue::get(Val);
2714}
2715
2716// If this is a reference to a subset of the elements of a vector, create an
2717// appropriate shufflevector.
2718RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LValue LV) {
2719 llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getExtVectorAddress(),
2720 LV.isVolatileQualified());
2721
2722 const llvm::Constant *Elts = LV.getExtVectorElts();
2723
2724 // If the result of the expression is a non-vector type, we must be extracting
2725 // a single element. Just codegen as an extractelement.
2726 const VectorType *ExprVT = LV.getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
2727 if (!ExprVT) {
2728 unsigned InIdx = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2729 llvm::Value *Elt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, InIdx);
2730 return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, Elt));
2731 }
2732
2733 // Always use shuffle vector to try to retain the original program structure
2734 unsigned NumResultElts = ExprVT->getNumElements();
2735
2736 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 4> Mask;
2737 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumResultElts; ++i)
2738 Mask.push_back(Builder.getInt32(getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)));
2739
2740 llvm::Value *MaskV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Mask);
2741 Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, llvm::UndefValue::get(Vec->getType()),
2742 MaskV);
2743 return RValue::get(Vec);
2744}
2745
2746/// Generates lvalue for partial ext_vector access.
2747Address CodeGenFunction::EmitExtVectorElementLValue(LValue LV) {
2748 Address VectorAddress = LV.getExtVectorAddress();
2749 const VectorType *ExprVT = LV.getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
2750 QualType EQT = ExprVT->getElementType();
2751 llvm::Type *VectorElementTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(EQT);
2752
2753 Address CastToPointerElement =
2754 Builder.CreateElementBitCast(VectorAddress, VectorElementTy,
2755 "conv.ptr.element");
2756
2757 const llvm::Constant *Elts = LV.getExtVectorElts();
2758 unsigned ix = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2759
2760 Address VectorBasePtrPlusIx =
2761 Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(CastToPointerElement, ix,
2762 "vector.elt");
2763
2764 return VectorBasePtrPlusIx;
2765}
2766
2767/// Load of global gamed gegisters are always calls to intrinsics.
2768RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfGlobalRegLValue(LValue LV) {
2769 assert((LV.getType()->isIntegerType() || LV.getType()->isPointerType()) &&
2770 "Bad type for register variable");
2771 llvm::MDNode *RegName = cast<llvm::MDNode>(
2772 cast<llvm::MetadataAsValue>(LV.getGlobalReg())->getMetadata());
2773
2774 // We accept integer and pointer types only
2775 llvm::Type *OrigTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(LV.getType());
2776 llvm::Type *Ty = OrigTy;
2777 if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2778 Ty = CGM.getTypes().getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(OrigTy);
2779 llvm::Type *Types[] = { Ty };
2780
2781 llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::read_register, Types);
2782 llvm::Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(
2783 F, llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Ty->getContext(), RegName));
2784 if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2785 Call = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Call, OrigTy);
2786 return RValue::get(Call);
2787}

2789
2790/// EmitStoreThroughLValue - Store the specified rvalue into the specified
2791/// lvalue, where both are guaranteed to the have the same type, and that type
2792/// is 'Ty'.
2793void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst,
2794 bool isInit) {
2795 if (!Dst.isSimple()) {
2796 if (Dst.isVectorElt()) {
2797 // Read/modify/write the vector, inserting the new element.
2798 llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getVectorAddress(),
2799 Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2800 Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, Src.getScalarVal(),
2801 Dst.getVectorIdx(), "vecins");
2802 Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getVectorAddress(),
2803 Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2804 return;
2805 }
2806
2807 // If this is an update of extended vector elements, insert them as
2808 // appropriate.
2809 if (Dst.isExtVectorElt())
2810 return EmitStoreThroughExtVectorComponentLValue(Src, Dst);
2811
2812 if (Dst.isGlobalReg())
2813 return EmitStoreThroughGlobalRegLValue(Src, Dst);
2814
2815 assert(Dst.isBitField() && "Unknown LValue type");
2816 return EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(Src, Dst);
2817 }
2818
2819 // There's special magic for assigning into an ARC-qualified l-value.
2820 if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime = Dst.getQuals().getObjCLifetime()) {
2821 switch (Lifetime) {
2822 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2823 llvm_unreachable("present but none");
2824
2825 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2826 // nothing special
2827 break;
2828
2829 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2830 if (isInit) {
2831 Src = RValue::get(EmitARCRetain(Dst.getType(), Src.getScalarVal()));
2832 break;
2833 }
2834 EmitARCStoreStrong(Dst, Src.getScalarVal(), /*ignore*/ true);
2835 return;
2836
2837 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2838 if (isInit)
2839 // Initialize and then skip the primitive store.
2840 EmitARCInitWeak(Dst.getAddress(), Src.getScalarVal());
2841 else
2842 EmitARCStoreWeak(Dst.getAddress(), Src.getScalarVal(), /*ignore*/ true);
2843 return;
2844
2845 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2846 Src = RValue::get(EmitObjCExtendObjectLifetime(Dst.getType(),
2847 Src.getScalarVal()));
2848 // fall into the normal path
2849 break;
2850 }
2851 }
2852
2853 if (Dst.isObjCWeak() && !Dst.isNonGC()) {
2854 // load of a __weak object.
2855 Address LvalueDst = Dst.getAddress();
2856 llvm::Value *src = Src.getScalarVal();
2857 CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCWeakAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst);
2858 return;
2859 }
2860
2861 if (Dst.isObjCStrong() && !Dst.isNonGC()) {
2862 // load of a __strong object.
2863 Address LvalueDst = Dst.getAddress();
2864 llvm::Value *src = Src.getScalarVal();
2865 if (Dst.isObjCIvar()) {
2866 assert(Dst.getBaseIvarExp() && "BaseIvarExp is NULL");
2867 llvm::Type *ResultType = IntPtrTy;
2868 Address dst = EmitPointerWithAlignment(Dst.getBaseIvarExp());
2869 llvm::Value *RHS = dst.getPointer();
2870 RHS = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(RHS, ResultType, "sub.ptr.rhs.cast");
2871 llvm::Value *LHS =
2872 Builder.CreatePtrToInt(LvalueDst.getPointer(), ResultType,
2873 "sub.ptr.lhs.cast");
2874 llvm::Value *BytesBetween = Builder.CreateSub(LHS, RHS, "ivar.offset");
2875 CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCIvarAssign(*this, src, dst,
2876 BytesBetween);
2877 } else if (Dst.isGlobalObjCRef()) {
2878 CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCGlobalAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst,
2879 Dst.isThreadLocalRef());
2880 }
2881 else
2882 CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCStrongCastAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst);
2883 return;
2884 }
2885
2886 assert(Src.isScalar() && "Can't emit an agg store with this method");
2887 EmitStoreOfScalar(Src.getScalarVal(), Dst, isInit);
2888}
2889
2890void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst,
2891 llvm::Value **Result) {
2892 const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = Dst.getBitFieldInfo();
2893 llvm::Type *ResLTy = ConvertTypeForMem(Dst.getType());
2894 Address Ptr = Dst.getBitFieldAddress();
2895
2896 // Get the source value, truncated to the width of the bit-field.
2897 llvm::Value *SrcVal = Src.getScalarVal();
2898
2899 // Cast the source to the storage type and shift it into place.
2900 SrcVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(SrcVal, Ptr.getElementType(),
2901 /*IsSigned=*/false);
2902 llvm::Value *MaskedVal = SrcVal;
2903
2904 // See if there are other bits in the bitfield's storage we'll need to load
2905 // and mask together with source before storing.
2906 if (Info.StorageSize != Info.Size) {
2907 assert(Info.StorageSize > Info.Size && "Invalid bitfield size.");
2908 llvm::Value *Val =
2909 Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, Dst.isVolatileQualified(), "bf.load");
2910
2911 // Mask the source value as needed.
2912 if (!hasBooleanRepresentation(Dst.getType()))
2913 SrcVal = Builder.CreateAnd(SrcVal,
2914 llvm::APInt::getLowBitsSet(Info.StorageSize,
2915 Info.Size),
2916 "bf.value");
2917 MaskedVal = SrcVal;
2918 if (Info.Offset)
2919 SrcVal = Builder.CreateShl(SrcVal, Info.Offset, "bf.shl");
2920
2921 // Mask out the original value.
2922 Val = Builder.CreateAnd(Val,
2923 ~llvm::APInt::getBitsSet(Info.StorageSize,
2924 Info.Offset,
2925 Info.Offset + Info.Size),
2926 "bf.clear");
2927
2928 // Or together the unchanged values and the source value.
2929 SrcVal = Builder.CreateOr(Val, SrcVal, "bf.set");
2930 } else {
2931 assert(Info.Offset == 0);
2932 }
2933
2934 // Write the new value back out.
2935 Builder.CreateStore(SrcVal, Ptr, Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2936
2937 // Return the new value of the bit-field, if requested.
2938 if (Result) {
2939 llvm::Value *ResultVal = MaskedVal;
2940
2941 // Sign extend the value if needed.
2942 if (Info.IsSigned) {
2943 assert(Info.Size <= Info.StorageSize);
2944 unsigned HighBits = Info.StorageSize - Info.Size;
2945 if (HighBits) {
2946 ResultVal = Builder.CreateShl(ResultVal, HighBits, "bf.result.shl");
2947 ResultVal = Builder.CreateAShr(ResultVal, HighBits, "bf.result.ashr");
2948 }
2949 }
2950
2951 ResultVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(ResultVal, ResLTy, Info.IsSigned,
2952 "bf.result.cast");
2953 *Result = EmitFromMemory(ResultVal, Dst.getType());
2954 }
2955}
2956
2957void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughExtVectorComponentLValue(RValue Src,
2958 LValue Dst) {
2959 // This access turns into a read/modify/write of the vector. Load the input
2960 // value now.
2961 llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getExtVectorAddress(),
2962 Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2963 const llvm::Constant *Elts = Dst.getExtVectorElts();
2964
2965 llvm::Value *SrcVal = Src.getScalarVal();
2966
2967 if (const VectorType *VTy = Dst.getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
2968 unsigned NumSrcElts = VTy->getNumElements();
2969 unsigned NumDstElts = Vec->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
2970 if (NumDstElts == NumSrcElts) {
2971 // Use shuffle vector is the src and destination are the same number of
2972 // elements and restore the vector mask since it is on the side it will be
2973 // stored.
2974 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 4> Mask(NumDstElts);
2975 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2976 Mask[getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)] = Builder.getInt32(i);
2977
2978 llvm::Value *MaskV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Mask);
2979 Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SrcVal,
2980 llvm::UndefValue::get(Vec->getType()),
2981 MaskV);
2982 } else if (NumDstElts > NumSrcElts) {
2983 // Extended the source vector to the same length and then shuffle it
2984 // into the destination.
2985 // FIXME: since we're shuffling with undef, can we just use the indices
2986 // into that? This could be simpler.
2987 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 4> ExtMask;
2988 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2989 ExtMask.push_back(Builder.getInt32(i));
2990 ExtMask.resize(NumDstElts, llvm::UndefValue::get(Int32Ty));
2991 llvm::Value *ExtMaskV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(ExtMask);
2992 llvm::Value *ExtSrcVal =
2993 Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SrcVal,
2994 llvm::UndefValue::get(SrcVal->getType()),
2995 ExtMaskV);
2996 // build identity
2997 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 4> Mask;
2998 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumDstElts; ++i)
2999 Mask.push_back(Builder.getInt32(i));
3000
3001 // When the vector size is odd and .odd or .hi is used, the last element
3002 // of the Elts constant array will be one past the size of the vector.
3003 // Ignore the last element here, if it is greater than the mask size.
3004 if (getAccessedFieldNo(NumSrcElts - 1, Elts) == Mask.size())
3005 NumSrcElts--;
3006
3007 // modify when what gets shuffled in
3008 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
3009 Mask[getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)] = Builder.getInt32(i+NumDstElts);
3010 llvm::Value *MaskV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(Mask);
3011 Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, ExtSrcVal, MaskV);
3012 } else {
3013 // We should never shorten the vector
3014 llvm_unreachable("unexpected shorten vector length");
3015 }
3016 } else {
3017 // If the Src is a scalar (not a vector) it must be updating one element.
3018 unsigned InIdx = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
3019 llvm::Value *Elt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, InIdx);
3020 Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, SrcVal, Elt);
3021 }
3022
3023 Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getExtVectorAddress(),
3024 Dst.isVolatileQualified());
3025}

3027/// Store of global named registers are always calls to intrinsics.
3028void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughGlobalRegLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst) {
3029 assert((Dst.getType()->isIntegerType() || Dst.getType()->isPointerType()) &&
3030 "Bad type for register variable");
3031 llvm::MDNode *RegName = cast<llvm::MDNode>(
3032 cast<llvm::MetadataAsValue>(Dst.getGlobalReg())->getMetadata());
3033 assert(RegName && "Register LValue is not metadata");
3034
3035 // We accept integer and pointer types only
3036 llvm::Type *OrigTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(Dst.getType());
3037 llvm::Type *Ty = OrigTy;
3038 if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
3039 Ty = CGM.getTypes().getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(OrigTy);
3040 llvm::Type *Types[] = { Ty };
3041
3042 llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::write_register, Types);
3043 llvm::Value *Value = Src.getScalarVal();
3044 if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
3045 Value = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Value, Ty);
3046 Builder.CreateCall(
3047 F, {llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Ty->getContext(), RegName), Value});
3048}

3050// setObjCGCLValueClass - sets class of the lvalue for the purpose of
3051// generating write-barries API. It is currently a global, ivar,
3052// or neither.
3053static void setObjCGCLValueClass(const ASTContext &Ctx, const Expr *E,
3054 LValue &LV,
3055 bool IsMemberAccess=false) {
3056 if (Ctx.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
3057 return;
3058
3059 if (isa<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E)) {
3060 QualType ExpTy = E->getType();
3061 if (IsMemberAccess && ExpTy->isPointerType()) {
3062 // If ivar is a structure pointer, assigning to field of
3063 // this struct follows gcc's behavior and makes it a non-ivar
3064 // writer-barrier conservatively.
3065 ExpTy = ExpTy->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
3066 if (ExpTy->isRecordType()) {
3067 LV.setObjCIvar(false);
3068 return;
3069 }
3070 }
3071 LV.setObjCIvar(true);
3072 auto *Exp = cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
3073 LV.setBaseIvarExp(Exp->getBase());
3074 LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
3075 return;
3076 }
3077
3078 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
3079 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Exp->getDecl())) {
3080 if (VD->hasGlobalStorage()) {
3081 LV.setGlobalObjCRef(true);
3082 LV.setThreadLocalRef(VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None);
3083 }
3084 }
3085 LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
3086 return;
3087 }
3088
3089 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
3090 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
3091 return;
3092 }
3093
3094 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
3095 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
3096 if (LV.isObjCIvar()) {
3097 // If cast is to a structure pointer, follow gcc's behavior and make it
3098 // a non-ivar write-barrier.
3099 QualType ExpTy = E->getType();
3100 if (ExpTy->isPointerType())
3101 ExpTy = ExpTy->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
3102 if (ExpTy->isRecordType())
3103 LV.setObjCIvar(false);
3104 }
3105 return;
3106 }
3107
3108 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)) {
3109 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getResultExpr(), LV);
3110 return;
3111 }
3112
3113 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
3114 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
3115 return;
3116 }
3117
3118 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<CStyleCastExpr>(E)) {
3119 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
3120 return;
3121 }
3122
3123 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ObjCBridgedCastExpr>(E)) {
3124 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
3125 return;
3126 }
3127
3128 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E)) {
3129 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getBase(), LV);
3130 if (LV.isObjCIvar() && !LV.isObjCArray())
3131 // Using array syntax to assigning to what an ivar points to is not
3132 // same as assigning to the ivar itself. {id *Names;} Names[i] = 0;
3133 LV.setObjCIvar(false);
3134 else if (LV.isGlobalObjCRef() && !LV.isObjCArray())
3135 // Using array syntax to assigning to what global points to is not
3136 // same as assigning to the global itself. {id *G;} G[i] = 0;
3137 LV.setGlobalObjCRef(false);
3138 return;
3139 }
3140
3141 if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
3142 setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getBase(), LV, true);
3143 // We don't know if member is an 'ivar', but this flag is looked at
3144 // only in the context of LV.isObjCIvar().
3145 LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
3146 return;
3147 }
3148}

3219static LValue EmitGlobalVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3220 const Expr *E, const VarDecl *VD) {
3221 QualType T = E->getType();
3222
3223 // If it's thread_local, emit a call to its wrapper function instead.
3224 if (VD->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
3225 CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().usesThreadWrapperFunction())
3226 return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitThreadLocalVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T);
3227 // Check if the variable is marked as declare target with link clause in
3228 // device codegen.
3229 if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice) {
3230 Address Addr = emitDeclTargetLinkVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T);
3231 if (Addr.isValid())
3232 return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3233 }
3234
3235 llvm::Value *V = CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
3236 llvm::Type *RealVarTy = CGF.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
3237 V = EmitBitCastOfLValueToProperType(CGF, V, RealVarTy);
3238 CharUnits Alignment = CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
3239 Address Addr(V, Alignment);
3240 // Emit reference to the private copy of the variable if it is an OpenMP
3241 // threadprivate variable.
3242 if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP && !CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd &&
3243 VD->hasAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()) {
3244 return EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T, Addr, RealVarTy,
3245 E->getExprLoc());
3246 }
3247 LValue LV = VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ?
3248 CGF.EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(Addr, VD->getType(),
3249 AlignmentSource::Decl) :
3250 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3251 setObjCGCLValueClass(CGF.getContext(), E, LV);
3252 return LV;
3253}
3254
3255llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3256 llvm::Value *Addr,
3257 llvm::Type *CapTy,
3258 bool IsDirectCall) {
3259 auto* VTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(Addr->getType());
3260 unsigned CapAS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS();
3261 if (!CapTy)
3262 CapTy = VTy->getElementType()->getPointerTo(CapAS);
3263 const bool IsFunction = isa<llvm::FunctionType>(VTy->getPointerElementType());
3264 if (llvm::MCTargetOptions::cheriUsesCapabilityTable()) {
3265 if (IsDirectCall) {
3266 assert(IsFunction);
3267 return Addr; // Don't add a cast for direct calls
3268 }
3269 return CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Addr, CapTy);
3270 }
3271
3272 // Without a cap table we need to get the function address using $pcc
3273 if (!IsFunction && VTy->getPointerAddressSpace() == CapAS)
3274 // For data we don't need any special handling:
3275 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, CapTy);
3276
3277 llvm::Value *V = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Addr, CGF.Int64Ty);
3278 llvm::Value *PCC = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(
3279 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_pcc_get), {});
3280 if (auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Addr->stripPointerCasts())) {
3281 if (F->hasWeakLinkage() || F->hasExternalWeakLinkage()) {
3282 V = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(
3283 CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_from_pointer,
3284 CGF.IntPtrTy),
3285 {PCC, V});
3286 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(V, CapTy);
3287 }
3288 }
3289 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(CGF.setPointerOffset(PCC, V), CapTy);
3290}

3338/// Named Registers are named metadata pointing to the register name
3339/// which will be read from/written to as an argument to the intrinsic
3340/// @llvm.read/write_register.
3341/// So far, only the name is being passed down, but other options such as
3342/// register type, allocation type or even optimization options could be
3343/// passed down via the metadata node.
3344static LValue EmitGlobalNamedRegister(const VarDecl *VD, CodeGenModule &CGM) {
3345 SmallString<64> Name("llvm.named.register.");
3346 AsmLabelAttr *Asm = VD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
3347 assert(Asm->getLabel().size() < 64-Name.size() &&
3348 "Register name too big");
3349 Name.append(Asm->getLabel());
3350 llvm::NamedMDNode *M =
3351 CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata(Name);
3352 if (M->getNumOperands() == 0) {
3353 llvm::MDString *Str = llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
3354 Asm->getLabel());
3355 llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = {Str};
3356 M->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Ops));
3357 }
3358
3359 CharUnits Alignment = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
3360
3361 llvm::Value *Ptr =
3362 llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), M->getOperand(0));
3363 return LValue::MakeGlobalReg(Address(Ptr, Alignment), VD->getType());
3364}
3365
3366LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitDeclRefLValue(const DeclRefExpr *E) {
3367 const NamedDecl *ND = E->getDecl();
3368 QualType T = E->getType();
3369
3370 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
3371 // Global Named registers access via intrinsics only
3372 if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register &&
3373 VD->hasAttr<AsmLabelAttr>() && !VD->isLocalVarDecl())
3374 return EmitGlobalNamedRegister(VD, CGM);
3375
3376 // A DeclRefExpr for a reference initialized by a constant expression can
3377 // appear without being odr-used. Directly emit the constant initializer.
3378 VD->getAnyInitializer(VD);
3379 if (E->isNonOdrUse() == NOUR_Constant && VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
3380 llvm::Constant *Val =
3381 ConstantEmitter(*this).emitAbstract(E->getLocation(),
3382 *VD->evaluateValue(),
3383 VD->getType());
3384
3385 // If this is a CHERI reference to a function then convert the function
3386 // address to a capability
3387 const ReferenceType *RT = cast<ReferenceType>(VD->getType().getTypePtr());
3388 llvm::Value* Result = Val; // use llvm::Value for
3389 // CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability
3390 if (RT->isCHERICapability() && RT->getPointeeType()->isFunctionType()) {
3391 // First strip the addrspacecast if the ConstantEmitter inserted it
3392 if (const auto CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Val)) {
3393 if (CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::AddrSpaceCast) {
3394 Result = CE->getOperand(0);
3395 }
3396 }
3397
3398 unsigned CapAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS();
3399 llvm::Type *ResTy = Result->getType();
3400 if (ResTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != CapAS) {
3401 Result = FunctionAddressToCapability(*this, Result);
3402 }
3403 }
3404
3405 assert(Result && "failed to emit reference constant expression");
3406 // FIXME: Eventually we will want to emit vector element references.
3407
3408 // Should we be using the alignment of the constant pointer we emitted?
3409 CharUnits Alignment = getNaturalTypeAlignment(E->getType(),
3410 /* BaseInfo= */ nullptr,
3411 /* TBAAInfo= */ nullptr,
3412 /* forPointeeType= */ true);
3413 return MakeAddrLValue(Address(Result, Alignment), T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3414 }
3415
3416 // FIXME: Handle other kinds of non-odr-use DeclRefExprs.
3417
3418 // Check for captured variables.
3419 if (E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
3420 VD = VD->getCanonicalDecl();
3421 if (auto *FD = LambdaCaptureFields.lookup(VD))
3422 return EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, FD, CXXABIThisValue);
3423 else if (CapturedStmtInfo) {
3424 auto I = LocalDeclMap.find(VD);
3425 if (I != LocalDeclMap.end()) {
3426 if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
3427 return EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(I->second, VD->getType(),
3428 AlignmentSource::Decl);
3429 return MakeAddrLValue(I->second, T);
3430 }
3431 LValue CapLVal =
3432 EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, CapturedStmtInfo->lookup(VD),
3433 CapturedStmtInfo->getContextValue());
3434 return MakeAddrLValue(
3435 Address(CapLVal.getPointer(), getContext().getDeclAlign(VD)),
3436 CapLVal.getType(), LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Decl),
3437 CapLVal.getTBAAInfo());
3438 }
3439
3440 assert(isa<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl));
3441 Address addr = GetAddrOfBlockDecl(VD);
3442 return MakeAddrLValue(addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3443 }
3444 }
3445
3446 // FIXME: We should be able to assert this for FunctionDecls as well!
3447 // FIXME: We should be able to assert this for all DeclRefExprs, not just
3448 // those with a valid source location.
3449 assert((ND->isUsed(false) || !isa<VarDecl>(ND) ||
3450 !E->getLocation().isValid()) &&
3451 "Should not use decl without marking it used!");
3452
3453 if (ND->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>()) {
3454 const auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(ND);
3455 ConstantAddress Aliasee = CGM.GetWeakRefReference(VD);
3456 return MakeAddrLValue(Aliasee, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3457 }
3458
3459 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
3460 // Check if this is a global variable.
3461 if (VD->hasLinkage() || VD->isStaticDataMember())
3462 return EmitGlobalVarDeclLValue(*this, E, VD);
3463
3464 Address addr = Address::invalid();
3465
3466 // The variable should generally be present in the local decl map.
3467 auto iter = LocalDeclMap.find(VD);
3468 if (iter != LocalDeclMap.end()) {
3469 addr = iter->second;
3470
3471 // Otherwise, it might be static local we haven't emitted yet for
3472 // some reason; most likely, because it's in an outer function.
3473 } else if (VD->isStaticLocal()) {
3474 addr = Address(CGM.getOrCreateStaticVarDecl(
3475 *VD, CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, /*isConstant=*/false)),
3476 getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
3477
3478 // No other cases for now.
3479 } else {
3480 llvm_unreachable("DeclRefExpr for Decl not entered in LocalDeclMap?");
3481 }
3482
3483
3484 // Check for OpenMP threadprivate variables.
3485 if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd &&
3486 VD->hasAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()) {
3487 return EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(
3488 *this, VD, T, addr, getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()),
3489 E->getExprLoc());
3490 }
3491
3492 // Drill into block byref variables.
3493 bool isBlockByref = VD->isEscapingByref();
3494 if (isBlockByref) {
3495 addr = emitBlockByrefAddress(addr, VD);
3496 }
3497
3498 // Drill into reference types.
3499 LValue LV = VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ?
3500 EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(addr, VD->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl) :
3501 MakeAddrLValue(addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3502
3503 bool isLocalStorage = VD->hasLocalStorage();
3504
3505 bool NonGCable = isLocalStorage &&
3506 !VD->getType()->isReferenceType() &&
3507 !isBlockByref;
3508 if (NonGCable) {
3509 LV.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
3510 LV.setNonGC(true);
3511 }
3512
3513 bool isImpreciseLifetime =
3514 (isLocalStorage && !VD->hasAttr<ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr>());
3515 if (isImpreciseLifetime)
3516 LV.setARCPreciseLifetime(ARCImpreciseLifetime);
3517 setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
3518 return LV;
3519 }
3520
3521 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND))
3522 return EmitFunctionDeclLValue(*this, E, FD);
3523
3524 // FIXME: While we're emitting a binding from an enclosing scope, all other
3525 // DeclRefExprs we see should be implicitly treated as if they also refer to
3526 // an enclosing scope.
3527 if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BindingDecl>(ND))
3528 return EmitLValue(BD->getBinding());
3529
3530 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled DeclRefExpr");
3531}
3532
3533LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnaryOpLValue(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3534 // __extension__ doesn't affect lvalue-ness.
3535 if (E->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
3536 return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
3537
3538 QualType ExprTy = getContext().getCanonicalType(E->getSubExpr()->getType());
3539 switch (E->getOpcode()) {
3540 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown unary operator lvalue!");
3541 case UO_Deref: {
3542 QualType T = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->getPointeeType();
3543 assert(!T.isNull() && "CodeGenFunction::EmitUnaryOpLValue: Illegal type");
3544
3545 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
3546 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
3547 Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getSubExpr(), &BaseInfo,
3548 &TBAAInfo);
3549 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
3550 LV.getQuals().setAddressSpace(ExprTy.getAddressSpace());
3551
3552 // We should not generate __weak write barrier on indirect reference
3553 // of a pointer to object; as in void foo (__weak id *param); *param = 0;
3554 // But, we continue to generate __strong write barrier on indirect write
3555 // into a pointer to object.
3556 if (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
3557 getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC &&
3558 LV.isObjCWeak())
3559 LV.setNonGC(!E->isOBJCGCCandidate(getContext()));
3560 return LV;
3561 }
3562 case UO_Real:
3563 case UO_Imag: {
3564 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
3565 assert(LV.isSimple() && "real/imag on non-ordinary l-value");
3566
3567 // __real is valid on scalars. This is a faster way of testing that.
3568 // __imag can only produce an rvalue on scalars.
3569 if (E->getOpcode() == UO_Real &&
3570 !LV.getAddress().getElementType()->isStructTy()) {
3571 assert(E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isArithmeticType());
3572 return LV;
3573 }
3574
3575 QualType T = ExprTy->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
3576
3577 Address Component =
3578 (E->getOpcode() == UO_Real
3579 ? emitAddrOfRealComponent(LV.getAddress(), LV.getType())
3580 : emitAddrOfImagComponent(LV.getAddress(), LV.getType()));
3581 LValue ElemLV = MakeAddrLValue(Component, T, LV.getBaseInfo(),
3582 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, T));
3583 ElemLV.getQuals().addQualifiers(LV.getQuals());
3584 return ElemLV;
3585 }
3586 case UO_PreInc:
3587 case UO_PreDec: {
3588 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
3589 bool isInc = E->getOpcode() == UO_PreInc;
3590
3591 if (E->getType()->isAnyComplexType())
3592 EmitComplexPrePostIncDec(E, LV, isInc, true/*isPre*/);
3593 else
3594 EmitScalarPrePostIncDec(E, LV, isInc, true/*isPre*/);
3595 return LV;
3596 }
3597 }
3598}

3602 E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);

3610LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPredefinedLValue(const PredefinedExpr *E) {
3611 auto SL = E->getFunctionName();
3612 assert(SL != nullptr && "No StringLiteral name in PredefinedExpr");
3613 StringRef FnName = CurFn->getName();
3614 if (FnName.startswith("\01"))
3615 FnName = FnName.substr(1);
3616 StringRef NameItems[] = {
3617 PredefinedExpr::getIdentKindName(E->getIdentKind()), FnName};
3618 std::string GVName = llvm::join(NameItems, NameItems + 2, ".");
3619 if (auto *BD = dyn_cast_or_null<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
3620 std::string Name = SL->getString();
3621 if (!Name.empty()) {
3622 unsigned Discriminator =
3623 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().getBlockId(BD, true);
3624 if (Discriminator)
3625 Name += "_" + Twine(Discriminator + 1).str();
3626 auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(Name, GVName.c_str());
3627 return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3628 } else {
3629 auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(FnName, GVName.c_str());
3630 return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3631 }
3632 }
3633 auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral(SL, GVName);
3634 return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3635}
3636
3637/// Emit a type description suitable for use by a runtime sanitizer library. The
3638/// format of a type descriptor is
3639///
3640/// \code
3641/// { i16 TypeKind, i16 TypeInfo }
3642/// \endcode
3643///
3644/// followed by an array of i8 containing the type name. TypeKind is 0 for an
3645/// integer, 1 for a floating point value, and -1 for anything else.
3646llvm::Constant *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType T) {
3647 // Only emit each type's descriptor once.
3648 if (llvm::Constant *C = CGM.getTypeDescriptorFromMap(T))
3649 return C;
3650
3651 uint16_t TypeKind = -1;
3652 uint16_t TypeInfo = 0;
3653
3654 if (T->isIntegerType()) {
3655 TypeKind = 0;
3656 TypeInfo = (llvm::Log2_32(getContext().getTypeSize(T)) << 1) |
3657 (T->isSignedIntegerType() ? 1 : 0);
3658 } else if (T->isFloatingType()) {
3659 TypeKind = 1;
3660 TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeSize(T);
3661 }
3662
3663 // Format the type name as if for a diagnostic, including quotes and
3664 // optionally an 'aka'.
3665 SmallString<32> Buffer;
3666 CGM.getDiags().ConvertArgToString(DiagnosticsEngine::ak_qualtype,
3667 (intptr_t)T.getAsOpaquePtr(),
3668 StringRef(), StringRef(), None, Buffer,
3669 None);
3670
3671 llvm::Constant *Components[] = {
3672 Builder.getInt16(TypeKind), Builder.getInt16(TypeInfo),
3673 llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), Buffer)
3674 };
3675 llvm::Constant *Descriptor = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Components);
3676
3677 auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3678 CGM.getModule(), Descriptor->getType(),
3679 /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Descriptor);
3680 GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3681 CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(GV);
3682
3683 // Remember the descriptor for this type.
3684 CGM.setTypeDescriptorInMap(T, GV);
3685
3686 return GV;
3687}
3688
3689llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckValue(llvm::Value *V) {
3690 llvm::Type *TargetTy = IntPtrTy;
3691
3692 if (V->getType() == TargetTy)
3693 return V;
3694
3695 // Floating-point types which fit into intptr_t are bitcast to integers
3696 // and then passed directly (after zero-extension, if necessary).
3697 if (V->getType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
3698 unsigned Bits = V->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
3699 if (Bits <= TargetTy->getIntegerBitWidth())
3700 V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(),
3701 Bits));
3702 }
3703
3704 // Integers which fit in intptr_t are zero-extended and passed directly.
3705 if (V->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
3706 V->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth() <= TargetTy->getIntegerBitWidth())
3707 return Builder.CreateZExt(V, TargetTy);
3708
3709 // Pointers are passed directly, everything else is passed by address.
3710 if (!V->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3711 Address Ptr = CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(V->getType());
3712 Builder.CreateStore(V, Ptr);
3713 V = Ptr.getPointer();
3714 }
3715 return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(V, TargetTy);
3716}
3717
3718/// Emit a representation of a SourceLocation for passing to a handler
3719/// in a sanitizer runtime library. The format for this data is:
3720/// \code
3721/// struct SourceLocation {
3722/// const char *Filename;
3723/// int32_t Line, Column;
3724/// };
3725/// \endcode
3726/// For an invalid SourceLocation, the Filename pointer is null.
3727llvm::Constant *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckSourceLocation(SourceLocation Loc) {
3728 llvm::Constant *Filename;
3729 int Line, Column;
3730
3731 PresumedLoc PLoc = getContext().getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(Loc);
3732 if (PLoc.isValid()) {
3733 StringRef FilenameString = PLoc.getFilename();
3734
3735 int PathComponentsToStrip =
3736 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCheckPathComponentsToStrip;
3737 if (PathComponentsToStrip < 0) {
3738 assert(PathComponentsToStrip != INT_MIN);
3739 int PathComponentsToKeep = -PathComponentsToStrip;
3740 auto I = llvm::sys::path::rbegin(FilenameString);
3741 auto E = llvm::sys::path::rend(FilenameString);
3742 while (I != E && --PathComponentsToKeep)
3743 ++I;
3744
3745 FilenameString = FilenameString.substr(I - E);
3746 } else if (PathComponentsToStrip > 0) {
3747 auto I = llvm::sys::path::begin(FilenameString);
3748 auto E = llvm::sys::path::end(FilenameString);
3749 while (I != E && PathComponentsToStrip--)
3750 ++I;
3751
3752 if (I != E)
3753 FilenameString =
3754 FilenameString.substr(I - llvm::sys::path::begin(FilenameString));
3755 else
3756 FilenameString = llvm::sys::path::filename(FilenameString);
3757 }
3758
3759 auto FilenameGV = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(FilenameString, ".src");
3760 CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(
3761 cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(FilenameGV.getPointer()));
3762 Filename = FilenameGV.getPointer();
3763 Line = PLoc.getLine();
3764 Column = PLoc.getColumn();
3765 } else {
3766 Filename = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int8PtrTy);
3767 Line = Column = 0;
3768 }
3769
3770 llvm::Constant *Data[] = {Filename, Builder.getInt32(Line),
3771 Builder.getInt32(Column)};
3772
3773 return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Data);
3774}
3775
3776namespace {
3777/// Specify under what conditions this check can be recovered
3778enum class CheckRecoverableKind {
3779 /// Always terminate program execution if this check fails.
3780 Unrecoverable,
3781 /// Check supports recovering, runtime has both fatal (noreturn) and
3782 /// non-fatal handlers for this check.
3783 Recoverable,
3784 /// Runtime conditionally aborts, always need to support recovery.
3785 AlwaysRecoverable
3786};
3787}
3788
3789static CheckRecoverableKind getRecoverableKind(SanitizerMask Kind) {
3790 assert(Kind.countPopulation() == 1);
3791 if (Kind == SanitizerKind::Vptr)
3792 return CheckRecoverableKind::AlwaysRecoverable;
3793 else if (Kind == SanitizerKind::Return || Kind == SanitizerKind::Unreachable)
3794 return CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable;
3795 else
3796 return CheckRecoverableKind::Recoverable;
3797}
3798
3799namespace {
3800struct SanitizerHandlerInfo {
3801 char const *const Name;
3802 unsigned Version;
3803};
3804}
3805
3806const SanitizerHandlerInfo SanitizerHandlers[] = {
3807#define SANITIZER_CHECK(Enum, Name, Version) {#Name, Version},
3808 LIST_SANITIZER_CHECKS
3809#undef SANITIZER_CHECK
3810};
3811
3812static void emitCheckHandlerCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3813 llvm::FunctionType *FnType,
3814 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> FnArgs,
3815 SanitizerHandler CheckHandler,
3816 CheckRecoverableKind RecoverKind, bool IsFatal,
3817 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB) {
3818 assert(IsFatal || RecoverKind != CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable);
3819 Optional<ApplyDebugLocation> DL;
3820 if (!CGF.Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation()) {
3821 // Ensure that the call has at least an artificial debug location.
3822 DL.emplace(CGF, SourceLocation());
3823 }
3824 bool NeedsAbortSuffix =
3825 IsFatal && RecoverKind != CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable;
3826 bool MinimalRuntime = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMinimalRuntime;
3827 const SanitizerHandlerInfo &CheckInfo = SanitizerHandlers[CheckHandler];
3828 const StringRef CheckName = CheckInfo.Name;
3829 std::string FnName = "__ubsan_handle_" + CheckName.str();
3830 if (CheckInfo.Version && !MinimalRuntime)
3831 FnName += "_v" + llvm::utostr(CheckInfo.Version);
3832 if (MinimalRuntime)
3833 FnName += "_minimal";
3834 if (NeedsAbortSuffix)
3835 FnName += "_abort";
3836 bool MayReturn =
3837 !IsFatal || RecoverKind == CheckRecoverableKind::AlwaysRecoverable;
3838
3839 llvm::AttrBuilder B;
3840 if (!MayReturn) {
3841 B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn)
3842 .addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
3843 }
3844 B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::UWTable);
3845
3846 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
3847 FnType, FnName,
3848 llvm::AttributeList::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(),
3849 llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B),
3850 /*Local=*/true);
3851 llvm::CallInst *HandlerCall = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn, FnArgs);
3852 if (!MayReturn) {
3853 HandlerCall->setDoesNotReturn();
3854 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3855 } else {
3856 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
3857 }
3858}
3859
3860void CodeGenFunction::EmitCheck(
3861 ArrayRef<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>> Checked,
3862 SanitizerHandler CheckHandler, ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> StaticArgs,
3863 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> DynamicArgs) {
3864 assert(IsSanitizerScope);
3865 assert(Checked.size() > 0);
3866 assert(CheckHandler >= 0 &&
3867 size_t(CheckHandler) < llvm::array_lengthof(SanitizerHandlers));
3868 const StringRef CheckName = SanitizerHandlers[CheckHandler].Name;
3869
3870 llvm::Value *FatalCond = nullptr;
3871 llvm::Value *RecoverableCond = nullptr;
3872 llvm::Value *TrapCond = nullptr;
3873 for (int i = 0, n = Checked.size(); i < n; ++i) {
3874 llvm::Value *Check = Checked[i].first;
3875 // -fsanitize-trap= overrides -fsanitize-recover=.
3876 llvm::Value *&Cond =
3877 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(Checked[i].second)
3878 ? TrapCond
3879 : CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeRecover.has(Checked[i].second)
3880 ? RecoverableCond
3881 : FatalCond;
3882 Cond = Cond ? Builder.CreateAnd(Cond, Check) : Check;
3883 }
3884
3885 if (TrapCond)
3886 EmitTrapCheck(TrapCond);
3887 if (!FatalCond && !RecoverableCond)
3888 return;
3889
3890 llvm::Value *JointCond;
3891 if (FatalCond && RecoverableCond)
3892 JointCond = Builder.CreateAnd(FatalCond, RecoverableCond);
3893 else
3894 JointCond = FatalCond ? FatalCond : RecoverableCond;
3895 assert(JointCond);
3896
3897 CheckRecoverableKind RecoverKind = getRecoverableKind(Checked[0].second);
3898 assert(SanOpts.has(Checked[0].second));
3899#ifndef NDEBUG
3900 for (int i = 1, n = Checked.size(); i < n; ++i) {
3901 assert(RecoverKind == getRecoverableKind(Checked[i].second) &&
3902 "All recoverable kinds in a single check must be same!");
3903 assert(SanOpts.has(Checked[i].second));
3904 }
3905#endif
3906
3907 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
3908 llvm::BasicBlock *Handlers = createBasicBlock("handler." + CheckName);
3909 llvm::Instruction *Branch = Builder.CreateCondBr(JointCond, Cont, Handlers);
3910 // Give hint that we very much don't expect to execute the handler
3911 // Value chosen to match UR_NONTAKEN_WEIGHT, see BranchProbabilityInfo.cpp
3912 llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
3913 llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createBranchWeights((1U << 20) - 1, 1);
3914 Branch->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_prof, Node);
3915 EmitBlock(Handlers);
3916
3917 // Handler functions take an i8* pointing to the (handler-specific) static
3918 // information block, followed by a sequence of intptr_t arguments
3919 // representing operand values.
3920 SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 4> Args;
3921 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 4> ArgTypes;
3922 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMinimalRuntime) {
3923 Args.reserve(DynamicArgs.size() + 1);
3924 ArgTypes.reserve(DynamicArgs.size() + 1);
3925
3926 // Emit handler arguments and create handler function type.
3927 if (!StaticArgs.empty()) {
3928 llvm::Constant *Info = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(StaticArgs);
3929 auto *InfoPtr =
3930 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Info->getType(), false,
3931 llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Info);
3932 InfoPtr->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3933 CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(InfoPtr);
3934 Args.push_back(Builder.CreateBitCast(InfoPtr, Int8PtrTy));
3935 ArgTypes.push_back(Int8PtrTy);
3936 }
3937
3938 for (size_t i = 0, n = DynamicArgs.size(); i != n; ++i) {
3939 Args.push_back(EmitCheckValue(DynamicArgs[i]));
3940 ArgTypes.push_back(IntPtrTy);
3941 }
3942 }
3943
3944 llvm::FunctionType *FnType =
3945 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, ArgTypes, false);
3946
3947 if (!FatalCond || !RecoverableCond) {
3948 // Simple case: we need to generate a single handler call, either
3949 // fatal, or non-fatal.
3950 emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind,
3951 (FatalCond != nullptr), Cont);
3952 } else {
3953 // Emit two handler calls: first one for set of unrecoverable checks,
3954 // another one for recoverable.
3955 llvm::BasicBlock *NonFatalHandlerBB =
3956 createBasicBlock("non_fatal." + CheckName);
3957 llvm::BasicBlock *FatalHandlerBB = createBasicBlock("fatal." + CheckName);
3958 Builder.CreateCondBr(FatalCond, NonFatalHandlerBB, FatalHandlerBB);
3959 EmitBlock(FatalHandlerBB);
3960 emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind, true,
3961 NonFatalHandlerBB);
3962 EmitBlock(NonFatalHandlerBB);
3963 emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind, false,
3964 Cont);
3965 }
3966
3967 EmitBlock(Cont);
3968}
3969
3970void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(
3971 SanitizerMask Kind, llvm::Value *Cond, llvm::ConstantInt *TypeId,
3972 llvm::Value *Ptr, ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> StaticArgs) {
3973 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cfi.cont");
3974
3975 llvm::BasicBlock *CheckBB = createBasicBlock("cfi.slowpath");
3976 llvm::BranchInst *BI = Builder.CreateCondBr(Cond, Cont, CheckBB);
3977
3978 llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
3979 llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createBranchWeights((1U << 20) - 1, 1);
3980 BI->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_prof, Node);
3981
3982 EmitBlock(CheckBB);
3983
3984 bool WithDiag = !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(Kind);
3985
3986 llvm::CallInst *CheckCall;
3987 llvm::FunctionCallee SlowPathFn;
3988 if (WithDiag) {
3989 llvm::Constant *Info = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(StaticArgs);
3990 auto *InfoPtr =
3991 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Info->getType(), false,
3992 llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Info);
3993 InfoPtr->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3994 CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(InfoPtr);
3995
3996 SlowPathFn = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction(
3997 "__cfi_slowpath_diag",
3998 llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy},
3999 false));
4000 CheckCall = Builder.CreateCall(
4001 SlowPathFn, {TypeId, Ptr, Builder.CreateBitCast(InfoPtr, Int8PtrTy)});
4002 } else {
4003 SlowPathFn = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction(
4004 "__cfi_slowpath",
4005 llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy}, false));
4006 CheckCall = Builder.CreateCall(SlowPathFn, {TypeId, Ptr});
4007 }
4008
4009 CGM.setDSOLocal(
4010 cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(SlowPathFn.getCallee()->stripPointerCasts()));
4011 CheckCall->setDoesNotThrow();
4012
4013 EmitBlock(Cont);
4014}

4016// Emit a stub for __cfi_check function so that the linker knows about this
4017// symbol in LTO mode.
4018void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiCheckStub() {
4019 llvm::Module *M = &CGM.getModule();
4020 auto &Ctx = M->getContext();
4021 llvm::Function *F = llvm::Function::Create(
4022 llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy}, false),
4023 llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, "__cfi_check", M);
4024 CGM.setDSOLocal(F);
4025 llvm::BasicBlock *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "entry", F);
4026 // FIXME: consider emitting an intrinsic call like
4027 // call void @llvm.cfi_check(i64 %0, i8* %1, i8* %2)
4028 // which can be lowered in CrossDSOCFI pass to the actual contents of
4029 // __cfi_check. This would allow inlining of __cfi_check calls.
4030 llvm::CallInst::Create(
4031 llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, llvm::Intrinsic::trap), "", BB);
4032 llvm::ReturnInst::Create(Ctx, nullptr, BB);
4033}
4034
4035// This function is basically a switch over the CFI failure kind, which is
4036// extracted from CFICheckFailData (1st function argument). Each case is either
4037// llvm.trap or a call to one of the two runtime handlers, based on
4038// -fsanitize-trap and -fsanitize-recover settings. Default case (invalid
4039// failure kind) traps, but this should really never happen. CFICheckFailData
4040// can be nullptr if the calling module has -fsanitize-trap behavior for this
4041// check kind; in this case __cfi_check_fail traps as well.
4042void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiCheckFail() {
4043 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
4044 FunctionArgList Args;
4045 ImplicitParamDecl ArgData(getContext(), getContext().VoidPtrTy,
4046 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
4047 ImplicitParamDecl ArgAddr(getContext(), getContext().VoidPtrTy,
4048 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
4049 Args.push_back(&ArgData);
4050 Args.push_back(&ArgAddr);
4051
4052 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
4053 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(getContext().VoidTy, Args);
4054
4055 llvm::Function *F = llvm::Function::Create(
4056 llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {VoidPtrTy, VoidPtrTy}, false),
4057 llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage, "__cfi_check_fail", &CGM.getModule());
4058 F->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
4059
4060 StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), CGM.getContext().VoidTy, F, FI, Args,
4061 SourceLocation());
4062
4063 // This function should not be affected by blacklist. This function does
4064 // not have a source location, but "src:*" would still apply. Revert any
4065 // changes to SanOpts made in StartFunction.
4066 SanOpts = CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize;
4067
4068 llvm::Value *Data =
4069 EmitLoadOfScalar(GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ArgData), /*Volatile=*/false,
4070 CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy, ArgData.getLocation());
4071 llvm::Value *Addr =
4072 EmitLoadOfScalar(GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ArgAddr), /*Volatile=*/false,
4073 CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy, ArgAddr.getLocation());
4074
4075 // Data == nullptr means the calling module has trap behaviour for this check.
4076 llvm::Value *DataIsNotNullPtr =
4077 Builder.CreateICmpNE(Data, llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(Int8PtrTy));
4078 EmitTrapCheck(DataIsNotNullPtr);
4079
4080 llvm::StructType *SourceLocationTy =
4081 llvm::StructType::get(VoidPtrTy, Int32Ty, Int32Ty);
4082 llvm::StructType *CfiCheckFailDataTy =
4083 llvm::StructType::get(Int8Ty, SourceLocationTy, VoidPtrTy);
4084
4085 llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(
4086 CfiCheckFailDataTy,
4087 Builder.CreatePointerCast(Data, CfiCheckFailDataTy->getPointerTo(0)), 0,
4088 0);
4089 Address CheckKindAddr(V, getIntAlign());
4090 llvm::Value *CheckKind = Builder.CreateLoad(CheckKindAddr);
4091
4092 llvm::Value *AllVtables = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(
4093 CGM.getLLVMContext(),
4094 llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables"));
4095 llvm::Value *ValidVtable = Builder.CreateZExt(
4096 Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test),
4097 {Addr, AllVtables}),
4098 IntPtrTy);
4099
4100 const std::pair<int, SanitizerMask> CheckKinds[] = {
4101 {CFITCK_VCall, SanitizerKind::CFIVCall},
4102 {CFITCK_NVCall, SanitizerKind::CFINVCall},
4103 {CFITCK_DerivedCast, SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast},
4104 {CFITCK_UnrelatedCast, SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast},
4105 {CFITCK_ICall, SanitizerKind::CFIICall}};
4106
4107 SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 5> Checks;
4108 for (auto CheckKindMaskPair : CheckKinds) {
4109 int Kind = CheckKindMaskPair.first;
4110 SanitizerMask Mask = CheckKindMaskPair.second;
4111 llvm::Value *Cond =
4112 Builder.CreateICmpNE(CheckKind, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Kind));
4113 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(Mask))
4114 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, Mask), SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, {},
4115 {Data, Addr, ValidVtable});
4116 else
4117 EmitTrapCheck(Cond);
4118 }
4119
4120 FinishFunction();
4121 // The only reference to this function will be created during LTO link.
4122 // Make sure it survives until then.
4123 CGM.addUsedGlobal(F);
4124}
