4126void CodeGenFunction::EmitUnreachable(SourceLocation Loc) {
4127 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Unreachable)) {
4128 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
4129 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(static_cast<llvm::Value *>(Builder.getFalse()),
4130 SanitizerKind::Unreachable),
4131 SanitizerHandler::BuiltinUnreachable,
4132 EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), None);
4133 }
4134 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4135}
4136
4137void CodeGenFunction::EmitTrapCheck(llvm::Value *Checked) {
4138 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
4139
4140 // If we're optimizing, collapse all calls to trap down to just one per
4141 // function to save on code size.
4142 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel || !TrapBB) {
4143 TrapBB = createBasicBlock("trap");
4144 Builder.CreateCondBr(Checked, Cont, TrapBB);
4145 EmitBlock(TrapBB);
4146 llvm::CallInst *TrapCall = EmitTrapCall(llvm::Intrinsic::trap);
4147 TrapCall->setDoesNotReturn();
4148 TrapCall->setDoesNotThrow();
4149 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4150 } else {
4151 Builder.CreateCondBr(Checked, Cont, TrapBB);
4152 }
4153
4154 EmitBlock(Cont);
4155}
4156
4157llvm::CallInst *CodeGenFunction::EmitTrapCall(llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrID) {
4158 llvm::CallInst *TrapCall = Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrID));
4159
4160 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName.empty()) {
4161 auto A = llvm::Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), "trap-func-name",
4162 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName);
4163 TrapCall->addAttribute(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, A);
4164 }
4165
4166 return TrapCall;
4167}
4168
4169Address CodeGenFunction::EmitArrayToPointerDecay(const Expr *E,
4170 LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
4171 TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
4172 assert(E->getType()->isArrayType() &&
4173 "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
4174
4175 // Expressions of array type can't be bitfields or vector elements.
4176 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E);
4177 Address Addr = LV.getAddress();
4178
4179 // If the array type was an incomplete type, we need to make sure
4180 // the decay ends up being the right type.
4181 llvm::Type *NewTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4182 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, NewTy);
4183
4184 // Note that VLA pointers are always decayed, so we don't need to do
4185 // anything here.
4186 if (!E->getType()->isVariableArrayType()) {
4187 assert(isa<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType()) &&
4188 "Expected pointer to array");
4189 Addr = Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Addr, 0, "arraydecay");
4190 }
4191
4192 // The result of this decay conversion points to an array element within the
4193 // base lvalue. However, since TBAA currently does not support representing
4194 // accesses to elements of member arrays, we conservatively represent accesses
4195 // to the pointee object as if it had no any base lvalue specified.
4196 // TODO: Support TBAA for member arrays.
4197 QualType EltType = E->getType()->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe()->getElementType();
4198 if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
4199 if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(EltType);
4200
4201 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ConvertTypeForMem(EltType));
4202 // FIXME-cheri-qual: should getTargetAddressSpace return 200?
4203 unsigned AS =
4204 CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(E->getType().getAddressSpace());
4205 llvm::PointerType *PtrTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(Addr.getPointer()->getType());
4206 if (PtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != AS) {
4207 if (getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
4208 assert(PtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
4209 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS() &&
4210 "Expected memory capability address space in pure capability ABI");
4211 assert(E->getType().getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default &&
4212 "non-zero address space in pure capability ABI");
4213 return Addr;
4214 } else
4215 Addr = Address(Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(Addr.getPointer(),
4216 llvm::PointerType::get(PtrTy->getElementType(), AS)),
4217 Addr.getAlignment());
4218 }
4219 if (getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() >= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe) {
4220 auto BoundedResult = setCHERIBoundsOnArrayDecay(Addr.getPointer(), E);
4221 assert(BoundedResult->getType() == Addr.getType());
4222 Addr = Address(BoundedResult, Addr.getAlignment());
4223 }
4224 return Addr;
4225}
4226
4227/// isSimpleArrayDecayOperand - If the specified expr is a simple decay from an
4228/// array to pointer, return the array subexpression.
4229static const Expr *isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(const Expr *E) {
4230 // If this isn't just an array->pointer decay, bail out.
4231 const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E);
4232 if (!CE || CE->getCastKind() != CK_ArrayToPointerDecay)
4233 return nullptr;
4234
4235 // If this is a decay from variable width array, bail out.
4236 const Expr *SubExpr = CE->getSubExpr();
4237 if (SubExpr->getType()->isVariableArrayType())
4238 return nullptr;
4239
4240 return SubExpr;
4241}
4242
4243static llvm::Value *
4244emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *ptr,
4245 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> indices, bool inbounds,
4246 bool signedIndices, const Expr *E,
4247 const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx") {
4248
4249 if (auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E)) {
4250 if (CGF.getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() >= LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe) {
4251 // CSetBounds must be done before the GEP otherwise we set the base before
4252 // adding the index!
4253 auto BoundedResult = CGF.setCHERIBoundsOnArraySubscript(ptr, ASE);
4254 assert(BoundedResult->getType() == ptr->getType());
4255 ptr = BoundedResult;
4256 }
4257 } else {
4258 // For now don't setbounds for OMPArraySectionExpr
4259 assert(isa<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E) && "Called with wrong expr type");
4260 }
4261 if (inbounds) {
4262 return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(ptr, indices, signedIndices,
4263 CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction,
4264 E->getExprLoc(), name);
4265 } else {
4266 return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(ptr, indices, name);
4267 }
4268}
4269
4270static CharUnits getArrayElementAlign(CharUnits arrayAlign,
4271 llvm::Value *idx,
4272 CharUnits eltSize) {
4273 // If we have a constant index, we can use the exact offset of the
4274 // element we're accessing.
4275 if (auto constantIdx = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx)) {
4276 CharUnits offset = constantIdx->getZExtValue() * eltSize;
4277 return arrayAlign.alignmentAtOffset(offset);
4278
4279 // Otherwise, use the worst-case alignment for any element.
4280 } else {
4281 return arrayAlign.alignmentOfArrayElement(eltSize);
4282 }
4283}
4284
4285static QualType getFixedSizeElementType(const ASTContext &ctx,
4286 const VariableArrayType *vla) {
4287 QualType eltType;
4288 do {
4289 eltType = vla->getElementType();
4290 } while ((vla = ctx.getAsVariableArrayType(eltType)));
4291 return eltType;
4292}
4293
4294static Address emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address addr,
4295 ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> indices,
4296 QualType eltType, bool inbounds,
4297 bool signedIndices, const Expr *E,
4298 const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx") {
4299 // All the indices except that last must be zero.
4300#ifndef NDEBUG
4301 for (auto idx : indices.drop_back())
4302 assert(isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx) &&
4303 cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx)->isZero());
4304#endif
4305
4306 // Determine the element size of the statically-sized base. This is
4307 // the thing that the indices are expressed in terms of.
4308 if (auto vla = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(eltType)) {
4309 eltType = getFixedSizeElementType(CGF.getContext(), vla);
4310 }
4311
4312 // We can use that to compute the best alignment of the element.
4313 CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(eltType);
4314 CharUnits eltAlign =
4315 getArrayElementAlign(addr.getAlignment(), indices.back(), eltSize);
4316
4317 llvm::Value *eltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(CGF, addr.getPointer(), indices,
4318 inbounds, signedIndices, E, name);
4319 return Address(eltPtr, eltAlign);
4320}
4321
4322LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitArraySubscriptExpr(const ArraySubscriptExpr *E,
4323 bool Accessed) {
4324 // The index must always be an integer, which is not an aggregate. Emit it
4325 // in lexical order (this complexity is, sadly, required by C++17).
4326 llvm::Value *IdxPre =
4327 (E->getLHS() == E->getIdx()) ? EmitScalarExpr(E->getIdx()) : nullptr;
4328 bool SignedIndices = false;
4329 auto EmitIdxAfterBase = [&, IdxPre](bool Promote) -> llvm::Value * {
4330 auto *Idx = IdxPre;
4331 if (E->getLHS() != E->getIdx()) {
4332 assert(E->getRHS() == E->getIdx() && "index was neither LHS nor RHS");
4333 Idx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getIdx());
4334 }
4335
4336 QualType IdxTy = E->getIdx()->getType();
4337 bool IdxSigned = IdxTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
4338 SignedIndices |= IdxSigned;
4339
4340 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
4341 EmitBoundsCheck(E, E->getBase(), Idx, IdxTy, Accessed);
4342
4343 if (Idx->getType()->isPointerTy())
4344 Idx = getCapabilityIntegerValue(Idx);
4345
4346 // Extend or truncate the index type to 32 or 64-bits.
4347 if (Promote && Idx->getType() != IntPtrTy)
4348 Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(Idx, IntPtrTy, IdxSigned, "idxprom");
4349
4350 return Idx;
4351 };
4352 IdxPre = nullptr;
4353
4354 // If the base is a vector type, then we are forming a vector element lvalue
4355 // with this subscript.
4356 if (E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType() &&
4357 !isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E->getBase())) {
4358 // Emit the vector as an lvalue to get its address.
4359 LValue LHS = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4360 auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/false);
4361 assert(LHS.isSimple() && "Can only subscript lvalue vectors here!");
4362 assert(getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() < LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe &&
4363 "vector subobject bounds not implemented yet");
4364 return LValue::MakeVectorElt(LHS.getAddress(), Idx, E->getBase()->getType(),
4365 LHS.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4366 }
4367
4368 // All the other cases basically behave like simple offsetting.
4369
4370 // Handle the extvector case we ignored above.
4371 if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E->getBase())) {
4372 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4373 auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4374 Address Addr = EmitExtVectorElementLValue(LV);
4375
4376 QualType EltType = LV.getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
4377 Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, EltType, /*inbounds*/ true,
4378 SignedIndices, E);
4379 assert(getLangOpts().getCheriBounds() < LangOptions::CBM_SubObjectsSafe &&
4380 "ExtVectorElementExpr subobject bounds not implemented yet");
4381 return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, EltType, LV.getBaseInfo(),
4382 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, EltType));
4383 }
4384
4385 LValueBaseInfo EltBaseInfo;
4386 TBAAAccessInfo EltTBAAInfo;
4387 Address Addr = Address::invalid();
4388 if (const VariableArrayType *vla =
4389 getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(E->getType())) {
4390 // The base must be a pointer, which is not an aggregate. Emit
4391 // it. It needs to be emitted first in case it's what captures
4392 // the VLA bounds.
4393 Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
4394 auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4395
4396 // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
4397 llvm::Value *numElements = getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
4398
4399 // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
4400 // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
4401 // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
4402 // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
4403 if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined()) {
4404 Idx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, numElements);
4405 } else {
4406 Idx = Builder.CreateNSWMul(Idx, numElements);
4407 }
4408
4409 Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, vla->getElementType(),
4410 !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4411 SignedIndices, E);
4412
4413 } else if (const ObjCObjectType *OIT = E->getType()->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()){
4414 // Indexing over an interface, as in "NSString *P; P[4];"
4415
4416 // Emit the base pointer.
4417 Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
4418 auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4419
4420 CharUnits InterfaceSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(OIT);
4421 llvm::Value *InterfaceSizeVal =
4422 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Idx->getType(), InterfaceSize.getQuantity());
4423
4424 llvm::Value *ScaledIdx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, InterfaceSizeVal);
4425
4426 // We don't necessarily build correct LLVM struct types for ObjC
4427 // interfaces, so we can't rely on GEP to do this scaling
4428 // correctly, so we need to cast to i8*. FIXME: is this actually
4429 // true? A lot of other things in the fragile ABI would break...
4430 llvm::Type *OrigBaseTy = Addr.getType();
4431 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, Int8Ty);
4432
4433 // Do the GEP.
4434 CharUnits EltAlign =
4435 getArrayElementAlign(Addr.getAlignment(), Idx, InterfaceSize);
4436 llvm::Value *EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
4437 *this, Addr.getPointer(), ScaledIdx, false, SignedIndices, E);
4438 Addr = Address(EltPtr, EltAlign);
4439
4440 // Cast back.
4441 Addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, OrigBaseTy);
4442 } else if (const Expr *Array = isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(E->getBase())) {
4443 // If this is A[i] where A is an array, the frontend will have decayed the
4444 // base to be a ArrayToPointerDecay implicit cast. While correct, it is
4445 // inefficient at -O0 to emit a "gep A, 0, 0" when codegen'ing it, then a
4446 // "gep x, i" here. Emit one "gep A, 0, i".
4447 assert(Array->getType()->isArrayType() &&
4448 "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
4449 LValue ArrayLV;
4450 // For simple multidimensional array indexing, set the 'accessed' flag for
4451 // better bounds-checking of the base expression.
4452 if (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Array))
4453 ArrayLV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(ASE, /*Accessed*/ true);
4454 else
4455 ArrayLV = EmitLValue(Array);
4456 auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4457
4458 // Propagate the alignment from the array itself to the result.
4459 Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
4460 *this, ArrayLV.getAddress(), {CGM.getSize(CharUnits::Zero()), Idx},
4461 E->getType(), !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(), SignedIndices,
4462 E);
4463 EltBaseInfo = ArrayLV.getBaseInfo();
4464 EltTBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(ArrayLV, E->getType());
4465 } else {
4466 // The base must be a pointer; emit it with an estimate of its alignment.
4467 Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
4468 auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4469 Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, E->getType(),
4470 !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4471 SignedIndices, E);
4472 }
4473
4474 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType(), EltBaseInfo, EltTBAAInfo);
4475
4476 if (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
4477 getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
4478 LV.setNonGC(!E->isOBJCGCCandidate(getContext()));
4479 setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
4480 }
4481 return LV;
4482}
4483
4484static Address emitOMPArraySectionBase(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *Base,
4485 LValueBaseInfo &BaseInfo,
4486 TBAAAccessInfo &TBAAInfo,
4487 QualType BaseTy, QualType ElTy,
4488 bool IsLowerBound) {
4489 LValue BaseLVal;
4490 if (auto *ASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(Base->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
4491 BaseLVal = CGF.EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(ASE, IsLowerBound);
4492 if (BaseTy->isArrayType()) {
4493 Address Addr = BaseLVal.getAddress();
4494 BaseInfo = BaseLVal.getBaseInfo();
4495
4496 // If the array type was an incomplete type, we need to make sure
4497 // the decay ends up being the right type.
4498 llvm::Type *NewTy = CGF.ConvertType(BaseTy);
4499 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, NewTy);
4500
4501 // Note that VLA pointers are always decayed, so we don't need to do
4502 // anything here.
4503 if (!BaseTy->isVariableArrayType()) {
4504 assert(isa<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType()) &&
4505 "Expected pointer to array");
4506 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Addr, 0, "arraydecay");
4507 }
4508
4509 return CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr,
4510 CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ElTy));
4511 }
4512 LValueBaseInfo TypeBaseInfo;
4513 TBAAAccessInfo TypeTBAAInfo;
4514 CharUnits Align = CGF.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ElTy, &TypeBaseInfo,
4515 &TypeTBAAInfo);
4516 BaseInfo.mergeForCast(TypeBaseInfo);
4517 TBAAInfo = CGF.CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForCast(TBAAInfo, TypeTBAAInfo);
4518 return Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(BaseLVal.getAddress()), Align);
4519 }
4520 return CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(Base, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4521}
4522
4523LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(const OMPArraySectionExpr *E,
4524 bool IsLowerBound) {
4525 QualType BaseTy = OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(E->getBase());
4526 QualType ResultExprTy;
4527 if (auto *AT = getContext().getAsArrayType(BaseTy))
4528 ResultExprTy = AT->getElementType();
4529 else
4530 ResultExprTy = BaseTy->getPointeeType();
4531 llvm::Value *Idx = nullptr;
4532 if (IsLowerBound || E->getColonLoc().isInvalid()) {
4533 // Requesting lower bound or upper bound, but without provided length and
4534 // without ':' symbol for the default length -> length = 1.
4535 // Idx = LowerBound ?: 0;
4536 if (auto *LowerBound = E->getLowerBound()) {
4537 Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4538 EmitScalarExpr(LowerBound), IntPtrTy,
4539 LowerBound->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
4540 } else
4541 Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
4542 } else {
4543 // Try to emit length or lower bound as constant. If this is possible, 1
4544 // is subtracted from constant length or lower bound. Otherwise, emit LLVM
4545 // IR (LB + Len) - 1.
4546 auto &C = CGM.getContext();
4547 auto *Length = E->getLength();
4548 llvm::APSInt ConstLength;
4549 if (Length) {
4550 // Idx = LowerBound + Length - 1;
4551 if (Length->isIntegerConstantExpr(ConstLength, C)) {
4552 ConstLength = ConstLength.zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4553 Length = nullptr;
4554 }
4555 auto *LowerBound = E->getLowerBound();
4556 llvm::APSInt ConstLowerBound(PointerWidthInBits, /*isUnsigned=*/false);
4557 if (LowerBound && LowerBound->isIntegerConstantExpr(ConstLowerBound, C)) {
4558 ConstLowerBound = ConstLowerBound.zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4559 LowerBound = nullptr;
4560 }
4561 if (!Length)
4562 --ConstLength;
4563 else if (!LowerBound)
4564 --ConstLowerBound;
4565
4566 if (Length || LowerBound) {
4567 auto *LowerBoundVal =
4568 LowerBound
4569 ? Builder.CreateIntCast(
4570 EmitScalarExpr(LowerBound), IntPtrTy,
4571 LowerBound->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation())
4572 : llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLowerBound);
4573 auto *LengthVal =
4574 Length
4575 ? Builder.CreateIntCast(
4576 EmitScalarExpr(Length), IntPtrTy,
4577 Length->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation())
4578 : llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength);
4579 Idx = Builder.CreateAdd(LowerBoundVal, LengthVal, "lb_add_len",
4580 /*HasNUW=*/false,
4581 !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4582 if (Length && LowerBound) {
4583 Idx = Builder.CreateSub(
4584 Idx, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, /*V=*/1), "idx_sub_1",
4585 /*HasNUW=*/false, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4586 }
4587 } else
4588 Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength + ConstLowerBound);
4589 } else {
4590 // Idx = ArraySize - 1;
4591 QualType ArrayTy = BaseTy->isPointerType()
4592 ? E->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->getType()
4593 : BaseTy;
4594 if (auto *VAT = C.getAsVariableArrayType(ArrayTy)) {
4595 Length = VAT->getSizeExpr();
4596 if (Length->isIntegerConstantExpr(ConstLength, C))
4597 Length = nullptr;
4598 } else {
4599 auto *CAT = C.getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayTy);
4600 ConstLength = CAT->getSize();
4601 }
4602 if (Length) {
4603 auto *LengthVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4604 EmitScalarExpr(Length), IntPtrTy,
4605 Length->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
4606 Idx = Builder.CreateSub(
4607 LengthVal, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, /*V=*/1), "len_sub_1",
4608 /*HasNUW=*/false, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4609 } else {
4610 ConstLength = ConstLength.zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4611 --ConstLength;
4612 Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength);
4613 }
4614 }
4615 }
4616 assert(Idx);
4617
4618 Address EltPtr = Address::invalid();
4619 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4620 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4621 if (auto *VLA = getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(ResultExprTy)) {
4622 // The base must be a pointer, which is not an aggregate. Emit
4623 // it. It needs to be emitted first in case it's what captures
4624 // the VLA bounds.
4625 Address Base =
4626 emitOMPArraySectionBase(*this, E->getBase(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo,
4627 BaseTy, VLA->getElementType(), IsLowerBound);
4628 // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
4629 llvm::Value *NumElements = getVLASize(VLA).NumElts;
4630
4631 // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
4632 // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
4633 // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
4634 // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
4635 if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
4636 Idx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, NumElements);
4637 else
4638 Idx = Builder.CreateNSWMul(Idx, NumElements);
4639 EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Base, Idx, VLA->getElementType(),
4640 !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4641 /*SignedIndices=*/false, E);
4642 } else if (const Expr *Array = isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(E->getBase())) {
4643 // If this is A[i] where A is an array, the frontend will have decayed the
4644 // base to be a ArrayToPointerDecay implicit cast. While correct, it is
4645 // inefficient at -O0 to emit a "gep A, 0, 0" when codegen'ing it, then a
4646 // "gep x, i" here. Emit one "gep A, 0, i".
4647 assert(Array->getType()->isArrayType() &&
4648 "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
4649 LValue ArrayLV;
4650 // For simple multidimensional array indexing, set the 'accessed' flag for
4651 // better bounds-checking of the base expression.
4652 if (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Array))
4653 ArrayLV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(ASE, /*Accessed*/ true);
4654 else
4655 ArrayLV = EmitLValue(Array);
4656
4657 // Propagate the alignment from the array itself to the result.
4658 EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
4659 *this, ArrayLV.getAddress(), {CGM.getSize(CharUnits::Zero()), Idx},
4660 ResultExprTy, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4661 /*SignedIndices=*/false, E);
4662 BaseInfo = ArrayLV.getBaseInfo();
4663 TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(ArrayLV, ResultExprTy);
4664 } else {
4665 Address Base = emitOMPArraySectionBase(*this, E->getBase(), BaseInfo,
4666 TBAAInfo, BaseTy, ResultExprTy,
4667 IsLowerBound);
4668 EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Base, Idx, ResultExprTy,
4669 !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4670 /*SignedIndices=*/false, E);
4671 }
4672
4673 return MakeAddrLValue(EltPtr, ResultExprTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4674}
4675
4676LValue CodeGenFunction::
4677EmitExtVectorElementExpr(const ExtVectorElementExpr *E) {
4678 // Emit the base vector as an l-value.
4679 LValue Base;
4680
4681 // ExtVectorElementExpr's base can either be a vector or pointer to vector.
4682 if (E->isArrow()) {
4683 // If it is a pointer to a vector, emit the address and form an lvalue with
4684 // it.
4685 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4686 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4687 Address Ptr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4688 const PointerType *PT = E->getBase()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
4689 Base = MakeAddrLValue(Ptr, PT->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4690 Base.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
4691 } else if (E->getBase()->isGLValue()) {
4692 // Otherwise, if the base is an lvalue ( as in the case of foo.x.x),
4693 // emit the base as an lvalue.
4694 assert(E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType());
4695 Base = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4696 } else {
4697 // Otherwise, the base is a normal rvalue (as in (V+V).x), emit it as such.
4698 assert(E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType() &&
4699 "Result must be a vector");
4700 llvm::Value *Vec = EmitScalarExpr(E->getBase());
4701
4702 // Store the vector to memory (because LValue wants an address).
4703 Address VecMem = CreateMemTemp(E->getBase()->getType());
4704 Builder.CreateStore(Vec, VecMem);
4705 Base = MakeAddrLValue(VecMem, E->getBase()->getType(),
4706 AlignmentSource::Decl);
4707 }
4708
4709 QualType type =
4710 E->getType().withCVRQualifiers(Base.getQuals().getCVRQualifiers());
4711
4712 // Encode the element access list into a vector of unsigned indices.
4713 SmallVector<uint32_t, 4> Indices;
4714 E->getEncodedElementAccess(Indices);
4715
4716 if (Base.isSimple()) {
4717 llvm::Constant *CV =
4718 llvm::ConstantDataVector::get(getLLVMContext(), Indices);
4719 return LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Base.getAddress(), CV, type,
4720 Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4721 }
4722 assert(Base.isExtVectorElt() && "Can only subscript lvalue vec elts here!");
4723
4724 llvm::Constant *BaseElts = Base.getExtVectorElts();
4725 SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> CElts;
4726
4727 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Indices.size(); i != e; ++i)
4728 CElts.push_back(BaseElts->getAggregateElement(Indices[i]));
4729 llvm::Constant *CV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(CElts);
4730 return LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Base.getExtVectorAddress(), CV, type,
4731 Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4732}
4733
4734LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitMemberExpr(const MemberExpr *E) {
4735 if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(*this, E)) {
4736 EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
4737 return EmitDeclRefLValue(DRE);
4738 }
4739
4740 Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
4741 // If this is s.x, emit s as an lvalue. If it is s->x, emit s as a scalar.
4742 LValue BaseLV;
4743 if (E->isArrow()) {
4744 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4745 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4746 Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(BaseExpr, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4747 QualType PtrTy = BaseExpr->getType()->getPointeeType();
4748 SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
4749 bool IsBaseCXXThis = IsWrappedCXXThis(BaseExpr);
4750 if (IsBaseCXXThis)
4751 SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Alignment, true);
4752 if (IsBaseCXXThis || isa<DeclRefExpr>(BaseExpr))
4753 SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
4754 EmitTypeCheck(TCK_MemberAccess, E->getExprLoc(), Addr.getPointer(), PtrTy,
4755 /*Alignment=*/CharUnits::Zero(), SkippedChecks);
4756 BaseLV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, PtrTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4757 } else
4758 BaseLV = EmitCheckedLValue(BaseExpr, TCK_MemberAccess);
4759
4760 NamedDecl *ND = E->getMemberDecl();
4761 if (auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ND)) {
4762 LValue LV = EmitLValueForField(BaseLV, Field);
4763 setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
4764 return LV;
4765 }
4766
4767 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND))
4768 return EmitFunctionDeclLValue(*this, E, FD);
4769
4770 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled member declaration!");
4771}

4774/// one of its members.
4775LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForLambdaField(const FieldDecl *Field) {
4776 assert(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)->getParent()->isLambda());
4777 assert(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)->getParent() == Field->getParent());
4778 QualType LambdaTagType =
4779 getContext().getTagDeclType(Field->getParent());
4780 LValue LambdaLV = MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(CXXABIThisValue, LambdaTagType);

4782}

4784/// Drill down to the storage of a field without walking into
4785/// reference types.
4786///
4787/// The resulting address doesn't necessarily have the right type.
4788static Address emitAddrOfFieldStorage(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address base,
4789 const FieldDecl *field) {
4790 const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4791
4792 unsigned idx =
4793 CGF.CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(rec).getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4794
4795 return CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(base, idx, field->getName());
4796}
4797
4798static bool hasAnyVptr(const QualType Type, const ASTContext &Context) {
4799 const auto *RD = Type.getTypePtr()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4800 if (!RD)
4801 return false;
4802
4803 if (RD->isDynamicClass())
4804 return true;
4805
4806 for (const auto &Base : RD->bases())
4807 if (hasAnyVptr(Base.getType(), Context))
4808 return true;
4809
4810 for (const FieldDecl *Field : RD->fields())
4811 if (hasAnyVptr(Field->getType(), Context))
4812 return true;
4813
4814 return false;
4815}
4816
4817LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForField(LValue base,
4818 const FieldDecl *field) {
4819 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo = base.getBaseInfo();
4820
4821 if (field->isBitField()) {
4822 const CGRecordLayout &RL =
4823 CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(field->getParent());
4824 const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = RL.getBitFieldInfo(field);
4825 Address Addr = base.getAddress();
4826 unsigned Idx = RL.getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4827 if (Idx != 0)
4828 // For structs, we GEP to the field that the record layout suggests.
4829 Addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Addr, Idx, field->getName());
4830 // Get the access type.
4831 llvm::Type *FieldIntTy =
4832 llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(), Info.StorageSize);
4833 if (Addr.getElementType() != FieldIntTy)
4834 Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, FieldIntTy);
4835
4836 QualType fieldType =
4837 field->getType().withCVRQualifiers(base.getVRQualifiers());
4838 // TODO: Support TBAA for bit fields.
4839 LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource());
4840 return LValue::MakeBitfield(Addr, Info, fieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
4841 TBAAAccessInfo());
4842 }
4843
4844 // Fields of may-alias structures are may-alias themselves.
4845 // FIXME: this should get propagated down through anonymous structs
4846 // and unions.
4847 QualType FieldType = field->getType();
4848 const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4849 AlignmentSource BaseAlignSource = BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource();
4850 LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(getFieldAlignmentSource(BaseAlignSource));
4851 TBAAAccessInfo FieldTBAAInfo;
4852 if (base.getTBAAInfo().isMayAlias() ||
4853 rec->hasAttr<MayAliasAttr>() || FieldType->isVectorType()) {
4854 FieldTBAAInfo = TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo();
4855 } else if (rec->isUnion()) {
4856 // TODO: Support TBAA for unions.
4857 FieldTBAAInfo = TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo();
4858 } else {
4859 // If no base type been assigned for the base access, then try to generate
4860 // one for this base lvalue.
4861 FieldTBAAInfo = base.getTBAAInfo();
4862 if (!FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType) {
4863 FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType = CGM.getTBAABaseTypeInfo(base.getType());
4864 assert(!FieldTBAAInfo.Offset &&
4865 "Nonzero offset for an access with no base type!");
4866 }
4867
4868 // Adjust offset to be relative to the base type.
4869 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
4870 getContext().getASTRecordLayout(field->getParent());
4871 unsigned CharWidth = getContext().getCharWidth();
4872 if (FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType)
4873 FieldTBAAInfo.Offset +=
4874 Layout.getFieldOffset(field->getFieldIndex()) / CharWidth;
4875
4876 // Update the final access type and size.
4877 FieldTBAAInfo.AccessType = CGM.getTBAATypeInfo(FieldType);
4878 FieldTBAAInfo.Size =
4879 getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(FieldType).getQuantity();
4880 }
4881
4882 Address addr = base.getAddress();
4883 if (auto *ClassDef = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(rec)) {
4884 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4885 ClassDef->isDynamicClass()) {
4886 // Getting to any field of dynamic object requires stripping dynamic
4887 // information provided by invariant.group. This is because accessing
4888 // fields may leak the real address of dynamic object, which could result
4889 // in miscompilation when leaked pointer would be compared.
4890 auto *stripped = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(addr.getPointer());
4891 addr = Address(stripped, addr.getAlignment());
4892 }
4893 }
4894
4895 unsigned RecordCVR = base.getVRQualifiers();
4896 if (rec->isUnion()) {
4897 // For unions, there is no pointer adjustment.
4898 assert(!FieldType->isReferenceType() && "union has reference member");
4899 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4900 hasAnyVptr(FieldType, getContext()))
4901 // Because unions can easily skip invariant.barriers, we need to add
4902 // a barrier every time CXXRecord field with vptr is referenced.
4903 addr = Address(Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(addr.getPointer()),
4904 addr.getAlignment());
4905 } else {
4906 // For structs, we GEP to the field that the record layout suggests.
4907 addr = emitAddrOfFieldStorage(*this, addr, field);
4908
4909 // If this is a reference field, load the reference right now.
4910 if (FieldType->isReferenceType()) {
4911 LValue RefLVal = MakeAddrLValue(addr, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
4912 FieldTBAAInfo);
4913 if (RecordCVR & Qualifiers::Volatile)
4914 RefLVal.getQuals().addVolatile();
4915 addr = EmitLoadOfReference(RefLVal, &FieldBaseInfo, &FieldTBAAInfo);
4916
4917 // Qualifiers on the struct don't apply to the referencee.
4918 RecordCVR = 0;
4919 FieldType = FieldType->getPointeeType();
4920 }
4921 }
4922
4923 // Make sure that the address is pointing to the right type. This is critical
4924 // for both unions and structs. A union needs a bitcast, a struct element
4925 // will need a bitcast if the LLVM type laid out doesn't match the desired
4926 // type.
4927 addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
4928 addr, CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType), field->getName());
4929
4930 if (field->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
4931 addr = EmitFieldAnnotations(field, addr);
4932
4933 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(addr, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo, FieldTBAAInfo);
4934 LV.getQuals().addCVRQualifiers(RecordCVR);
4935
4936 // __weak attribute on a field is ignored.
4937 if (LV.getQuals().getObjCGCAttr() == Qualifiers::Weak)
4938 LV.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
4939
4940 return LV;
4941}
4942
4943LValue
4944CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(LValue Base,
4945 const FieldDecl *Field) {
4946 QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
4947
4948 if (!FieldType->isReferenceType())
4949 return EmitLValueForField(Base, Field);
4950
4951 Address V = emitAddrOfFieldStorage(*this, Base.getAddress(), Field);
4952
4953 // Make sure that the address is pointing to the right type.
4954 llvm::Type *llvmType = ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType);
4955 V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(V, llvmType, Field->getName());
4956
4957 // TODO: Generate TBAA information that describes this access as a structure
4958 // member access and not just an access to an object of the field's type. This
4959 // should be similar to what we do in EmitLValueForField().
4960 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo = Base.getBaseInfo();
4961 AlignmentSource FieldAlignSource = BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource();
4962 LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(getFieldAlignmentSource(FieldAlignSource));
4963 return MakeAddrLValue(V, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
4964 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(Base, FieldType));
4965}

4996/// Emit the operand of a glvalue conditional operator. This is either a glvalue
4997/// or a (possibly-parenthesized) throw-expression. If this is a throw, no
4998/// LValue is returned and the current block has been terminated.
4999static Optional<LValue> EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5000 const Expr *Operand) {
5001 if (auto *ThrowExpr = dyn_cast<CXXThrowExpr>(Operand->IgnoreParens())) {
5002 CGF.EmitCXXThrowExpr(ThrowExpr, /*KeepInsertionPoint*/false);
5003 return None;
5004 }
5005
5006 return CGF.EmitLValue(Operand);
5007}
5008
5009LValue CodeGenFunction::
5010EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(const AbstractConditionalOperator *expr) {
5011 if (!expr->isGLValue()) {
5012 // ?: here should be an aggregate.
5013 assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(expr->getType()) &&
5014 "Unexpected conditional operator!");
5015 return EmitAggExprToLValue(expr);
5016 }
5017
5018 OpaqueValueMapping binding(*this, expr);
5019
5020 const Expr *condExpr = expr->getCond();
5021 bool CondExprBool;
5022 if (ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(condExpr, CondExprBool)) {
5023 const Expr *live = expr->getTrueExpr(), *dead = expr->getFalseExpr();
5024 if (!CondExprBool) std::swap(live, dead);
5025
5026 if (!ContainsLabel(dead)) {
5027 // If the true case is live, we need to track its region.
5028 if (CondExprBool)
5029 incrementProfileCounter(expr);
5030 return EmitLValue(live);
5031 }
5032 }
5033
5034 llvm::BasicBlock *lhsBlock = createBasicBlock("cond.true");
5035 llvm::BasicBlock *rhsBlock = createBasicBlock("cond.false");
5036 llvm::BasicBlock *contBlock = createBasicBlock("cond.end");
5037
5038 ConditionalEvaluation eval(*this);
5039 EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(condExpr, lhsBlock, rhsBlock, getProfileCount(expr));
5040
5041 // Any temporaries created here are conditional.
5042 EmitBlock(lhsBlock);
5043 incrementProfileCounter(expr);
5044 eval.begin(*this);
5045 Optional<LValue> lhs =
5046 EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(*this, expr->getTrueExpr());
5047 eval.end(*this);
5048
5049 if (lhs && !lhs->isSimple())
5050 return EmitUnsupportedLValue(expr, "conditional operator");
5051
5052 lhsBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5053 if (lhs)
5054 Builder.CreateBr(contBlock);
5055
5056 // Any temporaries created here are conditional.
5057 EmitBlock(rhsBlock);
5058 eval.begin(*this);
5059 Optional<LValue> rhs =
5060 EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(*this, expr->getFalseExpr());
5061 eval.end(*this);
5062 if (rhs && !rhs->isSimple())
5063 return EmitUnsupportedLValue(expr, "conditional operator");
5064 rhsBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5065
5066 EmitBlock(contBlock);
5067
5068 if (lhs && rhs) {
5069 llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(lhs->getPointer()->getType(),
5070 2, "cond-lvalue");
5071 phi->addIncoming(lhs->getPointer(), lhsBlock);
5072 phi->addIncoming(rhs->getPointer(), rhsBlock);
5073 Address result(phi, std::min(lhs->getAlignment(), rhs->getAlignment()));
5074 AlignmentSource alignSource =
5075 std::max(lhs->getBaseInfo().getAlignmentSource(),
5076 rhs->getBaseInfo().getAlignmentSource());
5077 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo = CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForConditionalOperator(
5078 lhs->getTBAAInfo(), rhs->getTBAAInfo());
5079 return MakeAddrLValue(result, expr->getType(), LValueBaseInfo(alignSource),
5080 TBAAInfo);
5081 } else {
5082 assert((lhs || rhs) &&
5083 "both operands of glvalue conditional are throw-expressions?");
5084 return lhs ? *lhs : *rhs;
5085 }
5086}
5087
5088/// EmitCastLValue - Casts are never lvalues unless that cast is to a reference
5089/// type. If the cast is to a reference, we can have the usual lvalue result,
5090/// otherwise if a cast is needed by the code generator in an lvalue context,
5091/// then it must mean that we need the address of an aggregate in order to
5092/// access one of its members. This can happen for all the reasons that casts
5093/// are permitted with aggregate result, including noop aggregate casts, and
5094/// cast from scalar to union.
5095LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCastLValue(const CastExpr *E) {
5096 switch (E->getCastKind()) {
5097 case CK_ToVoid:
5098 case CK_BitCast:
5099 case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
5100 case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
5101 case CK_NullToMemberPointer:
5102 case CK_NullToPointer:
5103 case CK_IntegralToPointer:
5104 case CK_PointerToIntegral:
5105 case CK_PointerToBoolean:
5106 case CK_VectorSplat:
5107 case CK_IntegralCast:
5108 case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral:
5109 case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
5110 case CK_IntegralToFloating:
5111 case CK_FloatingToIntegral:
5112 case CK_FloatingToBoolean:
5113 case CK_FloatingCast:
5114 case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
5115 case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
5116 case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
5117 case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
5118 case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
5119 case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
5120 case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
5121 case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean:
5122 case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
5123 case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
5124 case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer:
5125 case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
5126 case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean:
5127 case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
5128 case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
5129 case CK_ARCProduceObject:
5130 case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
5131 case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
5132 case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
5133 case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
5134 case CK_CHERICapabilityToPointer:
5135 case CK_PointerToCHERICapability:
5136 case CK_CHERICapabilityToOffset:
5137 case CK_CHERICapabilityToAddress:
5138 case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
5139 case CK_FixedPointCast:
5140 case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
5141 case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
5142 case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
5143 return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "unexpected cast lvalue");
5144
5145 case CK_Dependent:
5146 llvm_unreachable("dependent cast kind in IR gen!");
5147
5148 case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
5149 llvm_unreachable("builtin functions are handled elsewhere");
5150
5151 // These are never l-values; just use the aggregate emission code.
5152 case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
5153 case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
5154 return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5155
5156 case CK_Dynamic: {
5157 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5158 Address V = LV.getAddress();
5159 const auto *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(E);
5160 return MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(EmitDynamicCast(V, DCE), E->getType());
5161 }
5162
5163 case CK_ConstructorConversion:
5164 case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
5165 case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
5166 case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
5167 case CK_NoOp:
5168 case CK_LValueToRValue:
5169 return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5170
5171 case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
5172 case CK_DerivedToBase: {
5173 const RecordType *DerivedClassTy =
5174 E->getSubExpr()->getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
5175 auto *DerivedClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DerivedClassTy->getDecl());
5176
5177 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5178 Address This = LV.getAddress();
5179
5180 // Perform the derived-to-base conversion
5181 Address Base = GetAddressOfBaseClass(
5182 This, DerivedClassDecl, E->path_begin(), E->path_end(),
5183 /*NullCheckValue=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
5184
5185 // TODO: Support accesses to members of base classes in TBAA. For now, we
5186 // conservatively pretend that the complete object is of the base class
5187 // type.
5188 return MakeAddrLValue(Base, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5189 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5190 }
5191 case CK_ToUnion:
5192 return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5193 case CK_BaseToDerived: {
5194 const RecordType *DerivedClassTy = E->getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
5195 auto *DerivedClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DerivedClassTy->getDecl());
5196
5197 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5198
5199 // Perform the base-to-derived conversion
5200 Address Derived =
5201 GetAddressOfDerivedClass(LV.getAddress(), DerivedClassDecl,
5202 E->path_begin(), E->path_end(),
5203 /*NullCheckValue=*/false);
5204
5205 // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p2: Behavior is undefined if a downcast is
5206 // performed and the object is not of the derived type.
5207 if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
5208 EmitTypeCheck(TCK_DowncastReference, E->getExprLoc(),
5209 Derived.getPointer(), E->getType());
5210
5211 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast))
5212 EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(E->getType(), Derived.getPointer(),
5213 /*MayBeNull=*/false, CFITCK_DerivedCast,
5214 E->getBeginLoc());
5215
5216 return MakeAddrLValue(Derived, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5217 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5218 }
5219 case CK_LValueBitCast: {
5220 // This must be a reinterpret_cast (or c-style equivalent).
5221 const auto *CE = cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E);
5222
5223 CGM.EmitExplicitCastExprType(CE, this);
5224 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5225 Address V = Builder.CreateBitCast(LV.getAddress(),
5226 ConvertType(CE->getTypeAsWritten()));
5227
5228 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast))
5229 EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(E->getType(), V.getPointer(),
5230 /*MayBeNull=*/false, CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
5231 E->getBeginLoc());
5232
5233 return MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5234 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5235 }
5236 case CK_AddressSpaceConversion: {
5237 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5238 QualType DestTy = getContext().getPointerType(E->getType());
5239 llvm::Value *V = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
5240 *this, LV.getPointer(), E->getSubExpr()->getType().getAddressSpace(),
5241 E->getType().getAddressSpace(), ConvertType(DestTy));
5242 return MakeAddrLValue(Address(V, LV.getAddress().getAlignment()),
5243 E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(), LV.getTBAAInfo());
5244 }
5245 case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast: {
5246 LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5247 Address V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(LV.getAddress(),
5248 ConvertType(E->getType()));
5249 return MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5250 CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5251 }
5252 case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType:
5253 llvm_unreachable("NULL to OpenCL opaque type lvalue cast is not valid");
5254 }
5255
5256 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled lvalue cast kind?");
5257}

5264LValue
5265CodeGenFunction::getOrCreateOpaqueLValueMapping(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
5266 assert(OpaqueValueMapping::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
5267
5268 llvm::DenseMap<const OpaqueValueExpr*,LValue>::iterator
5269 it = OpaqueLValues.find(e);
5270
5271 if (it != OpaqueLValues.end())
5272 return it->second;
5273

5284
5285 if (it != OpaqueRValues.end())

5292RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitRValueForField(LValue LV,
5293 const FieldDecl *FD,
5294 SourceLocation Loc) {
5295 QualType FT = FD->getType();
5296 LValue FieldLV = EmitLValueForField(LV, FD);
5297 switch (getEvaluationKind(FT)) {
5298 case TEK_Complex:
5299 return RValue::getComplex(EmitLoadOfComplex(FieldLV, Loc));
5300 case TEK_Aggregate:
5301 return FieldLV.asAggregateRValue();
5302 case TEK_Scalar:
5303 // This routine is used to load fields one-by-one to perform a copy, so
5304 // don't load reference fields.
5305 if (FD->getType()->isReferenceType())
5306 return RValue::get(FieldLV.getPointer(),
5307 FieldLV.getAlignment().getQuantity());
5308 return EmitLoadOfLValue(FieldLV, Loc);
5309 }
5310 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5311}

5314// Expression Emission
5315//===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5316
5317RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
5318 ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
5319 // Builtins never have block type.
5320 if (E->getCallee()->getType()->isBlockPointerType())
5321 return EmitBlockCallExpr(E, ReturnValue);
5322
5323 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CXXMemberCallExpr>(E))
5324 return EmitCXXMemberCallExpr(CE, ReturnValue);
5325
5326 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CUDAKernelCallExpr>(E))
5327 return EmitCUDAKernelCallExpr(CE, ReturnValue);
5328
5329 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E))
5330 if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD =
5331 dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(CE->getCalleeDecl()))
5332 return EmitCXXOperatorMemberCallExpr(CE, MD, ReturnValue);
5333
5334 CGCallee callee = EmitCallee(E->getCallee());
5335
5336 if (callee.isBuiltin()) {
5337 return EmitBuiltinExpr(callee.getBuiltinDecl(), callee.getBuiltinID(),
5338 E, ReturnValue);
5339 }
5340
5341 if (callee.isPseudoDestructor()) {
5342 return EmitCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(callee.getPseudoDestructorExpr());
5343 }
5344
5345 return EmitCall(E->getCallee()->getType(), callee, E, ReturnValue);
5346}

5348/// Emit a CallExpr without considering whether it might be a subclass.
5349RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitSimpleCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
5350 ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
5351 CGCallee Callee = EmitCallee(E->getCallee());
5352 return EmitCall(E->getCallee()->getType(), Callee, E, ReturnValue);
5353}
5354
5355static CGCallee EmitDirectCallee(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const FunctionDecl *FD) {
5356 if (auto builtinID = FD->getBuiltinID()) {
5357 return CGCallee::forBuiltin(builtinID, FD);
5358 }
5359
5360 llvm::Value *calleePtr = EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CGF, FD, /*IsDirectCall=*/true);
5361 return CGCallee(GlobalDecl(FD), calleePtr);
5362}
5363
5364CGCallee CodeGenFunction::EmitCallee(const Expr *E) {
5365 E = E->IgnoreParens();
5366
5367 // Look through function-to-pointer decay.
5368 if (auto ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
5369 if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_FunctionToPointerDecay ||
5370 ICE->getCastKind() == CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr) {
5371 return EmitCallee(ICE->getSubExpr());
5372 }
5373
5374 // Resolve direct calls.
5375 } else if (auto DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
5376 if (auto FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
5377 return EmitDirectCallee(*this, FD);
5378 }
5379 } else if (auto ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
5380 if (auto FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
5381 EmitIgnoredExpr(ME->getBase());
5382 return EmitDirectCallee(*this, FD);
5383 }
5384
5385 // Look through template substitutions.
5386 } else if (auto NTTP = dyn_cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)) {
5387 return EmitCallee(NTTP->getReplacement());
5388
5389 // Treat pseudo-destructor calls differently.
5390 } else if (auto PDE = dyn_cast<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(E)) {
5391 return CGCallee::forPseudoDestructor(PDE);
5392 }
5393
5394 // Otherwise, we have an indirect reference.
5395 llvm::Value *calleePtr;
5396 QualType functionType;
5397 if (auto ptrType = E->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
5398 calleePtr = EmitScalarExpr(E);
5399 functionType = ptrType->getPointeeType();
5400 } else {
5401 functionType = E->getType();
5402 calleePtr = EmitLValue(E).getPointer();
5403 }
5404 assert(functionType->isFunctionType());
5405
5406 GlobalDecl GD;
5407 if (const auto *VD =
5408 dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(E->getReferencedDeclOfCallee()))
5409 GD = GlobalDecl(VD);
5410
5411 CGCalleeInfo calleeInfo(functionType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>(), GD);
5412 CGCallee callee(calleeInfo, calleePtr);
5413 return callee;
5414}
5415
5416LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitBinaryOperatorLValue(const BinaryOperator *E) {
5417 // Comma expressions just emit their LHS then their RHS as an l-value.
5418 if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
5419 EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getLHS());
5420 EnsureInsertPoint();
5421 return EmitLValue(E->getRHS());
5422 }
5423
5424 if (E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemD ||
5425 E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI)
5426 return EmitPointerToDataMemberBinaryExpr(E);
5427
5428 assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_Assign && "unexpected binary l-value");
5429
5430 // Note that in all of these cases, __block variables need the RHS
5431 // evaluated first just in case the variable gets moved by the RHS.
5432
5433 switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
5434 case TEK_Scalar: {
5435 switch (E->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
5436 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
5437 return EmitARCStoreStrong(E, /*ignored*/ false).first;
5438
5439 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
5440 return EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(E).first;
5441
5442 // No reason to do any of these differently.
5443 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
5444 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
5445 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
5446 break;
5447 }
5448
5449 RValue RV = EmitAnyExpr(E->getRHS());
5450 LValue LV = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), TCK_Store);
5451 if (RV.isScalar())
5452 EmitNullabilityCheck(LV, RV.getScalarVal(), E->getExprLoc());
5453 EmitStoreThroughLValue(RV, LV);
5454 return LV;
5455 }
5456
5457 case TEK_Complex:
5458 return EmitComplexAssignmentLValue(E);
5459
5460 case TEK_Aggregate:
5461 return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5462 }
5463 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5464}

5580
5581RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCall(QualType CalleeType, const CGCallee &OrigCallee,
5582 const CallExpr *E, ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
5583 llvm::Value *Chain) {
5584 // Get the actual function type. The callee type will always be a pointer to
5585 // function type or a block pointer type.
5586 assert(CalleeType->isFunctionPointerType() &&
5587 "Call must have function pointer type!");
5588
5589 const Decl *TargetDecl =
5590 OrigCallee.getAbstractInfo().getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
5591
5592 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))
5593 // We can only guarantee that a function is called from the correct
5594 // context/function based on the appropriate target attributes,
5595 // so only check in the case where we have both always_inline and target
5596 // since otherwise we could be making a conditional call after a check for
5597 // the proper cpu features (and it won't cause code generation issues due to
5598 // function based code generation).
5599 if (TargetDecl->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>() &&
5600 TargetDecl->hasAttr<TargetAttr>())
5601 checkTargetFeatures(E, FD);
5602
5603 CalleeType = getContext().getCanonicalType(CalleeType);
5604
5605 auto PointeeType = cast<PointerType>(CalleeType)->getPointeeType();
5606
5607 CGCallee Callee = OrigCallee;
5608
5609 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Function) &&
5610 (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
5611 if (llvm::Constant *PrefixSig =
5612 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getUBSanFunctionSignature(CGM)) {
5613 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5614 // Remove any (C++17) exception specifications, to allow calling e.g. a
5615 // noexcept function through a non-noexcept pointer.
5616 auto ProtoTy =
5617 getContext().getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(PointeeType, EST_None);
5618 llvm::Constant *FTRTTIConst =
5619 CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(ProtoTy, /*ForEH=*/true);
5620 llvm::Type *PrefixStructTyElems[] = {PrefixSig->getType(), Int32Ty};
5621 llvm::StructType *PrefixStructTy = llvm::StructType::get(
5622 CGM.getLLVMContext(), PrefixStructTyElems, /*isPacked=*/true);
5623
5624 llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5625
5626 llvm::Value *CalleePrefixStruct = Builder.CreateBitCast(
5627 CalleePtr, CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(PrefixStructTy));
5628 llvm::Value *CalleeSigPtr =
5629 Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(PrefixStructTy, CalleePrefixStruct, 0, 0);
5630 llvm::Value *CalleeSig =
5631 Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(CalleeSigPtr, getIntAlign());
5632 llvm::Value *CalleeSigMatch = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CalleeSig, PrefixSig);
5633
5634 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
5635 llvm::BasicBlock *TypeCheck = createBasicBlock("typecheck");
5636 Builder.CreateCondBr(CalleeSigMatch, TypeCheck, Cont);
5637
5638 EmitBlock(TypeCheck);
5639 llvm::Value *CalleeRTTIPtr =
5640 Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(PrefixStructTy, CalleePrefixStruct, 0, 1);
5641 llvm::Value *CalleeRTTIEncoded =
5642 Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(CalleeRTTIPtr, getPointerAlign());
5643 llvm::Value *CalleeRTTI =
5644 DecodeAddrUsedInPrologue(CalleePtr, CalleeRTTIEncoded);
5645 llvm::Value *CalleeRTTIMatch =
5646 Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CalleeRTTI, FTRTTIConst);
5647 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc()),
5648 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(CalleeType)};
5649 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(CalleeRTTIMatch, SanitizerKind::Function),
5650 SanitizerHandler::FunctionTypeMismatch, StaticData,
5651 {CalleePtr, CalleeRTTI, FTRTTIConst});
5652
5653 Builder.CreateBr(Cont);
5654 EmitBlock(Cont);
5655 }
5656 }
5657
5658 const auto *FnType = cast<FunctionType>(PointeeType);
5659
5660 // If we are checking indirect calls and this call is indirect, check that the
5661 // function pointer is a member of the bit set for the function type.
5662 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall) &&
5663 (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
5664 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5665 EmitSanitizerStatReport(llvm::SanStat_CFI_ICall);
5666
5667 llvm::Metadata *MD;
5668 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallGeneralizePointers)
5669 MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(QualType(FnType, 0));
5670 else
5671 MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(FnType, 0));
5672
5673 llvm::Value *TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(getLLVMContext(), MD);
5674
5675 llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5676 llvm::Value *CastedCallee = Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, Int8PtrTy);
5677 llvm::Value *TypeTest = Builder.CreateCall(
5678 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {CastedCallee, TypeId});
5679
5680 auto CrossDsoTypeId = CGM.CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD);
5681 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
5682 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, CFITCK_ICall),
5683 EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc()),
5684 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType(FnType, 0)),
5685 };
5686 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiCrossDso && CrossDsoTypeId) {
5687 EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(SanitizerKind::CFIICall, TypeTest, CrossDsoTypeId,
5688 CastedCallee, StaticData);
5689 } else {
5690 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(TypeTest, SanitizerKind::CFIICall),
5691 SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
5692 {CastedCallee, llvm::UndefValue::get(IntPtrTy)});
5693 }
5694 }
5695
5696 CallArgList Args;
5697 if (Chain)
5698 Args.add(RValue::get(Builder.CreateBitCast(Chain, CGM.VoidPtrTy)),
5699 CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
5700
5701 // C++17 requires that we evaluate arguments to a call using assignment syntax
5702 // right-to-left, and that we evaluate arguments to certain other operators
5703 // left-to-right. Note that we allow this to override the order dictated by
5704 // the calling convention on the MS ABI, which means that parameter
5705 // destruction order is not necessarily reverse construction order.
5706 // FIXME: Revisit this based on C++ committee response to unimplementability.
5707 EvaluationOrder Order = EvaluationOrder::Default;
5708 if (auto *OCE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E)) {
5709 if (OCE->isAssignmentOp())
5710 Order = EvaluationOrder::ForceRightToLeft;
5711 else {
5712 switch (OCE->getOperator()) {
5713 case OO_LessLess:
5714 case OO_GreaterGreater:
5715 case OO_AmpAmp:
5716 case OO_PipePipe:
5717 case OO_Comma:
5718 case OO_ArrowStar:
5719 Order = EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight;
5720 break;
5721 default:
5722 break;
5723 }
5724 }
5725 }
5726
5727 EmitCallArgs(Args, dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType), E->arguments(),
5728 E->getDirectCallee(), /*ParamsToSkip*/ 0, Order);
5729
5730 bool CallCHERIInvoke = false;
5731 // For CHERI callbacks, the function 'pointer' is actually a struct
5732 // containing all of the information required for a cross domain call.
5733 // Note: It doesn't actually matter what the order of the number and class
5734 // are, as they will be in a different category of register. This is *not*
5735 // necessarily the case for implementations that have a merged register file!
5736 if (FnType->getCallConv() == CC_CHERICCallback) {
5737 CallCHERIInvoke = true;
5738 SmallVector<QualType, 16> NewParams;
5739 // Add the method number
5740 auto *MethodNum = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Callee.getFunctionPointer(), {1});
5741 auto NumTy = getContext().UnsignedLongLongTy;
5742 CallArg MethodNumArg(RValue::get(MethodNum), NumTy);
5743 NewParams.push_back(NumTy);
5744 Args.insert(Args.begin(), MethodNumArg);
5745 // Add the CHERI object
5746 auto *Obj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Callee.getFunctionPointer(), {0});
5747 auto ObjTy = getContext().getCHERIClassType();
5748 CallArg ObjArg(RValue::get(Obj), ObjTy);
5749 NewParams.push_back(ObjTy);
5750 Args.insert(Args.begin(), ObjArg);
5751
5752 auto *FnPType = cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType);
5753 auto Params = FnPType->getParamTypes();
5754 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FnPType->getExtProtoInfo();
5755 NewParams.insert(NewParams.end(), Params.begin(), Params.end());
5756 FnType = getContext().getFunctionType(FnPType->getReturnType(),
5757 NewParams, EPI)->getAs<FunctionType>();
5758 } else if (FnType->getCallConv() == CC_CHERICCall &&
5759 TargetDecl->hasAttr<CHERIMethodClassAttr>()) {
5760 assert(TargetDecl);
5761 StringRef Suffix = TargetDecl->hasAttr<CHERIMethodSuffixAttr>() ?
5762 TargetDecl->getAttr<CHERIMethodSuffixAttr>()->getSuffix() : "";
5763 CallCHERIInvoke = true;
5764 SmallVector<QualType, 16> NewParams;
5765 auto NumTy = getContext().UnsignedLongLongTy;
5766 auto *ClsAttr = TargetDecl->getAttr<CHERIMethodClassAttr>();
5767 StringRef FunctionBaseName = cast<NamedDecl>(TargetDecl)->getName();
5768 FunctionBaseName = FunctionBaseName.substr(0, FunctionBaseName.size() -
5769 Suffix.size());
5770 auto *MethodNumVar =
5771 CGM.EmitSandboxRequiredMethod(ClsAttr->getDefaultClass()->getName(),
5772 FunctionBaseName);
5773 // Load the global and use it in the call
5774 // FIXME: EmitSandboxRequiredMethod should return an Address so that we
5775 // don't have to know the alignment here.
5776 auto *MethodNum = Builder.CreateLoad(Address(MethodNumVar, CharUnits::fromQuantity(8)));
5777 MethodNum->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("invariant.load"),
5778 llvm::MDNode::get(getLLVMContext(), None));
5779 CallArg MethodNumArg(RValue::get(MethodNum), NumTy);
5780 NewParams.push_back(NumTy);
5781 // If we have a non-empty suffix, then we're not the version of the method
5782 // that takes an explicit class, we're the version with the same explicit
5783 // parameters and extra implicit ones for the default class, so add the
5784 // default class.
5785 if (Suffix.size() == 0) {
5786 // FIXME: We should silently insert a common-linkage global if the class
5787 // isn't declared.
5788 DeclarationName DN(ClsAttr->getDefaultClass());
5789 auto *TU = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
5790 auto Cls = cast<VarDecl>(TU->lookup(DN)[0]);
5791 llvm::Value *V = CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(Cls);
5792 auto ClsTy = Cls->getType();
5793 llvm::Type *RealVarTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ClsTy);
5794 V = EmitBitCastOfLValueToProperType(*this, V, RealVarTy);
5795 CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getDeclAlign(Cls);
5796 LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(V, ClsTy, Alignment);
5797 Address A1 = Builder.CreateStructGEP(LV.getAddress(), 0, "arg1");
5798 Address A2 = Builder.CreateStructGEP(LV.getAddress(), 1, "arg2");
5799 auto Fields = ClsTy->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl()->fields();
5800 auto FieldsIt = Fields.begin();
5801 assert(std::distance(Fields.begin(), Fields.end()) == 2);
5802 QualType Ty1 = FieldsIt->getType();
5803 QualType Ty2 = (++FieldsIt)->getType();
5804 CallArg Arg1(RValue::get(Builder.CreateLoad(A1)), Ty1);
5805 CallArg Arg2(RValue::get(Builder.CreateLoad(A2)), Ty2);
5806 Args.insert(Args.begin(), MethodNumArg);
5807 Args.insert(Args.begin(), Arg2);
5808 Args.insert(Args.begin(), Arg1);
5809 NewParams.push_back(ClsTy);
5810 } else {
5811 Args.insert(Args.begin()+1, MethodNumArg);
5812 }
5813 auto *FnPType = cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType);
5814 auto Params = FnPType->getParamTypes();
5815 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FnPType->getExtProtoInfo();
5816 NewParams.insert(NewParams.end(), Params.begin(), Params.end());
5817 FnType = getContext().getFunctionType(FnPType->getReturnType(),
5818 NewParams, EPI)->getAs<FunctionType>();
5819 }
5820 const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo = CGM.getTypes().arrangeFreeFunctionCall(
5821 Args, FnType, /*isChainCall=*/Chain);
5822
5823 if (CallCHERIInvoke)
5824 Callee.setFunctionPointer(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction("cheri_invoke",
5825 getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo)).getCallee());
5826
5827 // C99 6.5.2.2p6:
5828 // If the expression that denotes the called function has a type
5829 // that does not include a prototype, [the default argument
5830 // promotions are performed]. If the number of arguments does not
5831 // equal the number of parameters, the behavior is undefined. If
5832 // the function is defined with a type that includes a prototype,
5833 // and either the prototype ends with an ellipsis (, ...) or the
5834 // types of the arguments after promotion are not compatible with
5835 // the types of the parameters, the behavior is undefined. If the
5836 // function is defined with a type that does not include a
5837 // prototype, and the types of the arguments after promotion are
5838 // not compatible with those of the parameters after promotion,
5839 // the behavior is undefined [except in some trivial cases].
5840 // That is, in the general case, we should assume that a call
5841 // through an unprototyped function type works like a *non-variadic*
5842 // call. The way we make this work is to cast to the exact type
5843 // of the promoted arguments.
5844 //
5845 // Chain calls use this same code path to add the invisible chain parameter
5846 // to the function type.
5847 if (isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(FnType) || Chain) {
5848 llvm::Type *CalleeTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
5849
5850 llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5851 CalleeTy =
5852 CalleeTy->getPointerTo(CalleePtr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
5853 CalleePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, CalleeTy, "callee.knr.cast");
5854 Callee.setFunctionPointer(CalleePtr);
5855 }
5856
5857 auto ret = EmitCall(FnInfo, Callee, ReturnValue, Args, nullptr, E->getExprLoc());
5858 // If we're doing a CHERI ccall in C++ mode and have exceptions enabled, then
5859 // translate the CHERI errno value into an exception.
5860 if (CallCHERIInvoke && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && getLangOpts().Exceptions &&
5861 TargetDecl && !TargetDecl->hasAttr<NoThrowAttr>()) {
5862 auto &M = CGM.getModule();
5863 auto *CHERIErrno = M.getNamedGlobal("cheri_errno");
5864 if (!CHERIErrno) {
5865 CHERIErrno = new llvm::GlobalVariable(M, IntTy,
5866 /*isConstant*/false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
5867 nullptr, "cheri_errno", nullptr, llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
5868 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTlsAddressSpace());
5869 CHERIErrno->setThreadLocal(true);
5870 }
5871 // FIXME: Don't hard code 4-byte alignment for int!
5872 auto *ErrVal = Builder.CreateLoad(Address(CHERIErrno, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4)));
5873 auto *IsZero = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(ErrVal,
5874 llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ErrVal->getType()));
5875 auto *Continue = createBasicBlock("cheri_invoke_continue");
5876 auto *Error = createBasicBlock("cheri_invoke_fail");
5877 Builder.CreateCondBr(IsZero, Continue, Error);
5878 llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, IntTy, false);
5879 llvm::AttrBuilder B;
5880 B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn);
5881 llvm::FunctionCallee ErrorFn =
5882 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_cheri_sandbox_invoke_failure",
5883 llvm::AttributeList::get(getLLVMContext(),
5884 llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B));
5885 EmitBlock(Error);
5886 Builder.CreateCall(ErrorFn, ErrVal);
5887 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
5888 EmitBlock(Continue);
5889 }
5890 return ret;
5891}
5892
5893LValue CodeGenFunction::
5894EmitPointerToDataMemberBinaryExpr(const BinaryOperator *E) {
5895 Address BaseAddr = Address::invalid();
5896 if (E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI) {
5897 BaseAddr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getLHS());
5898 } else {
5899 BaseAddr = EmitLValue(E->getLHS()).getAddress();
5900 }
5901
5902 llvm::Value *OffsetV = EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
5903
5904 const MemberPointerType *MPT
5905 = E->getRHS()->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
5906
5907 LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
5908 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
5909 Address MemberAddr =
5910 EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(E, BaseAddr, OffsetV, MPT, &BaseInfo,
5911 &TBAAInfo);
5912
5913 return MakeAddrLValue(MemberAddr, MPT->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
5914}

5916/// Given the address of a temporary variable, produce an r-value of
5917/// its type.
5918RValue CodeGenFunction::convertTempToRValue(Address addr,
5919 QualType type,
5920 SourceLocation loc) {
5921 LValue lvalue = MakeAddrLValue(addr, type, AlignmentSource::Decl);
5922 switch (getEvaluationKind(type)) {
5923 case TEK_Complex:
5924 return RValue::getComplex(EmitLoadOfComplex(lvalue, loc));
5925 case TEK_Aggregate:
5926 return lvalue.asAggregateRValue();
5927 case TEK_Scalar:
5928 return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(lvalue, loc));
5929 }
5930 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5931}

5933void CodeGenFunction::SetFPAccuracy(llvm::Value *Val, float Accuracy) {
5934 assert(Val->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy());
5935 if (Accuracy == 0.0 || !isa<llvm::Instruction>(Val))
5936 return;
5937
5938 llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
5939 llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createFPMath(Accuracy);
5940
5941 cast<llvm::Instruction>(Val)->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_fpmath, Node);
5942}

5944namespace {
5945 struct LValueOrRValue {
5946 LValue LV;
5947 RValue RV;
5948 };
5949}
5950
5951static LValueOrRValue emitPseudoObjectExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5952 const PseudoObjectExpr *E,
5953 bool forLValue,
5954 AggValueSlot slot) {
5955 SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData, 4> opaques;
5956
5957 // Find the result expression, if any.
5958 const Expr *resultExpr = E->getResultExpr();
5959 LValueOrRValue result;
5960
5961 for (PseudoObjectExpr::const_semantics_iterator
5962 i = E->semantics_begin(), e = E->semantics_end(); i != e; ++i) {
5963 const Expr *semantic = *i;
5964
5965 // If this semantic expression is an opaque value, bind it
5966 // to the result of its source expression.
5967 if (const auto *ov = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(semantic)) {
5968 // Skip unique OVEs.
5969 if (ov->isUnique()) {
5970 assert(ov != resultExpr &&
5971 "A unique OVE cannot be used as the result expression");
5972 continue;
5973 }
5974
5975 // If this is the result expression, we may need to evaluate
5976 // directly into the slot.
5977 typedef CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData OVMA;
5978 OVMA opaqueData;
5979 if (ov == resultExpr && ov->isRValue() && !forLValue &&
5980 CodeGenFunction::hasAggregateEvaluationKind(ov->getType())) {
5981 CGF.EmitAggExpr(ov->getSourceExpr(), slot);
5982 LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(slot.getAddress(), ov->getType(),
5983 AlignmentSource::Decl);
5984 opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, LV);
5985 result.RV = slot.asRValue();
5986
5987 // Otherwise, emit as normal.
5988 } else {
5989 opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, ov->getSourceExpr());
5990
5991 // If this is the result, also evaluate the result now.
5992 if (ov == resultExpr) {
5993 if (forLValue)
5994 result.LV = CGF.EmitLValue(ov);
5995 else
5996 result.RV = CGF.EmitAnyExpr(ov, slot);
5997 }
5998 }
5999
6000 opaques.push_back(opaqueData);
6001
6002 // Otherwise, if the expression is the result, evaluate it
6003 // and remember the result.
6004 } else if (semantic == resultExpr) {
6005 if (forLValue)
6006 result.LV = CGF.EmitLValue(semantic);
6007 else
6008 result.RV = CGF.EmitAnyExpr(semantic, slot);
6009
6010 // Otherwise, evaluate the expression in an ignored context.
6011 } else {
6012 CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(semantic);
6013 }
6014 }
6015
6016 // Unbind all the opaques now.
6017 for (unsigned i = 0, e = opaques.size(); i != e; ++i)
6018 opaques[i].unbind(CGF);
6019
6020 return result;
6021}
6022
6023RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPseudoObjectRValue(const PseudoObjectExpr *E,
6024 AggValueSlot slot) {
6025 return emitPseudoObjectExpr(*this, E, false, slot).RV;
6026}
6027
6028LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPseudoObjectLValue(const PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
6029 return emitPseudoObjectExpr(*this, E, true, AggValueSlot::ignored()).LV;
6030}
